6748 template<typename BasicJsonType>
6749 class lexer_base
6750 {
6751  public:
6753  enum class token_type
6754  {
6755  uninitialized,
6756  literal_true,
6757  literal_false,
6758  literal_null,
6759  value_string,
6760  value_unsigned,
6761  value_integer,
6762  value_float,
6763  begin_array,
6764  begin_object,
6765  end_array,
6766  end_object,
6767  name_separator,
6768  value_separator,
6769  parse_error,
6770  end_of_input,
6771  literal_or_value
6772  };
6773 
6775  JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
6776  JSON_HEDLEY_CONST
6777  static const char* token_type_name(const token_type t) noexcept
6778  {
6779  switch (t)
6780  {
6781  case token_type::uninitialized:
6782  return "<uninitialized>";
6783  case token_type::literal_true:
6784  return "true literal";
6785  case token_type::literal_false:
6786  return "false literal";
6787  case token_type::literal_null:
6788  return "null literal";
6789  case token_type::value_string:
6790  return "string literal";
6791  case token_type::value_unsigned:
6792  case token_type::value_integer:
6793  case token_type::value_float:
6794  return "number literal";
6795  case token_type::begin_array:
6796  return "'['";
6797  case token_type::begin_object:
6798  return "'{'";
6799  case token_type::end_array:
6800  return "']'";
6801  case token_type::end_object:
6802  return "'}'";
6803  case token_type::name_separator:
6804  return "':'";
6805  case token_type::value_separator:
6806  return "','";
6807  case token_type::parse_error:
6808  return "<parse error>";
6809  case token_type::end_of_input:
6810  return "end of input";
6811  case token_type::literal_or_value:
6812  return "'[', '{', or a literal";
6813  // LCOV_EXCL_START
6814  default: // catch non-enum values
6815  return "unknown token";
6816  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
6817  }
6818  }
6819 };
6825 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename InputAdapterType>
6826 class lexer : public lexer_base<BasicJsonType>
6827 {
6828  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
6829  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
6830  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
6831  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
6832  using char_type = typename InputAdapterType::char_type;
6833  using char_int_type = typename std::char_traits<char_type>::int_type;
6834 
6835  public:
6836  using token_type = typename lexer_base<BasicJsonType>::token_type;
6837 
6838  explicit lexer(InputAdapterType&& adapter, bool ignore_comments_ = false) noexcept
6839  : ia(std::move(adapter))
6840  , ignore_comments(ignore_comments_)
6841  , decimal_point_char(static_cast<char_int_type>(get_decimal_point()))
6842  {}
6843 
6844  // delete because of pointer members
6845  lexer(const lexer&) = delete;
6846  lexer(lexer&&) = default; // NOLINT(hicpp-noexcept-move,performance-noexcept-move-constructor)
6847  lexer& operator=(lexer&) = delete;
6848  lexer& operator=(lexer&&) = default; // NOLINT(hicpp-noexcept-move,performance-noexcept-move-constructor)
6849  ~lexer() = default;
6850 
6851  private:
6853  // locales
6855 
6857  JSON_HEDLEY_PURE
6858  static char get_decimal_point() noexcept
6859  {
6860  const auto* loc = localeconv();
6861  JSON_ASSERT(loc != nullptr);
6862  return (loc->decimal_point == nullptr) ? '.' : *(loc->decimal_point);
6863  }
6864 
6866  // scan functions
6868 
6884  int get_codepoint()
6885  {
6886  // this function only makes sense after reading `\u`
6887  JSON_ASSERT(current == 'u');
6888  int codepoint = 0;
6889 
6890  const auto factors = { 12u, 8u, 4u, 0u };
6891  for (const auto factor : factors)
6892  {
6893  get();
6894 
6895  if (current >= '0' && current <= '9')
6896  {
6897  codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x30u) << factor);
6898  }
6899  else if (current >= 'A' && current <= 'F')
6900  {
6901  codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x37u) << factor);
6902  }
6903  else if (current >= 'a' && current <= 'f')
6904  {
6905  codepoint += static_cast<int>((static_cast<unsigned int>(current) - 0x57u) << factor);
6906  }
6907  else
6908  {
6909  return -1;
6910  }
6911  }
6912 
6913  JSON_ASSERT(0x0000 <= codepoint && codepoint <= 0xFFFF);
6914  return codepoint;
6915  }
6916 
6932  bool next_byte_in_range(std::initializer_list<char_int_type> ranges)
6933  {
6934  JSON_ASSERT(ranges.size() == 2 || ranges.size() == 4 || ranges.size() == 6);
6935  add(current);
6936 
6937  for (auto range = ranges.begin(); range != ranges.end(); ++range)
6938  {
6939  get();
6940  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(*range <= current && current <= *(++range)))
6941  {
6942  add(current);
6943  }
6944  else
6945  {
6946  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
6947  return false;
6948  }
6949  }
6950 
6951  return true;
6952  }
6953 
6969  token_type scan_string()
6970  {
6971  // reset token_buffer (ignore opening quote)
6972  reset();
6973 
6974  // we entered the function by reading an open quote
6975  JSON_ASSERT(current == '\"');
6976 
6977  while (true)
6978  {
6979  // get next character
6980  switch (get())
6981  {
6982  // end of file while parsing string
6983  case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
6984  {
6985  error_message = "invalid string: missing closing quote";
6986  return token_type::parse_error;
6987  }
6988 
6989  // closing quote
6990  case '\"':
6991  {
6992  return token_type::value_string;
6993  }
6994 
6995  // escapes
6996  case '\\':
6997  {
6998  switch (get())
6999  {
7000  // quotation mark
7001  case '\"':
7002  add('\"');
7003  break;
7004  // reverse solidus
7005  case '\\':
7006  add('\\');
7007  break;
7008  // solidus
7009  case '/':
7010  add('/');
7011  break;
7012  // backspace
7013  case 'b':
7014  add('\b');
7015  break;
7016  // form feed
7017  case 'f':
7018  add('\f');
7019  break;
7020  // line feed
7021  case 'n':
7022  add('\n');
7023  break;
7024  // carriage return
7025  case 'r':
7026  add('\r');
7027  break;
7028  // tab
7029  case 't':
7030  add('\t');
7031  break;
7032 
7033  // unicode escapes
7034  case 'u':
7035  {
7036  const int codepoint1 = get_codepoint();
7037  int codepoint = codepoint1; // start with codepoint1
7038 
7039  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(codepoint1 == -1))
7040  {
7041  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
7042  return token_type::parse_error;
7043  }
7044 
7045  // check if code point is a high surrogate
7046  if (0xD800 <= codepoint1 && codepoint1 <= 0xDBFF)
7047  {
7048  // expect next \uxxxx entry
7049  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(get() == '\\' && get() == 'u'))
7050  {
7051  const int codepoint2 = get_codepoint();
7052 
7053  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(codepoint2 == -1))
7054  {
7055  error_message = "invalid string: '\\u' must be followed by 4 hex digits";
7056  return token_type::parse_error;
7057  }
7058 
7059  // check if codepoint2 is a low surrogate
7060  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint2 && codepoint2 <= 0xDFFF))
7061  {
7062  // overwrite codepoint
7063  codepoint = static_cast<int>(
7064  // high surrogate occupies the most significant 22 bits
7065  (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint1) << 10u)
7066  // low surrogate occupies the least significant 15 bits
7067  + static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint2)
7068  // there is still the 0xD800, 0xDC00 and 0x10000 noise
7069  // in the result, so we have to subtract with:
7070  // (0xD800 << 10) + DC00 - 0x10000 = 0x35FDC00
7071  - 0x35FDC00u);
7072  }
7073  else
7074  {
7075  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+D800..U+DBFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
7076  return token_type::parse_error;
7077  }
7078  }
7079  else
7080  {
7081  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+D800..U+DBFF must be followed by U+DC00..U+DFFF";
7082  return token_type::parse_error;
7083  }
7084  }
7085  else
7086  {
7087  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(0xDC00 <= codepoint1 && codepoint1 <= 0xDFFF))
7088  {
7089  error_message = "invalid string: surrogate U+DC00..U+DFFF must follow U+D800..U+DBFF";
7090  return token_type::parse_error;
7091  }
7092  }
7093 
7094  // result of the above calculation yields a proper codepoint
7095  JSON_ASSERT(0x00 <= codepoint && codepoint <= 0x10FFFF);
7096 
7097  // translate codepoint into bytes
7098  if (codepoint < 0x80)
7099  {
7100  // 1-byte characters: 0xxxxxxx (ASCII)
7101  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(codepoint));
7102  }
7103  else if (codepoint <= 0x7FF)
7104  {
7105  // 2-byte characters: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx
7106  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0xC0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u)));
7107  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
7108  }
7109  else if (codepoint <= 0xFFFF)
7110  {
7111  // 3-byte characters: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
7112  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0xE0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u)));
7113  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
7114  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
7115  }
7116  else
7117  {
7118  // 4-byte characters: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx
7119  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0xF0u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 18u)));
7120  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 12u) & 0x3Fu)));
7121  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | ((static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) >> 6u) & 0x3Fu)));
7122  add(static_cast<char_int_type>(0x80u | (static_cast<unsigned int>(codepoint) & 0x3Fu)));
7123  }
7124 
7125  break;
7126  }
7127 
7128  // other characters after escape
7129  default:
7130  error_message = "invalid string: forbidden character after backslash";
7131  return token_type::parse_error;
7132  }
7133 
7134  break;
7135  }
7136 
7137  // invalid control characters
7138  case 0x00:
7139  {
7140  error_message = "invalid string: control character U+0000 (NUL) must be escaped to \\u0000";
7141  return token_type::parse_error;
7142  }
7143 
7144  case 0x01:

7435  case 0xC6:
7436  case 0xC7:
7437  case 0xC8:
7438  case 0xC9:
7439  case 0xCA:
7440  case 0xCB:
7441  case 0xCC:
7442  case 0xCD:

7450  case 0xD5:
7451  case 0xD6:
7452  case 0xD7:
7453  case 0xD8:
7454  case 0xD9:
7455  case 0xDA:
7456  case 0xDB:
7457  case 0xDC:
7458  case 0xDD:
7459  case 0xDE:
7460  case 0xDF:
7461  {

7463  {
7464  return token_type::parse_error;
7465  }
7466  break;
7467  }
7468 
7469  // U+0800..U+0FFF: bytes E0 A0..BF 80..BF
7470  case 0xE0:
7471  {
7472  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0xA0, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
7473  {
7474  return token_type::parse_error;
7475  }
7476  break;
7477  }
7478 
7479  // U+1000..U+CFFF: bytes E1..EC 80..BF 80..BF
7480  // U+E000..U+FFFF: bytes EE..EF 80..BF 80..BF
7481  case 0xE1:
7482  case 0xE2:
7483  case 0xE3:
7484  case 0xE4:
7485  case 0xE5:
7486  case 0xE6:
7487  case 0xE7:
7488  case 0xE8:
7489  case 0xE9:
7490  case 0xEA:
7491  case 0xEB:
7492  case 0xEC:
7493  case 0xEE:
7494  case 0xEF:
7495  {
7496  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
7497  {
7498  return token_type::parse_error;
7499  }
7500  break;
7501  }
7502 
7503  // U+D000..U+D7FF: bytes ED 80..9F 80..BF
7504  case 0xED:
7505  {
7506  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x9F, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
7507  {
7508  return token_type::parse_error;
7509  }
7510  break;
7511  }
7512 
7513  // U+10000..U+3FFFF F0 90..BF 80..BF 80..BF
7514  case 0xF0:
7515  {
7516  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x90, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
7517  {
7518  return token_type::parse_error;
7519  }
7520  break;
7521  }
7522 
7523  // U+40000..U+FFFFF F1..F3 80..BF 80..BF 80..BF
7524  case 0xF1:
7525  case 0xF2:
7526  case 0xF3:
7527  {
7528  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
7529  {
7530  return token_type::parse_error;
7531  }
7532  break;
7533  }
7534 
7535  // U+100000..U+10FFFF F4 80..8F 80..BF 80..BF
7536  case 0xF4:
7537  {
7538  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(next_byte_in_range({0x80, 0x8F, 0x80, 0xBF, 0x80, 0xBF}))))
7539  {
7540  return token_type::parse_error;
7541  }
7542  break;
7543  }
7544 
7545  // remaining bytes (80..C1 and F5..FF) are ill-formed
7546  default:
7547  {
7548  error_message = "invalid string: ill-formed UTF-8 byte";
7549  return token_type::parse_error;
7550  }
7551  }
7552  }
7553  }
7554 
7559  bool scan_comment()
7560  {
7561  switch (get())
7562  {
7563  // single-line comments skip input until a newline or EOF is read
7564  case '/':
7565  {
7566  while (true)
7567  {
7568  switch (get())
7569  {
7570  case '\n':
7571  case '\r':
7572  case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
7573  case '\0':
7574  return true;
7575 
7576  default:
7577  break;
7578  }
7579  }
7580  }
7581 
7582  // multi-line comments skip input until */ is read
7583  case '*':
7584  {
7585  while (true)
7586  {
7587  switch (get())
7588  {
7589  case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
7590  case '\0':
7591  {
7592  error_message = "invalid comment; missing closing '*/'";
7593  return false;
7594  }
7595 
7596  case '*':
7597  {
7598  switch (get())
7599  {
7600  case '/':
7601  return true;
7602 
7603  default:
7604  {
7605  unget();
7606  continue;
7607  }
7608  }
7609  }
7610 
7611  default:
7612  continue;
7613  }
7614  }
7615  }
7616 
7617  // unexpected character after reading '/'
7618  default:
7619  {
7620  error_message = "invalid comment; expecting '/' or '*' after '/'";
7621  return false;
7622  }
7623  }
7624  }
7625 
7626  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7627  static void strtof(float& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
7628  {
7629  f = std::strtof(str, endptr);
7630  }
7631 
7632  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7633  static void strtof(double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
7634  {
7635  f = std::strtod(str, endptr);
7636  }
7637 
7638  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
7639  static void strtof(long double& f, const char* str, char** endptr) noexcept
7640  {
7641  f = std::strtold(str, endptr);
7642  }
7643 
7684  token_type scan_number() // lgtm [cpp/use-of-goto]
7685  {
7686  // reset token_buffer to store the number's bytes
7687  reset();
7688 
7689  // the type of the parsed number; initially set to unsigned; will be
7690  // changed if minus sign, decimal point or exponent is read
7691  token_type number_type = token_type::value_unsigned;
7692 
7693  // state (init): we just found out we need to scan a number
7694  switch (current)
7695  {
7696  case '-':
7697  {
7698  add(current);
7699  goto scan_number_minus;
7700  }
7701 
7702  case '0':
7703  {
7704  add(current);
7705  goto scan_number_zero;
7706  }
7707 
7708  case '1':
7709  case '2':
7710  case '3':
7711  case '4':
7712  case '5':
7713  case '6':
7714  case '7':
7715  case '8':
7716  case '9':
7717  {
7718  add(current);
7719  goto scan_number_any1;
7720  }
7721 
7722  // all other characters are rejected outside scan_number()
7723  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
7724  JSON_ASSERT(false); // NOLINT(cert-dcl03-c,hicpp-static-assert,misc-static-assert) LCOV_EXCL_LINE
7725  }
7726 
7727 scan_number_minus:
7728  // state: we just parsed a leading minus sign
7729  number_type = token_type::value_integer;
7730  switch (get())
7731  {
7732  case '0':
7733  {
7734  add(current);
7735  goto scan_number_zero;
7736  }
7737 
7738  case '1':
7739  case '2':
7740  case '3':
7741  case '4':
7742  case '5':
7743  case '6':
7744  case '7':
7745  case '8':
7746  case '9':
7747  {
7748  add(current);
7749  goto scan_number_any1;
7750  }
7751 
7752  default:
7753  {
7754  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '-'";
7755  return token_type::parse_error;
7756  }
7757  }
7758 
7759 scan_number_zero:
7760  // state: we just parse a zero (maybe with a leading minus sign)
7761  switch (get())
7762  {
7763  case '.':
7764  {
7765  add(decimal_point_char);
7766  goto scan_number_decimal1;
7767  }
7768 
7769  case 'e':
7770  case 'E':
7771  {
7772  add(current);
7773  goto scan_number_exponent;
7774  }
7775 
7776  default:
7777  goto scan_number_done;
7778  }
7779 
7780 scan_number_any1:
7781  // state: we just parsed a number 0-9 (maybe with a leading minus sign)
7782  switch (get())
7783  {
7784  case '0':
7785  case '1':
7786  case '2':
7787  case '3':
7788  case '4':
7789  case '5':
7790  case '6':
7791  case '7':
7792  case '8':
7793  case '9':
7794  {
7795  add(current);
7796  goto scan_number_any1;
7797  }
7798 
7799  case '.':
7800  {
7801  add(decimal_point_char);
7802  goto scan_number_decimal1;
7803  }
7804 
7805  case 'e':
7806  case 'E':
7807  {
7808  add(current);
7809  goto scan_number_exponent;
7810  }
7811 
7812  default:
7813  goto scan_number_done;
7814  }
7815 
7816 scan_number_decimal1:
7817  // state: we just parsed a decimal point
7818  number_type = token_type::value_float;
7819  switch (get())
7820  {
7821  case '0':
7822  case '1':
7823  case '2':
7824  case '3':
7825  case '4':
7826  case '5':
7827  case '6':
7828  case '7':
7829  case '8':
7830  case '9':
7831  {
7832  add(current);
7833  goto scan_number_decimal2;
7834  }
7835 
7836  default:
7837  {
7838  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after '.'";
7839  return token_type::parse_error;
7840  }
7841  }
7842 
7843 scan_number_decimal2:
7844  // we just parsed at least one number after a decimal point
7845  switch (get())
7846  {
7847  case '0':
7848  case '1':
7849  case '2':
7850  case '3':
7851  case '4':
7852  case '5':
7853  case '6':
7854  case '7':
7855  case '8':
7856  case '9':
7857  {
7858  add(current);
7859  goto scan_number_decimal2;
7860  }
7861 
7862  case 'e':
7863  case 'E':
7864  {
7865  add(current);
7866  goto scan_number_exponent;
7867  }
7868 
7869  default:
7870  goto scan_number_done;
7871  }
7872 
7873 scan_number_exponent:
7874  // we just parsed an exponent
7875  number_type = token_type::value_float;
7876  switch (get())
7877  {
7878  case '+':
7879  case '-':
7880  {
7881  add(current);
7882  goto scan_number_sign;
7883  }
7884 
7885  case '0':
7886  case '1':
7887  case '2':
7888  case '3':
7889  case '4':
7890  case '5':
7891  case '6':
7892  case '7':
7893  case '8':
7894  case '9':
7895  {
7896  add(current);
7897  goto scan_number_any2;
7898  }
7899 
7900  default:
7901  {
7902  error_message =
7903  "invalid number; expected '+', '-', or digit after exponent";
7904  return token_type::parse_error;
7905  }
7906  }
7907 
7908 scan_number_sign:
7909  // we just parsed an exponent sign
7910  switch (get())
7911  {
7912  case '0':
7913  case '1':
7914  case '2':
7915  case '3':
7916  case '4':
7917  case '5':
7918  case '6':
7919  case '7':
7920  case '8':
7921  case '9':
7922  {
7923  add(current);
7924  goto scan_number_any2;
7925  }
7926 
7927  default:
7928  {
7929  error_message = "invalid number; expected digit after exponent sign";
7930  return token_type::parse_error;
7931  }
7932  }
7933 
7934 scan_number_any2:
7935  // we just parsed a number after the exponent or exponent sign
7936  switch (get())
7937  {
7938  case '0':
7939  case '1':
7940  case '2':
7941  case '3':
7942  case '4':
7943  case '5':
7944  case '6':
7945  case '7':
7946  case '8':
7947  case '9':
7948  {
7949  add(current);
7950  goto scan_number_any2;
7951  }
7952 
7953  default:
7954  goto scan_number_done;
7955  }
7956 
7957 scan_number_done:
7958  // unget the character after the number (we only read it to know that
7959  // we are done scanning a number)
7960  unget();
7961 
7962  char* endptr = nullptr; // NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg,hicpp-vararg)
7963  errno = 0;
7964 
7965  // try to parse integers first and fall back to floats
7966  if (number_type == token_type::value_unsigned)
7967  {
7968  const auto x = std::strtoull(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
7969 
7970  // we checked the number format before
7971  JSON_ASSERT(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
7972 
7973  if (errno == 0)
7974  {
7975  value_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(x);
7976  if (value_unsigned == x)
7977  {
7978  return token_type::value_unsigned;
7979  }
7980  }
7981  }
7982  else if (number_type == token_type::value_integer)
7983  {
7984  const auto x = std::strtoll(token_buffer.data(), &endptr, 10);
7985 
7986  // we checked the number format before
7987  JSON_ASSERT(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
7988 
7989  if (errno == 0)
7990  {
7991  value_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(x);
7992  if (value_integer == x)
7993  {
7994  return token_type::value_integer;
7995  }
7996  }
7997  }
7998 
7999  // this code is reached if we parse a floating-point number or if an
8000  // integer conversion above failed
8001  strtof(value_float, token_buffer.data(), &endptr);
8002 
8003  // we checked the number format before
8004  JSON_ASSERT(endptr == token_buffer.data() + token_buffer.size());
8005 
8006  return token_type::value_float;
8007  }
8008 
8014  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
8015  token_type scan_literal(const char_type* literal_text, const std::size_t length,
8016  token_type return_type)
8017  {
8018  JSON_ASSERT(std::char_traits<char_type>::to_char_type(current) == literal_text[0]);
8019  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < length; ++i)
8020  {
8021  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(std::char_traits<char_type>::to_char_type(get()) != literal_text[i]))
8022  {
8023  error_message = "invalid literal";
8024  return token_type::parse_error;
8025  }
8026  }
8027  return return_type;
8028  }
8029 
8031  // input management
8033 
8035  void reset() noexcept
8036  {
8037  token_buffer.clear();
8038  token_string.clear();
8039  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char_type>::to_char_type(current));
8040  }
8041 
8042  /*
8043  @brief get next character from the input
8044 
8045  This function provides the interface to the used input adapter. It does
8046  not throw in case the input reached EOF, but returns a
8047  `std::char_traits<char>::eof()` in that case. Stores the scanned characters
8048  for use in error messages.
8049 
8050  @return character read from the input
8051  */
8052  char_int_type get()
8053  {
8054  ++position.chars_read_total;
8055  ++position.chars_read_current_line;
8056 
8057  if (next_unget)
8058  {
8059  // just reset the next_unget variable and work with current
8060  next_unget = false;
8061  }
8062  else
8063  {
8064  current = ia.get_character();
8065  }
8066 
8067  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char_type>::eof()))
8068  {
8069  token_string.push_back(std::char_traits<char_type>::to_char_type(current));
8070  }
8071 
8072  if (current == '\n')
8073  {
8074  ++position.lines_read;
8075  position.chars_read_current_line = 0;
8076  }
8077 
8078  return current;
8079  }
8080 
8089  void unget()
8090  {
8091  next_unget = true;
8092 
8093  --position.chars_read_total;
8094 
8095  // in case we "unget" a newline, we have to also decrement the lines_read
8096  if (position.chars_read_current_line == 0)
8097  {
8098  if (position.lines_read > 0)
8099  {
8100  --position.lines_read;
8101  }
8102  }
8103  else
8104  {
8105  --position.chars_read_current_line;
8106  }
8107 
8108  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char_type>::eof()))
8109  {
8110  JSON_ASSERT(!token_string.empty());
8111  token_string.pop_back();
8112  }
8113  }
8114 
8116  void add(char_int_type c)
8117  {
8118  token_buffer.push_back(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(c));
8119  }
8120 
8121  public:
8123  // value getters
8125 
8127  constexpr number_integer_t get_number_integer() const noexcept
8128  {
8129  return value_integer;
8130  }
8131 
8133  constexpr number_unsigned_t get_number_unsigned() const noexcept
8134  {
8135  return value_unsigned;
8136  }
8137 
8139  constexpr number_float_t get_number_float() const noexcept
8140  {
8141  return value_float;
8142  }
8143 
8145  string_t& get_string()
8146  {
8147  return token_buffer;
8148  }
8149 
8151  // diagnostics
8153 
8155  constexpr position_t get_position() const noexcept
8156  {
8157  return position;
8158  }
8159 
8163  std::string get_token_string() const
8164  {
8165  // escape control characters
8166  std::string result;
8167  for (const auto c : token_string)
8168  {
8169  if (static_cast<unsigned char>(c) <= '\x1F')
8170  {
8171  // escape control characters
8172  std::array<char, 9> cs{{}};
8173  static_cast<void>((std::snprintf)(cs.data(), cs.size(), "<U+%.4X>", static_cast<unsigned char>(c))); // NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg,hicpp-vararg)
8174  result += cs.data();
8175  }
8176  else
8177  {
8178  // add character as is
8179  result.push_back(static_cast<std::string::value_type>(c));
8180  }
8181  }
8182 
8183  return result;
8184  }
8185 
8187  JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
8188  constexpr const char* get_error_message() const noexcept
8189  {
8190  return error_message;
8191  }
8192 
8194  // actual scanner
8196 
8201  bool skip_bom()
8202  {
8203  if (get() == 0xEF)
8204  {
8205  // check if we completely parse the BOM
8206  return get() == 0xBB && get() == 0xBF;
8207  }
8208 
8209  // the first character is not the beginning of the BOM; unget it to
8210  // process is later
8211  unget();
8212  return true;
8213  }
8214 
8215  void skip_whitespace()
8216  {
8217  do
8218  {
8219  get();
8220  }
8221  while (current == ' ' || current == '\t' || current == '\n' || current == '\r');
8222  }
8223 
8224  token_type scan()
8225  {
8226  // initially, skip the BOM
8227  if (position.chars_read_total == 0 && !skip_bom())
8228  {
8229  error_message = "invalid BOM; must be 0xEF 0xBB 0xBF if given";
8230  return token_type::parse_error;
8231  }
8232 
8233  // read next character and ignore whitespace
8234  skip_whitespace();
8235 
8236  // ignore comments
8237  while (ignore_comments && current == '/')
8238  {
8239  if (!scan_comment())
8240  {
8241  return token_type::parse_error;
8242  }
8243 
8244  // skip following whitespace
8245  skip_whitespace();
8246  }
8247 
8248  switch (current)
8249  {
8250  // structural characters
8251  case '[':
8252  return token_type::begin_array;
8253  case ']':
8254  return token_type::end_array;
8255  case '{':
8256  return token_type::begin_object;
8257  case '}':
8258  return token_type::end_object;
8259  case ':':
8260  return token_type::name_separator;
8261  case ',':
8262  return token_type::value_separator;
8263 
8264  // literals
8265  case 't':
8266  {
8267  std::array<char_type, 4> true_literal = {{static_cast<char_type>('t'), static_cast<char_type>('r'), static_cast<char_type>('u'), static_cast<char_type>('e')}};
8268  return scan_literal(true_literal.data(), true_literal.size(), token_type::literal_true);
8269  }
8270  case 'f':
8271  {
8272  std::array<char_type, 5> false_literal = {{static_cast<char_type>('f'), static_cast<char_type>('a'), static_cast<char_type>('l'), static_cast<char_type>('s'), static_cast<char_type>('e')}};
8273  return scan_literal(false_literal.data(), false_literal.size(), token_type::literal_false);
8274  }
8275  case 'n':
8276  {
8277  std::array<char_type, 4> null_literal = {{static_cast<char_type>('n'), static_cast<char_type>('u'), static_cast<char_type>('l'), static_cast<char_type>('l')}};
8278  return scan_literal(null_literal.data(), null_literal.size(), token_type::literal_null);
8279  }
8280 
8281  // string
8282  case '\"':
8283  return scan_string();
8284 
8285  // number
8286  case '-':
8287  case '0':
8288  case '1':
8289  case '2':
8290  case '3':
8291  case '4':
8292  case '5':
8293  case '6':
8294  case '7':
8295  case '8':
8296  case '9':
8297  return scan_number();
8298 
8299  // end of input (the null byte is needed when parsing from
8300  // string literals)
8301  case '\0':
8302  case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
8303  return token_type::end_of_input;
8304 
8305  // error
8306  default:
8307  error_message = "invalid literal";
8308  return token_type::parse_error;
8309  }
8310  }
8311 
8312  private:
8314  InputAdapterType ia;
8315 
8317  const bool ignore_comments = false;
8318 
8320  char_int_type current = std::char_traits<char_type>::eof();
8321 
8323  bool next_unget = false;
8324 
8326  position_t position {};
8327 
8329  std::vector<char_type> token_string {};
8330 
8332  string_t token_buffer {};
8333 
8335  const char* error_message = "";
8336 
8337  // number values
8338  number_integer_t value_integer = 0;
8339  number_unsigned_t value_unsigned = 0;
8340  number_float_t value_float = 0;
8341 
8343  const char_int_type decimal_point_char = '.';
8344 };
8345 } // namespace detail
8346 } // namespace nlohmann

8366 template<typename T>
8367 using null_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().null());
8368 
8369 template<typename T>
8370 using boolean_function_t =
8371  decltype(std::declval<T&>().boolean(std::declval<bool>()));
8372 
8373 template<typename T, typename Integer>
8374 using number_integer_function_t =
8375  decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_integer(std::declval<Integer>()));
8376 
8377 template<typename T, typename Unsigned>
8378 using number_unsigned_function_t =
8379  decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_unsigned(std::declval<Unsigned>()));
8380 
8381 template<typename T, typename Float, typename String>
8382 using number_float_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().number_float(
8383  std::declval<Float>(), std::declval<const String&>()));
8384 
8385 template<typename T, typename String>
8386 using string_function_t =
8387  decltype(std::declval<T&>().string(std::declval<String&>()));
8388 
8389 template<typename T, typename Binary>
8390 using binary_function_t =
8391  decltype(std::declval<T&>().binary(std::declval<Binary&>()));
8392 
8393 template<typename T>
8394 using start_object_function_t =
8395  decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_object(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
8396 
8397 template<typename T, typename String>
8398 using key_function_t =
8399  decltype(std::declval<T&>().key(std::declval<String&>()));
8400 
8401 template<typename T>
8402 using end_object_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_object());
8403 
8404 template<typename T>
8405 using start_array_function_t =
8406  decltype(std::declval<T&>().start_array(std::declval<std::size_t>()));
8407 
8408 template<typename T>
8409 using end_array_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().end_array());
8410 
8411 template<typename T, typename Exception>
8412 using parse_error_function_t = decltype(std::declval<T&>().parse_error(
8413  std::declval<std::size_t>(), std::declval<const std::string&>(),
8414  std::declval<const Exception&>()));
8415 
8416 template<typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
8417 struct is_sax
8418 {
8419  private:
8420  static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value,
8421  "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
8422 
8423  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
8424  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
8425  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
8426  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
8427  using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
8428  using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
8429 
8430  public:
8431  static constexpr bool value =
8432  is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value &&
8433  is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value &&
8434  is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX, number_integer_t>::value &&
8435  is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX, number_unsigned_t>::value &&
8436  is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX, number_float_t, string_t>::value &&
8437  is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
8438  is_detected_exact<bool, binary_function_t, SAX, binary_t>::value &&
8439  is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
8440  is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value &&
8441  is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value &&
8442  is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
8443  is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value &&
8444  is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value;
8445 };
8446 
8447 template<typename SAX, typename BasicJsonType>
8448 struct is_sax_static_asserts
8449 {
8450  private:
8451  static_assert(is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value,
8452  "BasicJsonType must be of type basic_json<...>");
8453 
8454  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
8455  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
8456  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
8457  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
8458  using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
8459  using exception_t = typename BasicJsonType::exception;
8460 
8461  public:
8462  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, null_function_t, SAX>::value,
8463  "Missing/invalid function: bool null()");
8464  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
8465  "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
8466  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, boolean_function_t, SAX>::value,
8467  "Missing/invalid function: bool boolean(bool)");
8468  static_assert(
8469  is_detected_exact<bool, number_integer_function_t, SAX,
8470  number_integer_t>::value,
8471  "Missing/invalid function: bool number_integer(number_integer_t)");
8472  static_assert(
8473  is_detected_exact<bool, number_unsigned_function_t, SAX,
8474  number_unsigned_t>::value,
8475  "Missing/invalid function: bool number_unsigned(number_unsigned_t)");
8476  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, number_float_function_t, SAX,
8477  number_float_t, string_t>::value,
8478  "Missing/invalid function: bool number_float(number_float_t, const string_t&)");
8479  static_assert(
8480  is_detected_exact<bool, string_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
8481  "Missing/invalid function: bool string(string_t&)");
8482  static_assert(
8483  is_detected_exact<bool, binary_function_t, SAX, binary_t>::value,
8484  "Missing/invalid function: bool binary(binary_t&)");
8485  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
8486  "Missing/invalid function: bool start_object(std::size_t)");
8487  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, key_function_t, SAX, string_t>::value,
8488  "Missing/invalid function: bool key(string_t&)");
8489  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_object_function_t, SAX>::value,
8490  "Missing/invalid function: bool end_object()");
8491  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, start_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
8492  "Missing/invalid function: bool start_array(std::size_t)");
8493  static_assert(is_detected_exact<bool, end_array_function_t, SAX>::value,
8494  "Missing/invalid function: bool end_array()");
8495  static_assert(
8496  is_detected_exact<bool, parse_error_function_t, SAX, exception_t>::value,
8497  "Missing/invalid function: bool parse_error(std::size_t, const "
8498  "std::string&, const exception&)");
8499 };

8516 enum class cbor_tag_handler_t
8517 {
8518  error,
8519  ignore,
8520  store

8530 static inline bool little_endianness(int num = 1) noexcept
8531 {

8537 // binary reader //
8539 
8543 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename InputAdapterType, typename SAX = json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType>>
8544 class binary_reader
8545 {
8546  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
8547  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
8548  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
8549  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
8550  using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
8551  using json_sax_t = SAX;
8552  using char_type = typename InputAdapterType::char_type;
8553  using char_int_type = typename std::char_traits<char_type>::int_type;
8554 
8555  public:
8561  explicit binary_reader(InputAdapterType&& adapter, const input_format_t format = input_format_t::json) noexcept : ia(std::move(adapter)), input_format(format)
8562  {
8563  (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType> {};
8564  }
8565 
8566  // make class move-only
8567  binary_reader(const binary_reader&) = delete;
8568  binary_reader(binary_reader&&) = default; // NOLINT(hicpp-noexcept-move,performance-noexcept-move-constructor)
8569  binary_reader& operator=(const binary_reader&) = delete;
8570  binary_reader& operator=(binary_reader&&) = default; // NOLINT(hicpp-noexcept-move,performance-noexcept-move-constructor)
8571  ~binary_reader() = default;
8572 
8581  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
8582  bool sax_parse(const input_format_t format,
8583  json_sax_t* sax_,
8584  const bool strict = true,
8585  const cbor_tag_handler_t tag_handler = cbor_tag_handler_t::error)
8586  {
8587  sax = sax_;
8588  bool result = false;
8589 
8590  switch (format)
8591  {
8592  case input_format_t::bson:
8593  result = parse_bson_internal();
8594  break;
8595 
8596  case input_format_t::cbor:
8597  result = parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler);
8598  break;
8599 
8600  case input_format_t::msgpack:
8601  result = parse_msgpack_internal();
8602  break;
8603 
8604  case input_format_t::ubjson:
8605  case input_format_t::bjdata:
8606  result = parse_ubjson_internal();
8607  break;
8608 
8609  case input_format_t::json: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
8610  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
8611  JSON_ASSERT(false); // NOLINT(cert-dcl03-c,hicpp-static-assert,misc-static-assert) LCOV_EXCL_LINE
8612  }
8613 
8614  // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
8615  if (result && strict)
8616  {
8617  if (input_format == input_format_t::ubjson || input_format == input_format_t::bjdata)
8618  {
8619  get_ignore_noop();
8620  }
8621  else
8622  {
8623  get();
8624  }
8625 
8626  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current != std::char_traits<char_type>::eof()))
8627  {
8628  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(), parse_error::create(110, chars_read,
8629  exception_message(input_format, concat("expected end of input; last byte: 0x", get_token_string()), "value"), nullptr));
8630  }
8631  }
8632 
8633  return result;
8634  }
8635 
8636  private:
8638  // BSON //
8640 
8645  bool parse_bson_internal()
8646  {
8647  std::int32_t document_size{};
8648  get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
8649 
8650  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))))
8651  {
8652  return false;
8653  }
8654 
8655  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/false)))
8656  {
8657  return false;
8658  }
8659 
8660  return sax->end_object();
8661  }
8662 
8670  bool get_bson_cstr(string_t& result)
8671  {
8672  auto out = std::back_inserter(result);
8673  while (true)
8674  {
8675  get();
8676  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "cstring")))
8677  {
8678  return false;
8679  }
8680  if (current == 0x00)
8681  {
8682  return true;
8683  }
8684  *out++ = static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(current);
8685  }
8686  }
8687 
8699  template<typename NumberType>
8700  bool get_bson_string(const NumberType len, string_t& result)
8701  {
8702  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len < 1))
8703  {
8704  auto last_token = get_token_string();
8705  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
8706  exception_message(input_format_t::bson, concat("string length must be at least 1, is ", std::to_string(len)), "string"), nullptr));
8707  }
8708 
8709  return get_string(input_format_t::bson, len - static_cast<NumberType>(1), result) && get() != std::char_traits<char_type>::eof();
8710  }
8711 
8721  template<typename NumberType>
8722  bool get_bson_binary(const NumberType len, binary_t& result)
8723  {
8724  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(len < 0))
8725  {
8726  auto last_token = get_token_string();
8727  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
8728  exception_message(input_format_t::bson, concat("byte array length cannot be negative, is ", std::to_string(len)), "binary"), nullptr));
8729  }
8730 
8731  // All BSON binary values have a subtype
8732  std::uint8_t subtype{};
8733  get_number<std::uint8_t>(input_format_t::bson, subtype);
8734  result.set_subtype(subtype);
8735 
8736  return get_binary(input_format_t::bson, len, result);
8737  }
8738 
8749  bool parse_bson_element_internal(const char_int_type element_type,
8750  const std::size_t element_type_parse_position)
8751  {
8752  switch (element_type)
8753  {
8754  case 0x01: // double
8755  {
8756  double number{};
8757  return get_number<double, true>(input_format_t::bson, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
8758  }
8759 
8760  case 0x02: // string
8761  {
8762  std::int32_t len{};
8763  string_t value;
8764  return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, len) && get_bson_string(len, value) && sax->string(value);
8765  }
8766 
8767  case 0x03: // object
8768  {
8769  return parse_bson_internal();
8770  }
8771 
8772  case 0x04: // array
8773  {
8774  return parse_bson_array();
8775  }
8776 
8777  case 0x05: // binary
8778  {
8779  std::int32_t len{};
8780  binary_t value;
8781  return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, len) && get_bson_binary(len, value) && sax->binary(value);
8782  }
8783 
8784  case 0x08: // boolean
8785  {
8786  return sax->boolean(get() != 0);
8787  }
8788 
8789  case 0x0A: // null
8790  {
8791  return sax->null();
8792  }
8793 
8794  case 0x10: // int32
8795  {
8796  std::int32_t value{};
8797  return get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) && sax->number_integer(value);
8798  }
8799 
8800  case 0x12: // int64
8801  {
8802  std::int64_t value{};
8803  return get_number<std::int64_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, value) && sax->number_integer(value);
8804  }
8805 
8806  default: // anything else not supported (yet)
8807  {
8808  std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
8809  static_cast<void>((std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(element_type))); // NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg,hicpp-vararg)
8810  std::string cr_str{cr.data()};
8811  return sax->parse_error(element_type_parse_position, cr_str,
8812  parse_error::create(114, element_type_parse_position, concat("Unsupported BSON record type 0x", cr_str), nullptr));
8813  }
8814  }
8815  }
8816 
8829  bool parse_bson_element_list(const bool is_array)
8830  {
8831  string_t key;
8832 
8833  while (auto element_type = get())
8834  {
8835  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::bson, "element list")))
8836  {
8837  return false;
8838  }
8839 
8840  const std::size_t element_type_parse_position = chars_read;
8841  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_bson_cstr(key)))
8842  {
8843  return false;
8844  }
8845 
8846  if (!is_array && !sax->key(key))
8847  {
8848  return false;
8849  }
8850 
8851  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_bson_element_internal(element_type, element_type_parse_position)))
8852  {
8853  return false;
8854  }
8855 
8856  // get_bson_cstr only appends
8857  key.clear();
8858  }
8859 
8860  return true;
8861  }
8862 
8867  bool parse_bson_array()
8868  {
8869  std::int32_t document_size{};
8870  get_number<std::int32_t, true>(input_format_t::bson, document_size);
8871 
8872  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))))
8873  {
8874  return false;
8875  }
8876 
8877  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_bson_element_list(/*is_array*/true)))
8878  {
8879  return false;
8880  }
8881 
8882  return sax->end_array();
8883  }
8884 
8886  // CBOR //
8888 
8897  bool parse_cbor_internal(const bool get_char,
8898  const cbor_tag_handler_t tag_handler)
8899  {
8900  switch (get_char ? get() : current)
8901  {
8902  // EOF
8903  case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof():
8904  return unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "value");
8905 
8906  // Integer 0x00..0x17 (0..23)
8907  case 0x00:
8908  case 0x01:
8909  case 0x02:
8910  case 0x03:
8911  case 0x04:
8912  case 0x05:
8913  case 0x06:
8914  case 0x07:
8915  case 0x08:
8916  case 0x09:
8917  case 0x0A:
8918  case 0x0B:
8919  case 0x0C:
8920  case 0x0D:
8921  case 0x0E:
8922  case 0x0F:
8923  case 0x10:
8924  case 0x11:
8925  case 0x12:
8926  case 0x13:
8927  case 0x14:
8928  case 0x15:
8929  case 0x16:
8930  case 0x17:
8931  return sax->number_unsigned(static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(current));
8932 
8933  case 0x18: // Unsigned integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
8934  {
8935  std::uint8_t number{};
8936  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
8937  }
8938 
8939  case 0x19: // Unsigned integer (two-byte uint16_t follows)
8940  {
8941  std::uint16_t number{};
8942  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
8943  }
8944 
8945  case 0x1A: // Unsigned integer (four-byte uint32_t follows)
8946  {
8947  std::uint32_t number{};
8948  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
8949  }
8950 
8951  case 0x1B: // Unsigned integer (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
8952  {
8953  std::uint64_t number{};
8954  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
8955  }
8956 
8957  // Negative integer -1-0x00..-1-0x17 (-1..-24)
8958  case 0x20:
8959  case 0x21:
8960  case 0x22:
8961  case 0x23:
8962  case 0x24:
8963  case 0x25:
8964  case 0x26:
8965  case 0x27:
8966  case 0x28:
8967  case 0x29:
8968  case 0x2A:
8969  case 0x2B:
8970  case 0x2C:
8971  case 0x2D:
8972  case 0x2E:
8973  case 0x2F:
8974  case 0x30:
8975  case 0x31:
8976  case 0x32:
8977  case 0x33:
8978  case 0x34:
8979  case 0x35:
8980  case 0x36:
8981  case 0x37:
8982  return sax->number_integer(static_cast<std::int8_t>(0x20 - 1 - current));
8983 
8984  case 0x38: // Negative integer (one-byte uint8_t follows)
8985  {
8986  std::uint8_t number{};
8987  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
8988  }
8989 
8990  case 0x39: // Negative integer -1-n (two-byte uint16_t follows)
8991  {
8992  std::uint16_t number{};
8993  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
8994  }
8995 
8996  case 0x3A: // Negative integer -1-n (four-byte uint32_t follows)
8997  {
8998  std::uint32_t number{};
8999  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1) - number);
9000  }
9001 
9002  case 0x3B: // Negative integer -1-n (eight-byte uint64_t follows)
9003  {
9004  std::uint64_t number{};
9005  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(-1)
9006  - static_cast<number_integer_t>(number));
9007  }
9008 
9009  // Binary data (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
9010  case 0x40:
9011  case 0x41:
9012  case 0x42:
9013  case 0x43:
9014  case 0x44:
9015  case 0x45:
9016  case 0x46:
9017  case 0x47:
9018  case 0x48:
9019  case 0x49:
9020  case 0x4A:
9021  case 0x4B:
9022  case 0x4C:
9023  case 0x4D:
9024  case 0x4E:
9025  case 0x4F:
9026  case 0x50:
9027  case 0x51:
9028  case 0x52:
9029  case 0x53:
9030  case 0x54:
9031  case 0x55:
9032  case 0x56:
9033  case 0x57:
9034  case 0x58: // Binary data (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
9035  case 0x59: // Binary data (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
9036  case 0x5A: // Binary data (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
9037  case 0x5B: // Binary data (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
9038  case 0x5F: // Binary data (indefinite length)
9039  {
9040  binary_t b;
9041  return get_cbor_binary(b) && sax->binary(b);
9042  }
9043 
9044  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
9045  case 0x60:
9046  case 0x61:
9047  case 0x62:
9048  case 0x63:
9049  case 0x64:
9050  case 0x65:
9051  case 0x66:
9052  case 0x67:
9053  case 0x68:
9054  case 0x69:
9055  case 0x6A:
9056  case 0x6B:
9057  case 0x6C:
9058  case 0x6D:
9059  case 0x6E:
9060  case 0x6F:
9061  case 0x70:
9062  case 0x71:
9063  case 0x72:
9064  case 0x73:
9065  case 0x74:
9066  case 0x75:
9067  case 0x76:
9068  case 0x77:
9069  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
9070  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
9071  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
9072  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
9073  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
9074  {
9075  string_t s;
9076  return get_cbor_string(s) && sax->string(s);
9077  }
9078 
9079  // array (0x00..0x17 data items follow)
9080  case 0x80:
9081  case 0x81:
9082  case 0x82:
9083  case 0x83:
9084  case 0x84:
9085  case 0x85:
9086  case 0x86:
9087  case 0x87:
9088  case 0x88:
9089  case 0x89:
9090  case 0x8A:
9091  case 0x8B:
9092  case 0x8C:
9093  case 0x8D:
9094  case 0x8E:
9095  case 0x8F:
9096  case 0x90:
9097  case 0x91:
9098  case 0x92:
9099  case 0x93:
9100  case 0x94:
9101  case 0x95:
9102  case 0x96:
9103  case 0x97:
9104  return get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu), tag_handler);
9105 
9106  case 0x98: // array (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
9107  {
9108  std::uint8_t len{};
9109  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
9110  }
9111 
9112  case 0x99: // array (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
9113  {
9114  std::uint16_t len{};
9115  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
9116  }
9117 
9118  case 0x9A: // array (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
9119  {
9120  std::uint32_t len{};
9121  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
9122  }
9123 
9124  case 0x9B: // array (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
9125  {
9126  std::uint64_t len{};
9127  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_array(detail::conditional_static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
9128  }
9129 
9130  case 0x9F: // array (indefinite length)
9131  return get_cbor_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(-1), tag_handler);
9132 
9133  // map (0x00..0x17 pairs of data items follow)
9134  case 0xA0:
9135  case 0xA1:
9136  case 0xA2:
9137  case 0xA3:
9138  case 0xA4:
9139  case 0xA5:
9140  case 0xA6:
9141  case 0xA7:
9142  case 0xA8:
9143  case 0xA9:
9144  case 0xAA:
9145  case 0xAB:
9146  case 0xAC:
9147  case 0xAD:
9148  case 0xAE:
9149  case 0xAF:
9150  case 0xB0:
9151  case 0xB1:
9152  case 0xB2:
9153  case 0xB3:
9154  case 0xB4:
9155  case 0xB5:
9156  case 0xB6:
9157  case 0xB7:
9158  return get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu), tag_handler);
9159 
9160  case 0xB8: // map (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
9161  {
9162  std::uint8_t len{};
9163  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
9164  }
9165 
9166  case 0xB9: // map (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
9167  {
9168  std::uint16_t len{};
9169  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
9170  }
9171 
9172  case 0xBA: // map (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
9173  {
9174  std::uint32_t len{};
9175  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
9176  }
9177 
9178  case 0xBB: // map (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
9179  {
9180  std::uint64_t len{};
9181  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_cbor_object(detail::conditional_static_cast<std::size_t>(len), tag_handler);
9182  }
9183 
9184  case 0xBF: // map (indefinite length)
9185  return get_cbor_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(-1), tag_handler);
9186 
9187  case 0xC6: // tagged item
9188  case 0xC7:
9189  case 0xC8:
9190  case 0xC9:
9191  case 0xCA:
9192  case 0xCB:
9193  case 0xCC:
9194  case 0xCD:
9195  case 0xCE:
9196  case 0xCF:
9197  case 0xD0:
9198  case 0xD1:
9199  case 0xD2:
9200  case 0xD3:
9201  case 0xD4:
9202  case 0xD8: // tagged item (1 bytes follow)
9203  case 0xD9: // tagged item (2 bytes follow)
9204  case 0xDA: // tagged item (4 bytes follow)
9205  case 0xDB: // tagged item (8 bytes follow)
9206  {
9207  switch (tag_handler)
9208  {
9209  case cbor_tag_handler_t::error:
9210  {
9211  auto last_token = get_token_string();
9212  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
9213  exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, concat("invalid byte: 0x", last_token), "value"), nullptr));
9214  }
9215 
9216  case cbor_tag_handler_t::ignore:
9217  {
9218  // ignore binary subtype
9219  switch (current)
9220  {
9221  case 0xD8:
9222  {
9223  std::uint8_t subtype_to_ignore{};
9224  get_number(input_format_t::cbor, subtype_to_ignore);
9225  break;
9226  }
9227  case 0xD9:
9228  {
9229  std::uint16_t subtype_to_ignore{};
9230  get_number(input_format_t::cbor, subtype_to_ignore);
9231  break;
9232  }
9233  case 0xDA:
9234  {
9235  std::uint32_t subtype_to_ignore{};
9236  get_number(input_format_t::cbor, subtype_to_ignore);
9237  break;
9238  }
9239  case 0xDB:
9240  {
9241  std::uint64_t subtype_to_ignore{};
9242  get_number(input_format_t::cbor, subtype_to_ignore);
9243  break;
9244  }
9245  default:
9246  break;
9247  }
9248  return parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler);
9249  }
9250 
9251  case cbor_tag_handler_t::store:
9252  {
9253  binary_t b;
9254  // use binary subtype and store in binary container
9255  switch (current)
9256  {
9257  case 0xD8:
9258  {
9259  std::uint8_t subtype{};
9260  get_number(input_format_t::cbor, subtype);
9261  b.set_subtype(detail::conditional_static_cast<typename binary_t::subtype_type>(subtype));
9262  break;
9263  }
9264  case 0xD9:
9265  {
9266  std::uint16_t subtype{};
9267  get_number(input_format_t::cbor, subtype);
9268  b.set_subtype(detail::conditional_static_cast<typename binary_t::subtype_type>(subtype));
9269  break;
9270  }
9271  case 0xDA:
9272  {
9273  std::uint32_t subtype{};
9274  get_number(input_format_t::cbor, subtype);
9275  b.set_subtype(detail::conditional_static_cast<typename binary_t::subtype_type>(subtype));
9276  break;
9277  }
9278  case 0xDB:
9279  {
9280  std::uint64_t subtype{};
9281  get_number(input_format_t::cbor, subtype);
9282  b.set_subtype(detail::conditional_static_cast<typename binary_t::subtype_type>(subtype));
9283  break;
9284  }
9285  default:
9286  return parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler);
9287  }
9288  get();
9289  return get_cbor_binary(b) && sax->binary(b);
9290  }
9291 
9292  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9293  JSON_ASSERT(false); // NOLINT(cert-dcl03-c,hicpp-static-assert,misc-static-assert) LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9294  return false; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
9295  }
9296  }
9297 
9298  case 0xF4: // false
9299  return sax->boolean(false);
9300 
9301  case 0xF5: // true
9302  return sax->boolean(true);
9303 
9304  case 0xF6: // null
9305  return sax->null();
9306 
9307  case 0xF9: // Half-Precision Float (two-byte IEEE 754)
9308  {
9309  const auto byte1_raw = get();
9310  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number")))
9311  {
9312  return false;
9313  }
9314  const auto byte2_raw = get();
9315  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "number")))
9316  {
9317  return false;
9318  }
9319 
9320  const auto byte1 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte1_raw);
9321  const auto byte2 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte2_raw);
9322 
9323  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
9324  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
9325  // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
9326  // still only have limited support for them. It is very
9327  // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
9328  // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
9329  // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
9330  // is shown in Fig. 3.
9331  const auto half = static_cast<unsigned int>((byte1 << 8u) + byte2);
9332  const double val = [&half]
9333  {
9334  const int exp = (half >> 10u) & 0x1Fu;
9335  const unsigned int mant = half & 0x3FFu;
9336  JSON_ASSERT(0 <= exp&& exp <= 32);
9337  JSON_ASSERT(mant <= 1024);
9338  switch (exp)
9339  {
9340  case 0:
9341  return std::ldexp(mant, -24);
9342  case 31:
9343  return (mant == 0)
9344  ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
9345  : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
9346  default:
9347  return std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
9348  }
9349  }();
9350  return sax->number_float((half & 0x8000u) != 0
9351  ? static_cast<number_float_t>(-val)
9352  : static_cast<number_float_t>(val), "");
9353  }
9354 
9355  case 0xFA: // Single-Precision Float (four-byte IEEE 754)
9356  {
9357  float number{};
9358  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
9359  }
9360 
9361  case 0xFB: // Double-Precision Float (eight-byte IEEE 754)
9362  {
9363  double number{};
9364  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
9365  }
9366 
9367  default: // anything else (0xFF is handled inside the other types)
9368  {
9369  auto last_token = get_token_string();
9370  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
9371  exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, concat("invalid byte: 0x", last_token), "value"), nullptr));
9372  }
9373  }
9374  }
9375 
9387  bool get_cbor_string(string_t& result)
9388  {
9389  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "string")))
9390  {
9391  return false;
9392  }
9393 
9394  switch (current)
9395  {
9396  // UTF-8 string (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
9397  case 0x60:
9398  case 0x61:
9399  case 0x62:
9400  case 0x63:
9401  case 0x64:
9402  case 0x65:
9403  case 0x66:
9404  case 0x67:
9405  case 0x68:
9406  case 0x69:
9407  case 0x6A:
9408  case 0x6B:
9409  case 0x6C:
9410  case 0x6D:
9411  case 0x6E:
9412  case 0x6F:
9413  case 0x70:
9414  case 0x71:
9415  case 0x72:
9416  case 0x73:
9417  case 0x74:
9418  case 0x75:
9419  case 0x76:
9420  case 0x77:
9421  {
9422  return get_string(input_format_t::cbor, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
9423  }
9424 
9425  case 0x78: // UTF-8 string (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
9426  {
9427  std::uint8_t len{};
9428  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
9429  }
9430 
9431  case 0x79: // UTF-8 string (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
9432  {
9433  std::uint16_t len{};
9434  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
9435  }
9436 
9437  case 0x7A: // UTF-8 string (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
9438  {
9439  std::uint32_t len{};
9440  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
9441  }
9442 
9443  case 0x7B: // UTF-8 string (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
9444  {
9445  std::uint64_t len{};
9446  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) && get_string(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
9447  }
9448 
9449  case 0x7F: // UTF-8 string (indefinite length)
9450  {
9451  while (get() != 0xFF)
9452  {
9453  string_t chunk;
9454  if (!get_cbor_string(chunk))
9455  {
9456  return false;
9457  }
9458  result.append(chunk);
9459  }
9460  return true;
9461  }
9462 
9463  default:
9464  {
9465  auto last_token = get_token_string();
9466  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
9467  exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, concat("expected length specification (0x60-0x7B) or indefinite string type (0x7F); last byte: 0x", last_token), "string"), nullptr));
9468  }
9469  }
9470  }
9471 
9483  bool get_cbor_binary(binary_t& result)
9484  {
9485  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format_t::cbor, "binary")))
9486  {
9487  return false;
9488  }
9489 
9490  switch (current)
9491  {
9492  // Binary data (0x00..0x17 bytes follow)
9493  case 0x40:
9494  case 0x41:
9495  case 0x42:
9496  case 0x43:
9497  case 0x44:
9498  case 0x45:
9499  case 0x46:
9500  case 0x47:
9501  case 0x48:
9502  case 0x49:
9503  case 0x4A:
9504  case 0x4B:
9505  case 0x4C:
9506  case 0x4D:
9507  case 0x4E:
9508  case 0x4F:
9509  case 0x50:
9510  case 0x51:
9511  case 0x52:
9512  case 0x53:
9513  case 0x54:
9514  case 0x55:
9515  case 0x56:
9516  case 0x57:
9517  {
9518  return get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, static_cast<unsigned int>(current) & 0x1Fu, result);
9519  }
9520 
9521  case 0x58: // Binary data (one-byte uint8_t for n follows)
9522  {
9523  std::uint8_t len{};
9524  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) &&
9525  get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
9526  }
9527 
9528  case 0x59: // Binary data (two-byte uint16_t for n follow)
9529  {
9530  std::uint16_t len{};
9531  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) &&
9532  get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
9533  }
9534 
9535  case 0x5A: // Binary data (four-byte uint32_t for n follow)
9536  {
9537  std::uint32_t len{};
9538  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) &&
9539  get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
9540  }
9541 
9542  case 0x5B: // Binary data (eight-byte uint64_t for n follow)
9543  {
9544  std::uint64_t len{};
9545  return get_number(input_format_t::cbor, len) &&
9546  get_binary(input_format_t::cbor, len, result);
9547  }
9548 
9549  case 0x5F: // Binary data (indefinite length)
9550  {
9551  while (get() != 0xFF)
9552  {
9553  binary_t chunk;
9554  if (!get_cbor_binary(chunk))
9555  {
9556  return false;
9557  }
9558  result.insert(result.end(), chunk.begin(), chunk.end());
9559  }
9560  return true;
9561  }
9562 
9563  default:
9564  {
9565  auto last_token = get_token_string();
9566  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
9567  exception_message(input_format_t::cbor, concat("expected length specification (0x40-0x5B) or indefinite binary array type (0x5F); last byte: 0x", last_token), "binary"), nullptr));
9568  }
9569  }
9570  }
9571 
9578  bool get_cbor_array(const std::size_t len,
9579  const cbor_tag_handler_t tag_handler)
9580  {
9581  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(len)))
9582  {
9583  return false;
9584  }
9585 
9586  if (len != static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))
9587  {
9588  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
9589  {
9590  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler)))
9591  {
9592  return false;
9593  }
9594  }
9595  }
9596  else
9597  {
9598  while (get() != 0xFF)
9599  {
9600  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_cbor_internal(false, tag_handler)))
9601  {
9602  return false;
9603  }
9604  }
9605  }
9606 
9607  return sax->end_array();
9608  }
9609 
9616  bool get_cbor_object(const std::size_t len,
9617  const cbor_tag_handler_t tag_handler)
9618  {
9619  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(len)))
9620  {
9621  return false;
9622  }
9623 
9624  if (len != 0)
9625  {
9626  string_t key;
9627  if (len != static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))
9628  {
9629  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
9630  {
9631  get();
9632  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_cbor_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
9633  {
9634  return false;
9635  }
9636 
9637  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler)))
9638  {
9639  return false;
9640  }
9641  key.clear();
9642  }
9643  }
9644  else
9645  {
9646  while (get() != 0xFF)
9647  {
9648  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_cbor_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
9649  {
9650  return false;
9651  }
9652 
9653  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_cbor_internal(true, tag_handler)))
9654  {
9655  return false;
9656  }
9657  key.clear();
9658  }
9659  }
9660  }
9661 
9662  return sax->end_object();
9663  }

10118  {
10119  auto last_token = get_token_string();
10120  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
10121  exception_message(input_format_t::msgpack, concat("expected length specification (0xA0-0xBF, 0xD9-0xDB); last byte: 0x", last_token), "string"), nullptr));
10122  }
10123  }
10124  }
10125 
10136  bool get_msgpack_binary(binary_t& result)
10137  {
10138  // helper function to set the subtype
10139  auto assign_and_return_true = [&result](std::int8_t subtype)
10140  {
10141  result.set_subtype(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(subtype));
10142  return true;
10143  };
10144 
10145  switch (current)
10146  {
10147  case 0xC4: // bin 8
10148  {
10149  std::uint8_t len{};
10150  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
10151  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
10152  }
10153 
10154  case 0xC5: // bin 16
10155  {
10156  std::uint16_t len{};
10157  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
10158  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
10159  }
10160 
10161  case 0xC6: // bin 32
10162  {
10163  std::uint32_t len{};
10164  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
10165  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result);
10166  }
10167 
10168  case 0xC7: // ext 8
10169  {
10170  std::uint8_t len{};
10171  std::int8_t subtype{};
10172  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
10173  get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
10174  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result) &&
10175  assign_and_return_true(subtype);
10176  }
10177 
10178  case 0xC8: // ext 16
10179  {
10180  std::uint16_t len{};
10181  std::int8_t subtype{};
10182  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
10183  get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
10184  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result) &&
10185  assign_and_return_true(subtype);
10186  }
10187 
10188  case 0xC9: // ext 32
10189  {
10190  std::uint32_t len{};
10191  std::int8_t subtype{};
10192  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, len) &&
10193  get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
10194  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, len, result) &&
10195  assign_and_return_true(subtype);
10196  }
10197 
10198  case 0xD4: // fixext 1
10199  {
10200  std::int8_t subtype{};
10201  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
10202  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 1, result) &&
10203  assign_and_return_true(subtype);
10204  }
10205 
10206  case 0xD5: // fixext 2
10207  {
10208  std::int8_t subtype{};
10209  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
10210  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 2, result) &&
10211  assign_and_return_true(subtype);
10212  }
10213 
10214  case 0xD6: // fixext 4
10215  {
10216  std::int8_t subtype{};
10217  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
10218  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 4, result) &&
10219  assign_and_return_true(subtype);
10220  }
10221 
10222  case 0xD7: // fixext 8
10223  {
10224  std::int8_t subtype{};
10225  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
10226  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 8, result) &&
10227  assign_and_return_true(subtype);
10228  }
10229 
10230  case 0xD8: // fixext 16
10231  {
10232  std::int8_t subtype{};
10233  return get_number(input_format_t::msgpack, subtype) &&
10234  get_binary(input_format_t::msgpack, 16, result) &&
10235  assign_and_return_true(subtype);
10236  }
10237 
10238  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
10239  return false; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
10240  }
10241  }
10242 
10247  bool get_msgpack_array(const std::size_t len)
10248  {
10249  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(len)))
10250  {
10251  return false;
10252  }
10253 
10254  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
10255  {
10256  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_msgpack_internal()))
10257  {
10258  return false;
10259  }
10260  }
10261 
10262  return sax->end_array();
10263  }
10264 
10269  bool get_msgpack_object(const std::size_t len)
10270  {
10271  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(len)))
10272  {
10273  return false;
10274  }
10275 
10276  string_t key;
10277  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < len; ++i)
10278  {
10279  get();
10280  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_msgpack_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
10281  {
10282  return false;
10283  }
10284 
10285  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_msgpack_internal()))
10286  {
10287  return false;
10288  }
10289  key.clear();
10290  }
10291 
10292  return sax->end_object();
10293  }

10296  // UBJSON //
