10306  bool parse_ubjson_internal(const bool get_char = true)
10307  {
10308  return get_ubjson_value(get_char ? get_ignore_noop() : current);
10309  }
10310 
10325  bool get_ubjson_string(string_t& result, const bool get_char = true)
10326  {
10327  if (get_char)
10328  {
10329  get(); // TODO(niels): may we ignore N here?
10330  }
10331 
10332  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format, "value")))
10333  {
10334  return false;
10335  }
10336 
10337  switch (current)
10338  {
10339  case 'U':
10340  {
10341  std::uint8_t len{};
10342  return get_number(input_format, len) && get_string(input_format, len, result);
10343  }
10344 
10345  case 'i':
10346  {
10347  std::int8_t len{};
10348  return get_number(input_format, len) && get_string(input_format, len, result);
10349  }
10350 
10351  case 'I':
10352  {
10353  std::int16_t len{};
10354  return get_number(input_format, len) && get_string(input_format, len, result);
10355  }
10356 
10357  case 'l':
10358  {
10359  std::int32_t len{};
10360  return get_number(input_format, len) && get_string(input_format, len, result);
10361  }
10362 
10363  case 'L':
10364  {
10365  std::int64_t len{};
10366  return get_number(input_format, len) && get_string(input_format, len, result);
10367  }
10368 
10369  case 'u':
10370  {
10371  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10372  {
10373  break;
10374  }
10375  std::uint16_t len{};
10376  return get_number(input_format, len) && get_string(input_format, len, result);
10377  }
10378 
10379  case 'm':
10380  {
10381  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10382  {
10383  break;
10384  }
10385  std::uint32_t len{};
10386  return get_number(input_format, len) && get_string(input_format, len, result);
10387  }
10388 
10389  case 'M':
10390  {
10391  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10392  {
10393  break;
10394  }
10395  std::uint64_t len{};
10396  return get_number(input_format, len) && get_string(input_format, len, result);
10397  }
10398 
10399  default:
10400  break;
10401  }
10402  auto last_token = get_token_string();
10403  std::string message;
10404 
10405  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10406  {
10407  message = "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L); last byte: 0x" + last_token;
10408  }
10409  else
10410  {
10411  message = "expected length type specification (U, i, u, I, m, l, M, L); last byte: 0x" + last_token;
10412  }
10413  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format, message, "string"), nullptr));
10414  }
10415 
10420  bool get_ubjson_ndarray_size(std::vector<size_t>& dim)
10421  {
10422  std::pair<std::size_t, char_int_type> size_and_type;
10423  size_t dimlen = 0;
10424  bool is_ndarray = true;
10425 
10426  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
10427  {
10428  return false;
10429  }
10430 
10431  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
10432  {
10433  if (size_and_type.second != 0)
10434  {
10435  if (size_and_type.second != 'N')
10436  {
10437  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
10438  {
10439  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_size_value(dimlen, is_ndarray, size_and_type.second)))
10440  {
10441  return false;
10442  }
10443  dim.push_back(dimlen);
10444  }
10445  }
10446  }
10447  else
10448  {
10449  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
10450  {
10451  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_size_value(dimlen, is_ndarray)))
10452  {
10453  return false;
10454  }
10455  dim.push_back(dimlen);
10456  }
10457  }
10458  }
10459  else
10460  {
10461  while (current != ']')
10462  {
10463  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_size_value(dimlen, is_ndarray, current)))
10464  {
10465  return false;
10466  }
10467  dim.push_back(dimlen);
10468  get_ignore_noop();
10469  }
10470  }
10471  return true;
10472  }
10473 
10478  bool get_ubjson_size_value(std::size_t& result, bool& is_ndarray, char_int_type prefix = 0)
10479  {
10480  if (prefix == 0)
10481  {
10482  prefix = get_ignore_noop();
10483  }
10484 
10485  switch (prefix)
10486  {
10487  case 'U':
10488  {
10489  std::uint8_t number{};
10490  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format, number)))
10491  {
10492  return false;
10493  }
10494  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
10495  return true;
10496  }
10497 
10498  case 'i':
10499  {
10500  std::int8_t number{};
10501  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format, number)))
10502  {
10503  return false;
10504  }
10505  if (number < 0)
10506  {
10507  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(), parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
10508  exception_message(input_format, "count in an optimized container must be positive", "size"), nullptr));
10509  }
10510  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number); // NOLINT(bugprone-signed-char-misuse,cert-str34-c): number is not a char
10511  return true;
10512  }
10513 
10514  case 'I':
10515  {
10516  std::int16_t number{};
10517  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format, number)))
10518  {
10519  return false;
10520  }
10521  if (number < 0)
10522  {
10523  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(), parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
10524  exception_message(input_format, "count in an optimized container must be positive", "size"), nullptr));
10525  }
10526  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
10527  return true;
10528  }
10529 
10530  case 'l':
10531  {
10532  std::int32_t number{};
10533  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format, number)))
10534  {
10535  return false;
10536  }
10537  if (number < 0)
10538  {
10539  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(), parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
10540  exception_message(input_format, "count in an optimized container must be positive", "size"), nullptr));
10541  }
10542  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
10543  return true;
10544  }
10545 
10546  case 'L':
10547  {
10548  std::int64_t number{};
10549  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format, number)))
10550  {
10551  return false;
10552  }
10553  if (number < 0)
10554  {
10555  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(), parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
10556  exception_message(input_format, "count in an optimized container must be positive", "size"), nullptr));
10557  }
10558  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
10559  return true;
10560  }
10561 
10562  case 'u':
10563  {
10564  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10565  {
10566  break;
10567  }
10568  std::uint16_t number{};
10569  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format, number)))
10570  {
10571  return false;
10572  }
10573  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
10574  return true;
10575  }
10576 
10577  case 'm':
10578  {
10579  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10580  {
10581  break;
10582  }
10583  std::uint32_t number{};
10584  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format, number)))
10585  {
10586  return false;
10587  }
10588  result = static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
10589  return true;
10590  }
10591 
10592  case 'M':
10593  {
10594  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10595  {
10596  break;
10597  }
10598  std::uint64_t number{};
10599  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_number(input_format, number)))
10600  {
10601  return false;
10602  }
10603  result = detail::conditional_static_cast<std::size_t>(number);
10604  return true;
10605  }
10606 
10607  case '[':
10608  {
10609  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10610  {
10611  break;
10612  }
10613  if (is_ndarray) // ndarray dimensional vector can only contain integers, and can not embed another array
10614  {
10615  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, get_token_string(), parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format, "ndarray dimention vector can only contain integers", "size"), nullptr));
10616  }
10617  std::vector<size_t> dim;
10618  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_ndarray_size(dim)))
10619  {
10620  return false;
10621  }
10622  if (dim.size() == 1 || (dim.size() == 2 && dim.at(0) == 1)) // return normal array size if 1D row vector
10623  {
10624  result = dim.at(dim.size() - 1);
10625  return true;
10626  }
10627  if (!dim.empty()) // if ndarray, convert to an object in JData annotated array format
10628  {
10629  for (auto i : dim) // test if any dimension in an ndarray is 0, if so, return a 1D empty container
10630  {
10631  if ( i == 0 )
10632  {
10633  result = 0;
10634  return true;
10635  }
10636  }
10637 
10638  string_t key = "_ArraySize_";
10639  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(3) || !sax->key(key) || !sax->start_array(dim.size())))
10640  {
10641  return false;
10642  }
10643  result = 1;
10644  for (auto i : dim)
10645  {
10646  result *= i;
10647  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->number_integer(static_cast<number_integer_t>(i))))
10648  {
10649  return false;
10650  }
10651  }
10652  is_ndarray = true;
10653  return sax->end_array();
10654  }
10655  result = 0;
10656  return true;
10657  }
10658 
10659  default:
10660  break;
10661  }
10662  auto last_token = get_token_string();
10663  std::string message;
10664 
10665  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10666  {
10667  message = "expected length type specification (U, i, I, l, L) after '#'; last byte: 0x" + last_token;
10668  }
10669  else
10670  {
10671  message = "expected length type specification (U, i, u, I, m, l, M, L) after '#'; last byte: 0x" + last_token;
10672  }
10673  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read, exception_message(input_format, message, "size"), nullptr));
10674  }
10675 
10686  bool get_ubjson_size_type(std::pair<std::size_t, char_int_type>& result)
10687  {
10688  bool is_ndarray = false;
10689  result.first = string_t::npos; // size
10690  result.second = 0; // type
10691 
10692  get_ignore_noop();
10693 
10694  if (current == '$')
10695  {
10696  std::vector<char_int_type> bjdx = {'[', '{', 'S', 'H', 'T', 'F', 'N', 'Z'}; // excluded markers in bjdata optimized type
10697 
10698  result.second = get(); // must not ignore 'N', because 'N' maybe the type
10699  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY( input_format == input_format_t::bjdata && std::find(bjdx.begin(), bjdx.end(), result.second) != bjdx.end() ))
10700  {
10701  auto last_token = get_token_string();
10702  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
10703  exception_message(input_format, concat("marker 0x", last_token, " is not a permitted optimized array type"), "type"), nullptr));
10704  }
10705 
10706  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format, "type")))
10707  {
10708  return false;
10709  }
10710 
10711  get_ignore_noop();
10712  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current != '#'))
10713  {
10714  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format, "value")))
10715  {
10716  return false;
10717  }
10718  auto last_token = get_token_string();
10719  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
10720  exception_message(input_format, concat("expected '#' after type information; last byte: 0x", last_token), "size"), nullptr));
10721  }
10722 
10723  bool is_error = get_ubjson_size_value(result.first, is_ndarray);
10724  if (input_format == input_format_t::bjdata && is_ndarray)
10725  {
10726  result.second |= (1 << 8); // use bit 8 to indicate ndarray, all UBJSON and BJData markers should be ASCII letters
10727  }
10728  return is_error;
10729  }
10730 
10731  if (current == '#')
10732  {
10733  bool is_error = get_ubjson_size_value(result.first, is_ndarray);
10734  if (input_format == input_format_t::bjdata && is_ndarray)
10735  {
10736  result.second |= (1 << 8); // use bit 8 to indicate ndarray, all UBJSON and BJData markers should be ASCII letters
10737  }
10738  return is_error;
10739  }
10740 
10741  return true;
10742  }
10743 
10748  bool get_ubjson_value(const char_int_type prefix)
10749  {
10750  switch (prefix)
10751  {
10752  case std::char_traits<char_type>::eof(): // EOF
10753  return unexpect_eof(input_format, "value");
10754 
10755  case 'T': // true
10756  return sax->boolean(true);
10757  case 'F': // false
10758  return sax->boolean(false);
10759 
10760  case 'Z': // null
10761  return sax->null();
10762 
10763  case 'U':
10764  {
10765  std::uint8_t number{};
10766  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
10767  }
10768 
10769  case 'i':
10770  {
10771  std::int8_t number{};
10772  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_integer(number);
10773  }
10774 
10775  case 'I':
10776  {
10777  std::int16_t number{};
10778  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_integer(number);
10779  }
10780 
10781  case 'l':
10782  {
10783  std::int32_t number{};
10784  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_integer(number);
10785  }
10786 
10787  case 'L':
10788  {
10789  std::int64_t number{};
10790  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_integer(number);
10791  }
10792 
10793  case 'u':
10794  {
10795  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10796  {
10797  break;
10798  }
10799  std::uint16_t number{};
10800  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
10801  }
10802 
10803  case 'm':
10804  {
10805  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10806  {
10807  break;
10808  }
10809  std::uint32_t number{};
10810  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
10811  }
10812 
10813  case 'M':
10814  {
10815  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10816  {
10817  break;
10818  }
10819  std::uint64_t number{};
10820  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_unsigned(number);
10821  }
10822 
10823  case 'h':
10824  {
10825  if (input_format != input_format_t::bjdata)
10826  {
10827  break;
10828  }
10829  const auto byte1_raw = get();
10830  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format, "number")))
10831  {
10832  return false;
10833  }
10834  const auto byte2_raw = get();
10835  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format, "number")))
10836  {
10837  return false;
10838  }
10839 
10840  const auto byte1 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte1_raw);
10841  const auto byte2 = static_cast<unsigned char>(byte2_raw);
10842 
10843  // code from RFC 7049, Appendix D, Figure 3:
10844  // As half-precision floating-point numbers were only added
10845  // to IEEE 754 in 2008, today's programming platforms often
10846  // still only have limited support for them. It is very
10847  // easy to include at least decoding support for them even
10848  // without such support. An example of a small decoder for
10849  // half-precision floating-point numbers in the C language
10850  // is shown in Fig. 3.
10851  const auto half = static_cast<unsigned int>((byte2 << 8u) + byte1);
10852  const double val = [&half]
10853  {
10854  const int exp = (half >> 10u) & 0x1Fu;
10855  const unsigned int mant = half & 0x3FFu;
10856  JSON_ASSERT(0 <= exp&& exp <= 32);
10857  JSON_ASSERT(mant <= 1024);
10858  switch (exp)
10859  {
10860  case 0:
10861  return std::ldexp(mant, -24);
10862  case 31:
10863  return (mant == 0)
10864  ? std::numeric_limits<double>::infinity()
10865  : std::numeric_limits<double>::quiet_NaN();
10866  default:
10867  return std::ldexp(mant + 1024, exp - 25);
10868  }
10869  }();
10870  return sax->number_float((half & 0x8000u) != 0
10871  ? static_cast<number_float_t>(-val)
10872  : static_cast<number_float_t>(val), "");
10873  }
10874 
10875  case 'd':
10876  {
10877  float number{};
10878  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
10879  }
10880 
10881  case 'D':
10882  {
10883  double number{};
10884  return get_number(input_format, number) && sax->number_float(static_cast<number_float_t>(number), "");
10885  }
10886 
10887  case 'H':
10888  {
10889  return get_ubjson_high_precision_number();
10890  }
10891 
10892  case 'C': // char
10893  {
10894  get();
10895  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format, "char")))
10896  {
10897  return false;
10898  }
10899  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current > 127))
10900  {
10901  auto last_token = get_token_string();
10902  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(113, chars_read,
10903  exception_message(input_format, concat("byte after 'C' must be in range 0x00..0x7F; last byte: 0x", last_token), "char"), nullptr));
10904  }
10905  string_t s(1, static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(current));
10906  return sax->string(s);
10907  }
10908 
10909  case 'S': // string
10910  {
10911  string_t s;
10912  return get_ubjson_string(s) && sax->string(s);
10913  }
10914 
10915  case '[': // array
10916  return get_ubjson_array();
10917 
10918  case '{': // object
10919  return get_ubjson_object();
10920 
10921  default: // anything else
10922  break;
10923  }
10924  auto last_token = get_token_string();
10925  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read, exception_message(input_format, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "value"), nullptr));
10926  }
10927 
10931  bool get_ubjson_array()
10932  {
10933  std::pair<std::size_t, char_int_type> size_and_type;
10934  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
10935  {
10936  return false;
10937  }
10938 
10939  // if bit-8 of size_and_type.second is set to 1, encode bjdata ndarray as an object in JData annotated array format (https://github.com/NeuroJSON/jdata):
10940  // {"_ArrayType_" : "typeid", "_ArraySize_" : [n1, n2, ...], "_ArrayData_" : [v1, v2, ...]}
10941 
10942  if (input_format == input_format_t::bjdata && size_and_type.first != string_t::npos && (size_and_type.second & (1 << 8)) != 0)
10943  {
10944  std::map<char_int_type, string_t> bjdtype = {{'U', "uint8"}, {'i', "int8"}, {'u', "uint16"}, {'I', "int16"},
10945  {'m', "uint32"}, {'l', "int32"}, {'M', "uint64"}, {'L', "int64"}, {'d', "single"}, {'D', "double"}, {'C', "char"}
10946  };
10947 
10948  size_and_type.second &= ~(static_cast<char_int_type>(1) << 8); // use bit 8 to indicate ndarray, here we remove the bit to restore the type marker
10949 
10950  string_t key = "_ArrayType_";
10951  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(bjdtype.count(size_and_type.second) == 0))
10952  {
10953  auto last_token = get_token_string();
10954  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
10955  exception_message(input_format, "invalid byte: 0x" + last_token, "type"), nullptr));
10956  }
10957 
10958  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->key(key) || !sax->string(bjdtype[size_and_type.second]) ))
10959  {
10960  return false;
10961  }
10962 
10963  if (size_and_type.second == 'C')
10964  {
10965  size_and_type.second = 'U';
10966  }
10967 
10968  key = "_ArrayData_";
10969  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->key(key) || !sax->start_array(size_and_type.first) ))
10970  {
10971  return false;
10972  }
10973 
10974  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
10975  {
10976  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
10977  {
10978  return false;
10979  }
10980  }
10981 
10982  return (sax->end_array() && sax->end_object());
10983  }
10984 
10985  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
10986  {
10987  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(size_and_type.first)))
10988  {
10989  return false;
10990  }
10991 
10992  if (size_and_type.second != 0)
10993  {
10994  if (size_and_type.second != 'N')
10995  {
10996  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
10997  {
10998  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
10999  {
11000  return false;
11001  }
11002  }
11003  }
11004  }
11005  else
11006  {
11007  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
11008  {
11009  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_ubjson_internal()))
11010  {
11011  return false;
11012  }
11013  }
11014  }
11015  }
11016  else
11017  {
11018  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))))
11019  {
11020  return false;
11021  }
11022 
11023  while (current != ']')
11024  {
11025  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_ubjson_internal(false)))
11026  {
11027  return false;
11028  }
11029  get_ignore_noop();
11030  }
11031  }
11032 
11033  return sax->end_array();
11034  }
11035 
11039  bool get_ubjson_object()
11040  {
11041  std::pair<std::size_t, char_int_type> size_and_type;
11042  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_size_type(size_and_type)))
11043  {
11044  return false;
11045  }
11046 
11047  // do not accept ND-array size in objects in BJData
11048  if (input_format == input_format_t::bjdata && size_and_type.first != string_t::npos && (size_and_type.second & (1 << 8)) != 0)
11049  {
11050  auto last_token = get_token_string();
11051  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, last_token, parse_error::create(112, chars_read,
11052  exception_message(input_format, "BJData object does not support ND-array size in optimized format", "object"), nullptr));
11053  }
11054 
11055  string_t key;
11056  if (size_and_type.first != string_t::npos)
11057  {
11058  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(size_and_type.first)))
11059  {
11060  return false;
11061  }
11062 
11063  if (size_and_type.second != 0)
11064  {
11065  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
11066  {
11067  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
11068  {
11069  return false;
11070  }
11071  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_value(size_and_type.second)))
11072  {
11073  return false;
11074  }
11075  key.clear();
11076  }
11077  }
11078  else
11079  {
11080  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size_and_type.first; ++i)
11081  {
11082  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_string(key) || !sax->key(key)))
11083  {
11084  return false;
11085  }
11086  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_ubjson_internal()))
11087  {
11088  return false;
11089  }
11090  key.clear();
11091  }
11092  }
11093  }
11094  else
11095  {
11096  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))))
11097  {
11098  return false;
11099  }
11100 
11101  while (current != '}')
11102  {
11103  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!get_ubjson_string(key, false) || !sax->key(key)))
11104  {
11105  return false;
11106  }
11107  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!parse_ubjson_internal()))
11108  {
11109  return false;
11110  }
11111  get_ignore_noop();
11112  key.clear();
11113  }
11114  }
11115 
11116  return sax->end_object();
11117  }
11118 
11119  // Note, no reader for UBJSON binary types is implemented because they do
11120  // not exist
11121 
11122  bool get_ubjson_high_precision_number()
11123  {
11124  // get size of following number string
11125  std::size_t size{};
11126  bool is_ndarray = false;
11127  auto res = get_ubjson_size_value(size, is_ndarray);
11128  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!res))
11129  {
11130  return res;
11131  }
11132 
11133  // get number string
11134  std::vector<char> number_vector;
11135  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < size; ++i)
11136  {
11137  get();
11138  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(input_format, "number")))
11139  {
11140  return false;
11141  }
11142  number_vector.push_back(static_cast<char>(current));
11143  }
11144 
11145  // parse number string
11146  using ia_type = decltype(detail::input_adapter(number_vector));
11147  auto number_lexer = detail::lexer<BasicJsonType, ia_type>(detail::input_adapter(number_vector), false);
11148  const auto result_number = number_lexer.scan();
11149  const auto number_string = number_lexer.get_token_string();
11150  const auto result_remainder = number_lexer.scan();
11151 
11152  using token_type = typename detail::lexer_base<BasicJsonType>::token_type;
11153 
11154  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(result_remainder != token_type::end_of_input))
11155  {
11156  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, number_string, parse_error::create(115, chars_read,
11157  exception_message(input_format, concat("invalid number text: ", number_lexer.get_token_string()), "high-precision number"), nullptr));
11158  }
11159 
11160  switch (result_number)
11161  {
11162  case token_type::value_integer:
11163  return sax->number_integer(number_lexer.get_number_integer());
11164  case token_type::value_unsigned:
11165  return sax->number_unsigned(number_lexer.get_number_unsigned());
11166  case token_type::value_float:
11167  return sax->number_float(number_lexer.get_number_float(), std::move(number_string));
11168  case token_type::uninitialized:
11169  case token_type::literal_true:
11170  case token_type::literal_false:
11171  case token_type::literal_null:
11172  case token_type::value_string:
11173  case token_type::begin_array:
11174  case token_type::begin_object:
11175  case token_type::end_array:
11176  case token_type::end_object:
11177  case token_type::name_separator:
11178  case token_type::value_separator:
11179  case token_type::parse_error:
11180  case token_type::end_of_input:
11181  case token_type::literal_or_value:
11182  default:
11183  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, number_string, parse_error::create(115, chars_read,
11184  exception_message(input_format, concat("invalid number text: ", number_lexer.get_token_string()), "high-precision number"), nullptr));
11185  }
11186  }
11187 
11189  // Utility functions //
11191 
11201  char_int_type get()
11202  {
11203  ++chars_read;
11204  return current = ia.get_character();
11205  }
11206 
11210  char_int_type get_ignore_noop()
11211  {
11212  do
11213  {
11214  get();
11215  }
11216  while (current == 'N');
11217 
11218  return current;
11219  }
11220 
11221  /*
11222  @brief read a number from the input
11223 
11224  @tparam NumberType the type of the number
11225  @param[in] format the current format (for diagnostics)
11226  @param[out] result number of type @a NumberType
11227 
11228  @return whether conversion completed
11229 
11230  @note This function needs to respect the system's endianness, because
11231  bytes in CBOR, MessagePack, and UBJSON are stored in network order
11232  (big endian) and therefore need reordering on little endian systems.
11233  On the other hand, BSON and BJData use little endian and should reorder
11234  on big endian systems.
11235  */
11236  template<typename NumberType, bool InputIsLittleEndian = false>
11237  bool get_number(const input_format_t format, NumberType& result)
11238  {
11239  // step 1: read input into array with system's byte order
11240  std::array<std::uint8_t, sizeof(NumberType)> vec{};
11241  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < sizeof(NumberType); ++i)
11242  {
11243  get();
11244  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(format, "number")))
11245  {
11246  return false;
11247  }
11248 
11249  // reverse byte order prior to conversion if necessary
11250  if (is_little_endian != (InputIsLittleEndian || format == input_format_t::bjdata))
11251  {
11252  vec[sizeof(NumberType) - i - 1] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current);
11253  }
11254  else
11255  {
11256  vec[i] = static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
11257  }
11258  }
11259 
11260  // step 2: convert array into number of type T and return
11261  std::memcpy(&result, vec.data(), sizeof(NumberType));
11262  return true;
11263  }
11264 
11279  template<typename NumberType>
11280  bool get_string(const input_format_t format,
11281  const NumberType len,
11282  string_t& result)
11283  {
11284  bool success = true;
11285  for (NumberType i = 0; i < len; i++)
11286  {
11287  get();
11288  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(format, "string")))
11289  {
11290  success = false;
11291  break;
11292  }
11293  result.push_back(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(current));
11294  }
11295  return success;
11296  }
11297 
11312  template<typename NumberType>
11313  bool get_binary(const input_format_t format,
11314  const NumberType len,
11315  binary_t& result)
11316  {
11317  bool success = true;
11318  for (NumberType i = 0; i < len; i++)
11319  {
11320  get();
11321  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!unexpect_eof(format, "binary")))
11322  {
11323  success = false;
11324  break;
11325  }
11326  result.push_back(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(current));
11327  }
11328  return success;
11329  }
11330 
11336  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(3)
11337  bool unexpect_eof(const input_format_t format, const char* context) const
11338  {
11339  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(current == std::char_traits<char_type>::eof()))
11340  {
11341  return sax->parse_error(chars_read, "<end of file>",
11342  parse_error::create(110, chars_read, exception_message(format, "unexpected end of input", context), nullptr));
11343  }
11344  return true;
11345  }
11346 
11350  std::string get_token_string() const
11351  {
11352  std::array<char, 3> cr{{}};
11353  static_cast<void>((std::snprintf)(cr.data(), cr.size(), "%.2hhX", static_cast<unsigned char>(current))); // NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg,hicpp-vararg)
11354  return std::string{cr.data()};
11355  }
11356 
11363  std::string exception_message(const input_format_t format,
11364  const std::string& detail,
11365  const std::string& context) const
11366  {
11367  std::string error_msg = "syntax error while parsing ";
11368 
11369  switch (format)
11370  {
11371  case input_format_t::cbor:
11372  error_msg += "CBOR";
11373  break;
11374 
11375  case input_format_t::msgpack:
11376  error_msg += "MessagePack";
11377  break;
11378 
11379  case input_format_t::ubjson:
11380  error_msg += "UBJSON";
11381  break;
11382 
11383  case input_format_t::bson:
11384  error_msg += "BSON";
11385  break;
11386 
11387  case input_format_t::bjdata:
11388  error_msg += "BJData";
11389  break;
11390 
11391  case input_format_t::json: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
11392  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
11393  JSON_ASSERT(false); // NOLINT(cert-dcl03-c,hicpp-static-assert,misc-static-assert) LCOV_EXCL_LINE
11394  }
11395 
11396  return concat(error_msg, ' ', context, ": ", detail);
11397  }
11398 
11399  private:
11401  InputAdapterType ia;
11402 
11404  char_int_type current = std::char_traits<char_type>::eof();
11405 
11407  std::size_t chars_read = 0;
11408 
11410  const bool is_little_endian = little_endianness();
11411 
11413  const input_format_t input_format = input_format_t::json;
11414 
11416  json_sax_t* sax = nullptr;
11417 };

11457 // parser //
11459 
11460 enum class parse_event_t : std::uint8_t
11461 {
11463  object_start,
11465  object_end,
11467  array_start,
11469  array_end,
11471  key,
11473  value
11474 };
11475 
11476 template<typename BasicJsonType>
11477 using parser_callback_t =
11478  std::function<bool(int /*depth*/, parse_event_t /*event*/, BasicJsonType& /*parsed*/)>;
11479 
11485 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename InputAdapterType>
11486 class parser
11487 {
11488  using number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
11489  using number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
11490  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
11491  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
11492  using lexer_t = lexer<BasicJsonType, InputAdapterType>;
11493  using token_type = typename lexer_t::token_type;
11494 
11495  public:
11497  explicit parser(InputAdapterType&& adapter,
11498  const parser_callback_t<BasicJsonType> cb = nullptr,
11499  const bool allow_exceptions_ = true,
11500  const bool skip_comments = false)
11501  : callback(cb)
11502  , m_lexer(std::move(adapter), skip_comments)
11503  , allow_exceptions(allow_exceptions_)
11504  {
11505  // read first token
11506  get_token();
11507  }
11508 
11519  void parse(const bool strict, BasicJsonType& result)
11520  {
11521  if (callback)
11522  {
11523  json_sax_dom_callback_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, callback, allow_exceptions);
11524  sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
11525 
11526  // in strict mode, input must be completely read
11527  if (strict && (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
11528  {
11529  sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11530  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11531  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(),
11532  exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value"), nullptr));
11533  }
11534 
11535  // in case of an error, return discarded value
11536  if (sdp.is_errored())
11537  {
11538  result = value_t::discarded;
11539  return;
11540  }
11541 
11542  // set top-level value to null if it was discarded by the callback
11543  // function
11544  if (result.is_discarded())
11545  {
11546  result = nullptr;
11547  }
11548  }
11549  else
11550  {
11551  json_sax_dom_parser<BasicJsonType> sdp(result, allow_exceptions);
11552  sax_parse_internal(&sdp);
11553 
11554  // in strict mode, input must be completely read
11555  if (strict && (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
11556  {
11557  sdp.parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11558  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11559  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value"), nullptr));
11560  }
11561 
11562  // in case of an error, return discarded value
11563  if (sdp.is_errored())
11564  {
11565  result = value_t::discarded;
11566  return;
11567  }
11568  }
11569 
11570  result.assert_invariant();
11571  }
11572 
11579  bool accept(const bool strict = true)
11580  {
11581  json_sax_acceptor<BasicJsonType> sax_acceptor;
11582  return sax_parse(&sax_acceptor, strict);
11583  }
11584 
11585  template<typename SAX>
11586  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
11587  bool sax_parse(SAX* sax, const bool strict = true)
11588  {
11589  (void)detail::is_sax_static_asserts<SAX, BasicJsonType> {};
11590  const bool result = sax_parse_internal(sax);
11591 
11592  // strict mode: next byte must be EOF
11593  if (result && strict && (get_token() != token_type::end_of_input))
11594  {
11595  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11596  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11597  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_of_input, "value"), nullptr));
11598  }
11599 
11600  return result;
11601  }
11602 
11603  private:
11604  template<typename SAX>
11605  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
11606  bool sax_parse_internal(SAX* sax)
11607  {
11608  // stack to remember the hierarchy of structured values we are parsing
11609  // true = array; false = object
11610  std::vector<bool> states;
11611  // value to avoid a goto (see comment where set to true)
11612  bool skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
11613 
11614  while (true)
11615  {
11616  if (!skip_to_state_evaluation)
11617  {
11618  // invariant: get_token() was called before each iteration
11619  switch (last_token)
11620  {
11621  case token_type::begin_object:
11622  {
11623  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_object(static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))))
11624  {
11625  return false;
11626  }
11627 
11628  // closing } -> we are done
11629  if (get_token() == token_type::end_object)
11630  {
11631  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->end_object()))
11632  {
11633  return false;
11634  }
11635  break;
11636  }
11637 
11638  // parse key
11639  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(last_token != token_type::value_string))
11640  {
11641  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11642  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11643  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key"), nullptr));
11644  }
11645  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
11646  {
11647  return false;
11648  }
11649 
11650  // parse separator (:)
11651  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
11652  {
11653  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11654  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11655  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator"), nullptr));
11656  }
11657 
11658  // remember we are now inside an object
11659  states.push_back(false);
11660 
11661  // parse values
11662  get_token();
11663  continue;
11664  }
11665 
11666  case token_type::begin_array:
11667  {
11668  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->start_array(static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))))
11669  {
11670  return false;
11671  }
11672 
11673  // closing ] -> we are done
11674  if (get_token() == token_type::end_array)
11675  {
11676  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->end_array()))
11677  {
11678  return false;
11679  }
11680  break;
11681  }
11682 
11683  // remember we are now inside an array
11684  states.push_back(true);
11685 
11686  // parse values (no need to call get_token)
11687  continue;
11688  }
11689 
11690  case token_type::value_float:
11691  {
11692  const auto res = m_lexer.get_number_float();
11693 
11694  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!std::isfinite(res)))
11695  {
11696  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11697  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11698  out_of_range::create(406, concat("number overflow parsing '", m_lexer.get_token_string(), '\''), nullptr));
11699  }
11700 
11701  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->number_float(res, m_lexer.get_string())))
11702  {
11703  return false;
11704  }
11705 
11706  break;
11707  }
11708 
11709  case token_type::literal_false:
11710  {
11711  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->boolean(false)))
11712  {
11713  return false;
11714  }
11715  break;
11716  }
11717 
11718  case token_type::literal_null:
11719  {
11720  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->null()))
11721  {
11722  return false;
11723  }
11724  break;
11725  }
11726 
11727  case token_type::literal_true:
11728  {
11729  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->boolean(true)))
11730  {
11731  return false;
11732  }
11733  break;
11734  }
11735 
11736  case token_type::value_integer:
11737  {
11738  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->number_integer(m_lexer.get_number_integer())))
11739  {
11740  return false;
11741  }
11742  break;
11743  }
11744 
11745  case token_type::value_string:
11746  {
11747  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->string(m_lexer.get_string())))
11748  {
11749  return false;
11750  }
11751  break;
11752  }
11753 
11754  case token_type::value_unsigned:
11755  {
11756  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->number_unsigned(m_lexer.get_number_unsigned())))
11757  {
11758  return false;
11759  }
11760  break;
11761  }
11762 
11763  case token_type::parse_error:
11764  {
11765  // using "uninitialized" to avoid "expected" message
11766  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11767  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11768  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::uninitialized, "value"), nullptr));
11769  }
11770 
11771  case token_type::uninitialized:
11772  case token_type::end_array:
11773  case token_type::end_object:
11774  case token_type::name_separator:
11775  case token_type::value_separator:
11776  case token_type::end_of_input:
11777  case token_type::literal_or_value:
11778  default: // the last token was unexpected
11779  {
11780  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11781  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11782  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::literal_or_value, "value"), nullptr));
11783  }
11784  }
11785  }
11786  else
11787  {
11788  skip_to_state_evaluation = false;
11789  }
11790 
11791  // we reached this line after we successfully parsed a value
11792  if (states.empty())
11793  {
11794  // empty stack: we reached the end of the hierarchy: done
11795  return true;
11796  }
11797 
11798  if (states.back()) // array
11799  {
11800  // comma -> next value
11801  if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
11802  {
11803  // parse a new value
11804  get_token();
11805  continue;
11806  }
11807 
11808  // closing ]
11809  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_array))
11810  {
11811  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->end_array()))
11812  {
11813  return false;
11814  }
11815 
11816  // We are done with this array. Before we can parse a
11817  // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
11818  // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
11819  // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
11820  JSON_ASSERT(!states.empty());
11821  states.pop_back();
11822  skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
11823  continue;
11824  }
11825 
11826  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11827  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11828  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_array, "array"), nullptr));
11829  }
11830 
11831  // states.back() is false -> object
11832 
11833  // comma -> next value
11834  if (get_token() == token_type::value_separator)
11835  {
11836  // parse key
11837  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::value_string))
11838  {
11839  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11840  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11841  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::value_string, "object key"), nullptr));
11842  }
11843 
11844  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->key(m_lexer.get_string())))
11845  {
11846  return false;
11847  }
11848 
11849  // parse separator (:)
11850  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(get_token() != token_type::name_separator))
11851  {
11852  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11853  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11854  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::name_separator, "object separator"), nullptr));
11855  }
11856 
11857  // parse values
11858  get_token();
11859  continue;
11860  }
11861 
11862  // closing }
11863  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(last_token == token_type::end_object))
11864  {
11865  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!sax->end_object()))
11866  {
11867  return false;
11868  }
11869 
11870  // We are done with this object. Before we can parse a
11871  // new value, we need to evaluate the new state first.
11872  // By setting skip_to_state_evaluation to false, we
11873  // are effectively jumping to the beginning of this if.
11874  JSON_ASSERT(!states.empty());
11875  states.pop_back();
11876  skip_to_state_evaluation = true;
11877  continue;
11878  }
11879 
11880  return sax->parse_error(m_lexer.get_position(),
11881  m_lexer.get_token_string(),
11882  parse_error::create(101, m_lexer.get_position(), exception_message(token_type::end_object, "object"), nullptr));
11883  }
11884  }
11885 
11887  token_type get_token()
11888  {
11889  return last_token = m_lexer.scan();
11890  }
11891 
11892  std::string exception_message(const token_type expected, const std::string& context)
11893  {
11894  std::string error_msg = "syntax error ";
11895 
11896  if (!context.empty())
11897  {
11898  error_msg += concat("while parsing ", context, ' ');
11899  }
11900 
11901  error_msg += "- ";
11902 
11903  if (last_token == token_type::parse_error)
11904  {
11905  error_msg += concat(m_lexer.get_error_message(), "; last read: '",
11906  m_lexer.get_token_string(), '\'');
11907  }
11908  else
11909  {
11910  error_msg += concat("unexpected ", lexer_t::token_type_name(last_token));
11911  }
11912 
11913  if (expected != token_type::uninitialized)
11914  {
11915  error_msg += concat("; expected ", lexer_t::token_type_name(expected));
11916  }
11917 
11918  return error_msg;
11919  }
11920 
11921  private:
11923  const parser_callback_t<BasicJsonType> callback = nullptr;
11925  token_type last_token = token_type::uninitialized;
11927  lexer_t m_lexer;
11929  const bool allow_exceptions = true;
11930 };
11931 
11932 } // namespace detail
11933 } // namespace nlohmann
11934 
11935 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/internal_iterator.hpp>
11936 
11937 
11938 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
11939 
11940 
11941 #include <cstddef> // ptrdiff_t
11942 #include <limits> // numeric_limits
11943 
11944 // #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
11945 
11946 
11947 namespace nlohmann
11948 {
11949 namespace detail
11950 {
11951 /*
11952 @brief an iterator for primitive JSON types
11953 
11954 This class models an iterator for primitive JSON types (boolean, number,
11955 string). It's only purpose is to allow the iterator/const_iterator classes
11956 to "iterate" over primitive values. Internally, the iterator is modeled by
11957 a `difference_type` variable. Value begin_value (`0`) models the begin,
11958 end_value (`1`) models past the end.
11959 */
11960 class primitive_iterator_t
11961 {
11962  private:
11963  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
11964  static constexpr difference_type begin_value = 0;
11965  static constexpr difference_type end_value = begin_value + 1;
11966 
11967  JSON_PRIVATE_UNLESS_TESTED:
11969  difference_type m_it = (std::numeric_limits<std::ptrdiff_t>::min)();
11970 
11971  public:
11972  constexpr difference_type get_value() const noexcept
11973  {
11974  return m_it;
11975  }
11976 
11978  void set_begin() noexcept
11979  {
11980  m_it = begin_value;
11981  }
11982 
11984  void set_end() noexcept
11985  {
11986  m_it = end_value;
11987  }
11988 
11990  constexpr bool is_begin() const noexcept
11991  {
11992  return m_it == begin_value;
11993  }
11994 
11996  constexpr bool is_end() const noexcept
11997  {
11998  return m_it == end_value;
11999  }
12000 
12001  friend constexpr bool operator==(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
12002  {
12003  return lhs.m_it == rhs.m_it;
12004  }
12005 
12006  friend constexpr bool operator<(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
12007  {
12008  return lhs.m_it < rhs.m_it;
12009  }
12010 
12011  primitive_iterator_t operator+(difference_type n) noexcept
12012  {
12013  auto result = *this;
12014  result += n;
12015  return result;
12016  }
12017 
12018  friend constexpr difference_type operator-(primitive_iterator_t lhs, primitive_iterator_t rhs) noexcept
12019  {
12020  return lhs.m_it - rhs.m_it;
12021  }
12022 
12023  primitive_iterator_t& operator++() noexcept
12024  {
12025  ++m_it;
12026  return *this;
12027  }
12028 
12029  primitive_iterator_t operator++(int)& noexcept // NOLINT(cert-dcl21-cpp)
12030  {
12031  auto result = *this;
12032  ++m_it;
12033  return result;
12034  }
12035 
12036  primitive_iterator_t& operator--() noexcept
12037  {
12038  --m_it;
12039  return *this;
12040  }
12041 
12042  primitive_iterator_t operator--(int)& noexcept // NOLINT(cert-dcl21-cpp)
12043  {
12044  auto result = *this;
12045  --m_it;
12046  return result;
12047  }
12048 
12049  primitive_iterator_t& operator+=(difference_type n) noexcept
12050  {
12051  m_it += n;
12052  return *this;
12053  }
12054 
12055  primitive_iterator_t& operator-=(difference_type n) noexcept
12056  {
12057  m_it -= n;
12058  return *this;
12059  }
12060 };
12061 } // namespace detail
12062 } // namespace nlohmann
12063

12065 namespace nlohmann
12066 {
12067 namespace detail

12075 template<typename BasicJsonType> struct internal_iterator
12076 {
12078  typename BasicJsonType::object_t::iterator object_iterator {};
12080  typename BasicJsonType::array_t::iterator array_iterator {};
12082  primitive_iterator_t primitive_iterator {};
12083 };
12084 } // namespace detail

12089 
12090 #include <iterator> // iterator, random_access_iterator_tag, bidirectional_iterator_tag, advance, next
12091 #include <type_traits> // conditional, is_const, remove_const
12092 
12093 // #include <nlohmann/detail/exceptions.hpp>
12094 
12095 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/internal_iterator.hpp>
12096 
12097 // #include <nlohmann/detail/iterators/primitive_iterator.hpp>
12098 
12099 // #include <nlohmann/detail/macro_scope.hpp>
12100 
12101 // #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/cpp_future.hpp>
12102 
12103 // #include <nlohmann/detail/meta/type_traits.hpp>
12104 
12105 // #include <nlohmann/detail/value_t.hpp>
12106 
12107 
12108 namespace nlohmann
12109 {
12110 namespace detail
12111 {
12112 // forward declare, to be able to friend it later on
12113 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy;
12114 template<typename IteratorType> class iteration_proxy_value;
12115 
12132 template<typename BasicJsonType>
12133 class iter_impl // NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions,hicpp-special-member-functions)
12134 {
12136  using other_iter_impl = iter_impl<typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value, typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type, const BasicJsonType>::type>;
12138  friend other_iter_impl;
12139  friend BasicJsonType;
12140  friend iteration_proxy<iter_impl>;
12141  friend iteration_proxy_value<iter_impl>;
12142 
12143  using object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
12144  using array_t = typename BasicJsonType::array_t;
12145  // make sure BasicJsonType is basic_json or const basic_json
12146  static_assert(is_basic_json<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>::value,
12147  "iter_impl only accepts (const) basic_json");
12148 
12149  public:
12150 
12156  using iterator_category = std::bidirectional_iterator_tag;
12157 
12159  using value_type = typename BasicJsonType::value_type;
12161  using difference_type = typename BasicJsonType::difference_type;
12163  using pointer = typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
12164  typename BasicJsonType::const_pointer,
12165  typename BasicJsonType::pointer>::type;
12167  using reference =
12168  typename std::conditional<std::is_const<BasicJsonType>::value,
12169  typename BasicJsonType::const_reference,
12170  typename BasicJsonType::reference>::type;
12171 
12172  iter_impl() = default;
12173  ~iter_impl() = default;
12174  iter_impl(iter_impl&&) noexcept = default;
12175  iter_impl& operator=(iter_impl&&) noexcept = default;
12176 
12183  explicit iter_impl(pointer object) noexcept : m_object(object)
12184  {
12185  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12186 
12187  switch (m_object->m_type)
12188  {
12189  case value_t::object:
12190  {
12191  m_it.object_iterator = typename object_t::iterator();
12192  break;
12193  }
12194 
12195  case value_t::array:
12196  {
12197  m_it.array_iterator = typename array_t::iterator();
12198  break;
12199  }
12200 
12201  case value_t::null:
12202  case value_t::string:
12203  case value_t::boolean:
12204  case value_t::number_integer:
12205  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12206  case value_t::number_float:
12207  case value_t::binary:
12208  case value_t::discarded:
12209  default:
12210  {
12211  m_it.primitive_iterator = primitive_iterator_t();
12212  break;
12213  }
12214  }
12215  }
12216 
12233  iter_impl(const iter_impl<const BasicJsonType>& other) noexcept
12234  : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it)
12235  {}
12236 
12243  iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<const BasicJsonType>& other) noexcept
12244  {
12245  if (&other != this)
12246  {
12247  m_object = other.m_object;
12248  m_it = other.m_it;
12249  }
12250  return *this;
12251  }
12252 
12258  iter_impl(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept
12259  : m_object(other.m_object), m_it(other.m_it)
12260  {}
12261 
12268  iter_impl& operator=(const iter_impl<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type>& other) noexcept // NOLINT(cert-oop54-cpp)
12269  {
12270  m_object = other.m_object;
12271  m_it = other.m_it;
12272  return *this;
12273  }
12274 
12275  JSON_PRIVATE_UNLESS_TESTED:
12280  void set_begin() noexcept
12281  {
12282  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12283 
12284  switch (m_object->m_type)
12285  {
12286  case value_t::object:
12287  {
12288  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->begin();
12289  break;
12290  }
12291 
12292  case value_t::array:
12293  {
12294  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->begin();
12295  break;
12296  }
12297 
12298  case value_t::null:
12299  {
12300  // set to end so begin()==end() is true: null is empty
12301  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
12302  break;
12303  }
12304 
12305  case value_t::string:
12306  case value_t::boolean:
12307  case value_t::number_integer:
12308  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12309  case value_t::number_float:
12310  case value_t::binary:
12311  case value_t::discarded:
12312  default:
12313  {
12314  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_begin();
12315  break;
12316  }
12317  }
12318  }
12319 
12324  void set_end() noexcept
12325  {
12326  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12327 
12328  switch (m_object->m_type)
12329  {
12330  case value_t::object:
12331  {
12332  m_it.object_iterator = m_object->m_value.object->end();
12333  break;
12334  }
12335 
12336  case value_t::array:
12337  {
12338  m_it.array_iterator = m_object->m_value.array->end();
12339  break;
12340  }
12341 
12342  case value_t::null:
12343  case value_t::string:
12344  case value_t::boolean:
12345  case value_t::number_integer:
12346  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12347  case value_t::number_float:
12348  case value_t::binary:
12349  case value_t::discarded:
12350  default:
12351  {
12352  m_it.primitive_iterator.set_end();
12353  break;
12354  }
12355  }
12356  }
12357 
12358  public:
12363  reference operator*() const
12364  {
12365  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12366 
12367  switch (m_object->m_type)
12368  {
12369  case value_t::object:
12370  {
12371  JSON_ASSERT(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
12372  return m_it.object_iterator->second;
12373  }
12374 
12375  case value_t::array:
12376  {
12377  JSON_ASSERT(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
12378  return *m_it.array_iterator;
12379  }
12380 
12381  case value_t::null:
12382  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value", m_object));
12383 
12384  case value_t::string:
12385  case value_t::boolean:
12386  case value_t::number_integer:
12387  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12388  case value_t::number_float:
12389  case value_t::binary:
12390  case value_t::discarded:
12391  default:
12392  {
12393  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
12394  {
12395  return *m_object;
12396  }
12397 
12398  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value", m_object));
12399  }
12400  }
12401  }
12402 
12407  pointer operator->() const
12408  {
12409  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12410 
12411  switch (m_object->m_type)
12412  {
12413  case value_t::object:
12414  {
12415  JSON_ASSERT(m_it.object_iterator != m_object->m_value.object->end());
12416  return &(m_it.object_iterator->second);
12417  }
12418 
12419  case value_t::array:
12420  {
12421  JSON_ASSERT(m_it.array_iterator != m_object->m_value.array->end());
12422  return &*m_it.array_iterator;
12423  }
12424 
12425  case value_t::null:
12426  case value_t::string:
12427  case value_t::boolean:
12428  case value_t::number_integer:
12429  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12430  case value_t::number_float:
12431  case value_t::binary:
12432  case value_t::discarded:
12433  default:
12434  {
12435  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
12436  {
12437  return m_object;
12438  }
12439 
12440  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value", m_object));
12441  }
12442  }
12443  }
12444 
12449  iter_impl operator++(int)& // NOLINT(cert-dcl21-cpp)
12450  {
12451  auto result = *this;
12452  ++(*this);
12453  return result;
12454  }
12455 
12460  iter_impl& operator++()
12461  {
12462  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12463 
12464  switch (m_object->m_type)
12465  {
12466  case value_t::object:
12467  {
12468  std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, 1);
12469  break;
12470  }
12471 
12472  case value_t::array:
12473  {
12474  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, 1);
12475  break;
12476  }
12477 
12478  case value_t::null:
12479  case value_t::string:
12480  case value_t::boolean:
12481  case value_t::number_integer:
12482  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12483  case value_t::number_float:
12484  case value_t::binary:
12485  case value_t::discarded:
12486  default:
12487  {
12488  ++m_it.primitive_iterator;
12489  break;
12490  }
12491  }
12492 
12493  return *this;
12494  }
12495 
12500  iter_impl operator--(int)& // NOLINT(cert-dcl21-cpp)
12501  {
12502  auto result = *this;
12503  --(*this);
12504  return result;
12505  }
12506 
12511  iter_impl& operator--()
12512  {
12513  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12514 
12515  switch (m_object->m_type)
12516  {
12517  case value_t::object:
12518  {
12519  std::advance(m_it.object_iterator, -1);
12520  break;
12521  }
12522 
12523  case value_t::array:
12524  {
12525  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, -1);
12526  break;
12527  }
12528 
12529  case value_t::null:
12530  case value_t::string:
12531  case value_t::boolean:
12532  case value_t::number_integer:
12533  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12534  case value_t::number_float:
12535  case value_t::binary:
12536  case value_t::discarded:
12537  default:
12538  {
12539  --m_it.primitive_iterator;
12540  break;
12541  }
12542  }
12543

12545  }

12551  template < typename IterImpl, detail::enable_if_t < (std::is_same<IterImpl, iter_impl>::value || std::is_same<IterImpl, other_iter_impl>::value), std::nullptr_t > = nullptr >
12552  bool operator==(const IterImpl& other) const
12553  {
12554  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
12555  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
12556  {
12557  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers", m_object));
12558  }
12559 
12560  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12561 
12562  switch (m_object->m_type)
12563  {
12564  case value_t::object:
12565  return (m_it.object_iterator == other.m_it.object_iterator);
12566 
12567  case value_t::array:
12568  return (m_it.array_iterator == other.m_it.array_iterator);
12569 
12570  case value_t::null:
12571  case value_t::string:
12572  case value_t::boolean:
12573  case value_t::number_integer:
12574  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12575  case value_t::number_float:
12576  case value_t::binary:
12577  case value_t::discarded:
12578  default:
12579  return (m_it.primitive_iterator == other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
12580  }
12581  }
12582 
12587  template < typename IterImpl, detail::enable_if_t < (std::is_same<IterImpl, iter_impl>::value || std::is_same<IterImpl, other_iter_impl>::value), std::nullptr_t > = nullptr >
12588  bool operator!=(const IterImpl& other) const
12589  {
12590  return !operator==(other);
12591  }
12592 
12597  bool operator<(const iter_impl& other) const
12598  {
12599  // if objects are not the same, the comparison is undefined
12600  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(m_object != other.m_object))
12601  {
12602  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(212, "cannot compare iterators of different containers", m_object));
12603  }
12604 
12605  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12606 
12607  switch (m_object->m_type)
12608  {
12609  case value_t::object:
12610  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(213, "cannot compare order of object iterators", m_object));
12611 
12612  case value_t::array:
12613  return (m_it.array_iterator < other.m_it.array_iterator);
12614 
12615  case value_t::null:
12616  case value_t::string:
12617  case value_t::boolean:
12618  case value_t::number_integer:
12619  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12620  case value_t::number_float:
12621  case value_t::binary:
12622  case value_t::discarded:
12623  default:
12624  return (m_it.primitive_iterator < other.m_it.primitive_iterator);
12625  }
12626  }

12633  {
12634  return !other.operator < (*this);
12635  }

12642  {

12644  }

12651  {
12652  return !operator<(other);
12653  }

12659  iter_impl& operator+=(difference_type i)
12660  {

12662

12664  {
12665  case value_t::object:
12666  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators", m_object));
12667 
12668  case value_t::array:
12669  {
12670  std::advance(m_it.array_iterator, i);
12671  break;
12672  }
12673 
12674  case value_t::null:
12675  case value_t::string:
12676  case value_t::boolean:
12677  case value_t::number_integer:
12678  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12679  case value_t::number_float:
12680  case value_t::binary:
12681  case value_t::discarded:
12682  default:
12683  {
12684  m_it.primitive_iterator += i;
12685  break;
12686  }
12687  }
12688

12690  }

12697  {
12698  return operator+=(-i);
12699  }

12706  {

12708  result += i;
12709  return result;

12717  {

12719  result += i;
12720  return result;
12721  }

12728  {

12730  result -= i;
12731  return result;

12738  difference_type operator-(const iter_impl& other) const
12739  {
12740  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12741 
12742  switch (m_object->m_type)
12743  {
12744  case value_t::object:
12745  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(209, "cannot use offsets with object iterators", m_object));
12746 
12747  case value_t::array:
12748  return m_it.array_iterator - other.m_it.array_iterator;
12749 
12750  case value_t::null:
12751  case value_t::string:
12752  case value_t::boolean:
12753  case value_t::number_integer:
12754  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12755  case value_t::number_float:
12756  case value_t::binary:
12757  case value_t::discarded:
12758  default:
12759  return m_it.primitive_iterator - other.m_it.primitive_iterator;
12760  }
12761  }
12762 
12767  reference operator[](difference_type n) const
12768  {
12769  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12770 
12771  switch (m_object->m_type)
12772  {
12773  case value_t::object:
12774  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(208, "cannot use operator[] for object iterators", m_object));
12775 
12776  case value_t::array:
12777  return *std::next(m_it.array_iterator, n);
12778 
12779  case value_t::null:
12780  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value", m_object));
12781 
12782  case value_t::string:
12783  case value_t::boolean:
12784  case value_t::number_integer:
12785  case value_t::number_unsigned:
12786  case value_t::number_float:
12787  case value_t::binary:
12788  case value_t::discarded:
12789  default:
12790  {
12791  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_it.primitive_iterator.get_value() == -n))
12792  {
12793  return *m_object;
12794  }
12795 
12796  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(214, "cannot get value", m_object));
12797  }
12798  }
12799  }
12800 
12805  const typename object_t::key_type& key() const
12806  {
12807  JSON_ASSERT(m_object != nullptr);
12808 
12809  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(m_object->is_object()))
12810  {
12811  return m_it.object_iterator->first;
12812  }
12813 
12814  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(207, "cannot use key() for non-object iterators", m_object));
12815  }
12816 
12821  reference value() const
12822  {
12823  return operator*();
12824  }
12825 
12826  JSON_PRIVATE_UNLESS_TESTED:
12828  pointer m_object = nullptr;
12830  internal_iterator<typename std::remove_const<BasicJsonType>::type> m_it {};
12831 };

12870 template<typename Base>
12871 class json_reverse_iterator : public std::reverse_iterator<Base>
12872 {
12873  public:
12874  using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
12876  using base_iterator = std::reverse_iterator<Base>;
12878  using reference = typename Base::reference;
12879

12882  : base_iterator(it) {}
12883

12886

12889  {
12890  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator++(1));
12891  }
12892

12895  {
12896  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator++());
12897  }
12898 
12900  json_reverse_iterator operator--(int)& // NOLINT(cert-dcl21-cpp)
12901  {
12902  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator--(1));
12903  }
12904 
12906  json_reverse_iterator& operator--()
12907  {
12908  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator--());
12909  }
12910 
12912  json_reverse_iterator& operator+=(difference_type i)
12913  {
12914  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator&>(base_iterator::operator+=(i));
12915  }
12916

12919  {
12920  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator+(i));
12921  }
12922

12925  {
12926  return static_cast<json_reverse_iterator>(base_iterator::operator-(i));
12927  }
12928

12931  {
12932  return base_iterator(*this) - base_iterator(other);
12933  }
12934 
12936  reference operator[](difference_type n) const
12937  {
12938  return *(this->operator+(n));
12939  }
12940 
12942  auto key() const -> decltype(std::declval<Base>().key())
12943  {
12944  auto it = --this->base();
12945  return it.key();
12946  }
12947 
12949  reference value() const
12950  {
12951  auto it = --this->base();
12952  return it.operator * ();
12953  }
