12989 template<typename RefStringType>
12990 class json_pointer
12991 {
12992  // allow basic_json to access private members
12993  NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
12994  friend class basic_json;
12995 
12996  template<typename>
12997  friend class json_pointer;
12998 
12999  template<typename T>
13000  struct string_t_helper
13001  {
13002  using type = T;
13003  };
13004 
13005  NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL_DECLARATION
13006  struct string_t_helper<NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL>
13007  {
13008  using type = StringType;
13009  };
13010 
13011  public:
13012  // for backwards compatibility accept BasicJsonType
13013  using string_t = typename string_t_helper<RefStringType>::type;
13014 
13017  explicit json_pointer(const string_t& s = "")
13018  : reference_tokens(split(s))
13019  {}
13020 
13023  string_t to_string() const
13024  {
13025  return std::accumulate(reference_tokens.begin(), reference_tokens.end(),
13026  string_t{},
13027  [](const string_t& a, const string_t& b)
13028  {
13029  return detail::concat(a, '/', detail::escape(b));
13030  });
13031  }
13032 
13035  operator string_t() const
13036  {
13037  return to_string();
13038  }
13039 
13042  json_pointer& operator/=(const json_pointer& ptr)
13043  {
13044  reference_tokens.insert(reference_tokens.end(),
13045  ptr.reference_tokens.begin(),
13046  ptr.reference_tokens.end());
13047  return *this;
13048  }
13049 
13052  json_pointer& operator/=(string_t token)
13053  {
13054  push_back(std::move(token));
13055  return *this;
13056  }
13057 
13060  json_pointer& operator/=(std::size_t array_idx)
13061  {
13062  return *this /= std::to_string(array_idx);
13063  }
13064 
13067  friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& lhs,
13068  const json_pointer& rhs)
13069  {
13070  return json_pointer(lhs) /= rhs;
13071  }
13072 
13075  friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& lhs, string_t token) // NOLINT(performance-unnecessary-value-param)
13076  {
13077  return json_pointer(lhs) /= std::move(token);
13078  }
13079 
13082  friend json_pointer operator/(const json_pointer& lhs, std::size_t array_idx)
13083  {
13084  return json_pointer(lhs) /= array_idx;
13085  }
13086 
13089  json_pointer parent_pointer() const
13090  {
13091  if (empty())
13092  {
13093  return *this;
13094  }
13095 
13096  json_pointer res = *this;
13097  res.pop_back();
13098  return res;
13099  }
13100 
13103  void pop_back()
13104  {
13105  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(empty()))
13106  {
13107  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent", nullptr));
13108  }
13109 
13110  reference_tokens.pop_back();
13111  }
13112 
13115  const string_t& back() const
13116  {
13117  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(empty()))
13118  {
13119  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent", nullptr));
13120  }
13121 
13122  return reference_tokens.back();
13123  }
13124 
13127  void push_back(const string_t& token)
13128  {
13129  reference_tokens.push_back(token);
13130  }
13131 
13134  void push_back(string_t&& token)
13135  {
13136  reference_tokens.push_back(std::move(token));
13137  }
13138 
13141  bool empty() const noexcept
13142  {
13143  return reference_tokens.empty();
13144  }
13145 
13146  private:
13157  template<typename BasicJsonType>
13158  static typename BasicJsonType::size_type array_index(const string_t& s)
13159  {
13160  using size_type = typename BasicJsonType::size_type;
13161 
13162  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
13163  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(s.size() > 1 && s[0] == '0'))
13164  {
13165  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(106, 0, detail::concat("array index '", s, "' must not begin with '0'"), nullptr));
13166  }
13167 
13168  // error condition (cf. RFC 6901, Sect. 4)
13169  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(s.size() > 1 && !(s[0] >= '1' && s[0] <= '9')))
13170  {
13171  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(109, 0, detail::concat("array index '", s, "' is not a number"), nullptr));
13172  }
13173 
13174  const char* p = s.c_str();
13175  char* p_end = nullptr;
13176  errno = 0; // strtoull doesn't reset errno
13177  unsigned long long res = std::strtoull(p, &p_end, 10); // NOLINT(runtime/int)
13178  if (p == p_end // invalid input or empty string
13179  || errno == ERANGE // out of range
13180  || JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(static_cast<std::size_t>(p_end - p) != s.size())) // incomplete read
13181  {
13182  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, detail::concat("unresolved reference token '", s, "'"), nullptr));
13183  }
13184 
13185  // only triggered on special platforms (like 32bit), see also
13186  // https://github.com/nlohmann/json/pull/2203
13187  if (res >= static_cast<unsigned long long>((std::numeric_limits<size_type>::max)())) // NOLINT(runtime/int)
13188  {
13189  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(410, detail::concat("array index ", s, " exceeds size_type"), nullptr)); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
13190  }
13191 
13192  return static_cast<size_type>(res);
13193  }
13194 
13195  JSON_PRIVATE_UNLESS_TESTED:
13196  json_pointer top() const
13197  {
13198  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(empty()))
13199  {
13200  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(405, "JSON pointer has no parent", nullptr));
13201  }
13202 
13203  json_pointer result = *this;
13204  result.reference_tokens = {reference_tokens[0]};
13205  return result;
13206  }
13207 
13208  private:
13217  template<typename BasicJsonType>
13218  BasicJsonType& get_and_create(BasicJsonType& j) const
13219  {
13220  auto* result = &j;
13221 
13222  // in case no reference tokens exist, return a reference to the JSON value
13223  // j which will be overwritten by a primitive value
13224  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13225  {
13226  switch (result->type())
13227  {
13228  case detail::value_t::null:
13229  {
13230  if (reference_token == "0")
13231  {
13232  // start a new array if reference token is 0
13233  result = &result->operator[](0);
13234  }
13235  else
13236  {
13237  // start a new object otherwise
13238  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
13239  }
13240  break;
13241  }
13242 
13243  case detail::value_t::object:
13244  {
13245  // create an entry in the object
13246  result = &result->operator[](reference_token);
13247  break;
13248  }
13249 
13250  case detail::value_t::array:
13251  {
13252  // create an entry in the array
13253  result = &result->operator[](array_index<BasicJsonType>(reference_token));
13254  break;
13255  }
13256 
13257  /*
13258  The following code is only reached if there exists a reference
13259  token _and_ the current value is primitive. In this case, we have
13260  an error situation, because primitive values may only occur as
13261  single value; that is, with an empty list of reference tokens.
13262  */
13263  case detail::value_t::string:
13264  case detail::value_t::boolean:
13265  case detail::value_t::number_integer:
13266  case detail::value_t::number_unsigned:
13267  case detail::value_t::number_float:
13268  case detail::value_t::binary:
13269  case detail::value_t::discarded:
13270  default:
13271  JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(313, "invalid value to unflatten", &j));
13272  }
13273  }
13274 
13275  return *result;
13276  }
13277 
13297  template<typename BasicJsonType>
13298  BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
13299  {
13300  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13301  {
13302  // convert null values to arrays or objects before continuing
13303  if (ptr->is_null())
13304  {
13305  // check if reference token is a number
13306  const bool nums =
13307  std::all_of(reference_token.begin(), reference_token.end(),
13308  [](const unsigned char x)
13309  {
13310  return std::isdigit(x);
13311  });
13312 
13313  // change value to array for numbers or "-" or to object otherwise
13314  *ptr = (nums || reference_token == "-")
13315  ? detail::value_t::array
13316  : detail::value_t::object;
13317  }
13318 
13319  switch (ptr->type())
13320  {
13321  case detail::value_t::object:
13322  {
13323  // use unchecked object access
13324  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
13325  break;
13326  }
13327 
13328  case detail::value_t::array:
13329  {
13330  if (reference_token == "-")
13331  {
13332  // explicitly treat "-" as index beyond the end
13333  ptr = &ptr->operator[](ptr->m_value.array->size());
13334  }
13335  else
13336  {
13337  // convert array index to number; unchecked access
13338  ptr = &ptr->operator[](array_index<BasicJsonType>(reference_token));
13339  }
13340  break;
13341  }
13342 
13343  case detail::value_t::null:
13344  case detail::value_t::string:
13345  case detail::value_t::boolean:
13346  case detail::value_t::number_integer:
13347  case detail::value_t::number_unsigned:
13348  case detail::value_t::number_float:
13349  case detail::value_t::binary:
13350  case detail::value_t::discarded:
13351  default:
13352  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, detail::concat("unresolved reference token '", reference_token, "'"), ptr));
13353  }
13354  }
13355 
13356  return *ptr;
13357  }
13358 
13365  template<typename BasicJsonType>
13366  BasicJsonType& get_checked(BasicJsonType* ptr) const
13367  {
13368  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13369  {
13370  switch (ptr->type())
13371  {
13372  case detail::value_t::object:
13373  {
13374  // note: at performs range check
13375  ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
13376  break;
13377  }
13378 
13379  case detail::value_t::array:
13380  {
13381  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
13382  {
13383  // "-" always fails the range check
13384  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402, detail::concat(
13385  "array index '-' (", std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()),
13386  ") is out of range"), ptr));
13387  }
13388 
13389  // note: at performs range check
13390  ptr = &ptr->at(array_index<BasicJsonType>(reference_token));
13391  break;
13392  }
13393 
13394  case detail::value_t::null:
13395  case detail::value_t::string:
13396  case detail::value_t::boolean:
13397  case detail::value_t::number_integer:
13398  case detail::value_t::number_unsigned:
13399  case detail::value_t::number_float:
13400  case detail::value_t::binary:
13401  case detail::value_t::discarded:
13402  default:
13403  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, detail::concat("unresolved reference token '", reference_token, "'"), ptr));
13404  }
13405  }
13406 
13407  return *ptr;
13408  }
13409 
13423  template<typename BasicJsonType>
13424  const BasicJsonType& get_unchecked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
13425  {
13426  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13427  {
13428  switch (ptr->type())
13429  {
13430  case detail::value_t::object:
13431  {
13432  // use unchecked object access
13433  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
13434  break;
13435  }
13436 
13437  case detail::value_t::array:
13438  {
13439  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
13440  {
13441  // "-" cannot be used for const access
13442  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402, detail::concat("array index '-' (", std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()), ") is out of range"), ptr));
13443  }
13444 
13445  // use unchecked array access
13446  ptr = &ptr->operator[](array_index<BasicJsonType>(reference_token));
13447  break;
13448  }
13449 
13450  case detail::value_t::null:
13451  case detail::value_t::string:
13452  case detail::value_t::boolean:
13453  case detail::value_t::number_integer:
13454  case detail::value_t::number_unsigned:
13455  case detail::value_t::number_float:
13456  case detail::value_t::binary:
13457  case detail::value_t::discarded:
13458  default:
13459  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, detail::concat("unresolved reference token '", reference_token, "'"), ptr));
13460  }
13461  }
13462 
13463  return *ptr;
13464  }
13465 
13472  template<typename BasicJsonType>
13473  const BasicJsonType& get_checked(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
13474  {
13475  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13476  {
13477  switch (ptr->type())
13478  {
13479  case detail::value_t::object:
13480  {
13481  // note: at performs range check
13482  ptr = &ptr->at(reference_token);
13483  break;
13484  }
13485 
13486  case detail::value_t::array:
13487  {
13488  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
13489  {
13490  // "-" always fails the range check
13491  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(402, detail::concat(
13492  "array index '-' (", std::to_string(ptr->m_value.array->size()),
13493  ") is out of range"), ptr));
13494  }
13495 
13496  // note: at performs range check
13497  ptr = &ptr->at(array_index<BasicJsonType>(reference_token));
13498  break;
13499  }
13500 
13501  case detail::value_t::null:
13502  case detail::value_t::string:
13503  case detail::value_t::boolean:
13504  case detail::value_t::number_integer:
13505  case detail::value_t::number_unsigned:
13506  case detail::value_t::number_float:
13507  case detail::value_t::binary:
13508  case detail::value_t::discarded:
13509  default:
13510  JSON_THROW(detail::out_of_range::create(404, detail::concat("unresolved reference token '", reference_token, "'"), ptr));
13511  }
13512  }
13513 
13514  return *ptr;
13515  }
13516 
13521  template<typename BasicJsonType>
13522  bool contains(const BasicJsonType* ptr) const
13523  {
13524  for (const auto& reference_token : reference_tokens)
13525  {
13526  switch (ptr->type())
13527  {
13528  case detail::value_t::object:
13529  {
13530  if (!ptr->contains(reference_token))
13531  {
13532  // we did not find the key in the object
13533  return false;
13534  }
13535 
13536  ptr = &ptr->operator[](reference_token);
13537  break;
13538  }
13539 
13540  case detail::value_t::array:
13541  {
13542  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token == "-"))
13543  {
13544  // "-" always fails the range check
13545  return false;
13546  }
13547  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() == 1 && !("0" <= reference_token && reference_token <= "9")))
13548  {
13549  // invalid char
13550  return false;
13551  }
13552  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_token.size() > 1))
13553  {
13554  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!('1' <= reference_token[0] && reference_token[0] <= '9')))
13555  {
13556  // first char should be between '1' and '9'
13557  return false;
13558  }
13559  for (std::size_t i = 1; i < reference_token.size(); i++)
13560  {
13561  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!('0' <= reference_token[i] && reference_token[i] <= '9')))
13562  {
13563  // other char should be between '0' and '9'
13564  return false;
13565  }
13566  }
13567  }
13568 
13569  const auto idx = array_index<BasicJsonType>(reference_token);
13570  if (idx >= ptr->size())
13571  {
13572  // index out of range
13573  return false;
13574  }
13575 
13576  ptr = &ptr->operator[](idx);
13577  break;
13578  }
13579 
13580  case detail::value_t::null:
13581  case detail::value_t::string:
13582  case detail::value_t::boolean:
13583  case detail::value_t::number_integer:
13584  case detail::value_t::number_unsigned:
13585  case detail::value_t::number_float:
13586  case detail::value_t::binary:
13587  case detail::value_t::discarded:
13588  default:
13589  {
13590  // we do not expect primitive values if there is still a
13591  // reference token to process
13592  return false;
13593  }
13594  }
13595  }
13596 
13597  // no reference token left means we found a primitive value
13598  return true;
13599  }
13600 
13610  static std::vector<string_t> split(const string_t& reference_string)
13611  {
13612  std::vector<string_t> result;
13613 
13614  // special case: empty reference string -> no reference tokens
13615  if (reference_string.empty())
13616  {
13617  return result;
13618  }
13619 
13620  // check if nonempty reference string begins with slash
13621  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(reference_string[0] != '/'))
13622  {
13623  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(107, 1, detail::concat("JSON pointer must be empty or begin with '/' - was: '", reference_string, "'"), nullptr));
13624  }
13625 
13626  // extract the reference tokens:
13627  // - slash: position of the last read slash (or end of string)
13628  // - start: position after the previous slash
13629  for (
13630  // search for the first slash after the first character
13631  std::size_t slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', 1),
13632  // set the beginning of the first reference token
13633  start = 1;
13634  // we can stop if start == 0 (if slash == string_t::npos)
13635  start != 0;
13636  // set the beginning of the next reference token
13637  // (will eventually be 0 if slash == string_t::npos)
13638  start = (slash == string_t::npos) ? 0 : slash + 1,
13639  // find next slash
13640  slash = reference_string.find_first_of('/', start))
13641  {
13642  // use the text between the beginning of the reference token
13643  // (start) and the last slash (slash).
13644  auto reference_token = reference_string.substr(start, slash - start);
13645 
13646  // check reference tokens are properly escaped
13647  for (std::size_t pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~');
13648  pos != string_t::npos;
13649  pos = reference_token.find_first_of('~', pos + 1))
13650  {
13651  JSON_ASSERT(reference_token[pos] == '~');
13652 
13653  // ~ must be followed by 0 or 1
13654  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(pos == reference_token.size() - 1 ||
13655  (reference_token[pos + 1] != '0' &&
13656  reference_token[pos + 1] != '1')))
13657  {
13658  JSON_THROW(detail::parse_error::create(108, 0, "escape character '~' must be followed with '0' or '1'", nullptr));
13659  }
13660  }
13661 
13662  // finally, store the reference token
13663  detail::unescape(reference_token);
13664  result.push_back(reference_token);
13665  }
13666 
13667  return result;
13668  }
13669 
13670  private:
13678  template<typename BasicJsonType>
13679  static void flatten(const string_t& reference_string,
13680  const BasicJsonType& value,
13681  BasicJsonType& result)
13682  {
13683  switch (value.type())
13684  {
13685  case detail::value_t::array:
13686  {
13687  if (value.m_value.array->empty())
13688  {
13689  // flatten empty array as null
13690  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
13691  }
13692  else
13693  {
13694  // iterate array and use index as reference string
13695  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < value.m_value.array->size(); ++i)
13696  {
13697  flatten(detail::concat(reference_string, '/', std::to_string(i)),
13698  value.m_value.array->operator[](i), result);
13699  }
13700  }
13701  break;
13702  }
13703 
13704  case detail::value_t::object:
13705  {
13706  if (value.m_value.object->empty())
13707  {
13708  // flatten empty object as null
13709  result[reference_string] = nullptr;
13710  }
13711  else
13712  {
13713  // iterate object and use keys as reference string
13714  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
13715  {
13716  flatten(detail::concat(reference_string, '/', detail::escape(element.first)), element.second, result);
13717  }
13718  }
13719  break;
13720  }
13721 
13722  case detail::value_t::null:
13723  case detail::value_t::string:
13724  case detail::value_t::boolean:
13725  case detail::value_t::number_integer:
13726  case detail::value_t::number_unsigned:
13727  case detail::value_t::number_float:
13728  case detail::value_t::binary:
13729  case detail::value_t::discarded:
13730  default:
13731  {
13732  // add primitive value with its reference string
13733  result[reference_string] = value;
13734  break;
13735  }
13736  }
13737  }
13738 
13749  template<typename BasicJsonType>
13750  static BasicJsonType
13751  unflatten(const BasicJsonType& value)
13752  {
13753  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!value.is_object()))
13754  {
13755  JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(314, "only objects can be unflattened", &value));
13756  }
13757 
13758  BasicJsonType result;
13759 
13760  // iterate the JSON object values
13761  for (const auto& element : *value.m_value.object)
13762  {
13763  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!element.second.is_primitive()))
13764  {
13765  JSON_THROW(detail::type_error::create(315, "values in object must be primitive", &element.second));
13766  }
13767 
13768  // assign value to reference pointed to by JSON pointer; Note that if
13769  // the JSON pointer is "" (i.e., points to the whole value), function
13770  // get_and_create returns a reference to result itself. An assignment
13771  // will then create a primitive value.
13772  json_pointer(element.first).get_and_create(result) = element.second;
13773  }
13774 
13775  return result;
13776  }
13777 
13778  // can't use conversion operator because of ambiguity
13779  json_pointer<string_t> convert() const&
13780  {
13781  json_pointer<string_t> result;
13782  result.reference_tokens = reference_tokens;
13783  return result;
13784  }
13785 
13786  json_pointer<string_t> convert()&&
13787  {
13788  json_pointer<string_t> result;
13789  result.reference_tokens = std::move(reference_tokens);
13790  return result;
13791  }
13792 
13804  template<typename RefStringTypeLhs, typename RefStringTypeRhs>
13805  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(readability-redundant-declaration)
13806  friend bool operator==(json_pointer<RefStringTypeLhs> const& lhs,
13807  json_pointer<RefStringTypeRhs> const& rhs) noexcept;
13808 
13820  template<typename RefStringTypeLhs, typename RefStringTypeRhs>
13821  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(readability-redundant-declaration)
13822  friend bool operator!=(json_pointer<RefStringTypeLhs> const& lhs,
13823  json_pointer<RefStringTypeRhs> const& rhs) noexcept;
13824 
13826  std::vector<string_t> reference_tokens;
13827 };
13828 
13829 // functions cannot be defined inside class due to ODR violations
13830 template<typename RefStringTypeLhs, typename RefStringTypeRhs>
13831 inline bool operator==(json_pointer<RefStringTypeLhs> const& lhs,
13832  json_pointer<RefStringTypeRhs> const& rhs) noexcept
13833 {
13834  return lhs.reference_tokens == rhs.reference_tokens;
13835 }
13836 
13837 template<typename RefStringTypeLhs, typename RefStringTypeRhs>
13838 inline bool operator!=(json_pointer<RefStringTypeLhs> const& lhs,
13839  json_pointer<RefStringTypeRhs> const& rhs) noexcept
13840 {
13841  return !(lhs == rhs);
13842 }

13855 {
13856 namespace detail
13857 {
13858 template<typename BasicJsonType>
13859 class json_ref
13860 {
13861  public:
13862  using value_type = BasicJsonType;
13863 
13864  json_ref(value_type&& value)
13865  : owned_value(std::move(value))
13866  {}
13867 
13868  json_ref(const value_type& value)
13869  : value_ref(&value)
13870  {}
13871 
13872  json_ref(std::initializer_list<json_ref> init)
13873  : owned_value(init)
13874  {}
13875 
13876  template <
13877  class... Args,
13878  enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<value_type, Args...>::value, int> = 0 >
13879  json_ref(Args && ... args)
13880  : owned_value(std::forward<Args>(args)...)
13881  {}
13882 
13883  // class should be movable only
13884  json_ref(json_ref&&) noexcept = default;
13885  json_ref(const json_ref&) = delete;
13886  json_ref& operator=(const json_ref&) = delete;
13887  json_ref& operator=(json_ref&&) = delete;
13888  ~json_ref() = default;
13889 
13890  value_type moved_or_copied() const
13891  {
13892  if (value_ref == nullptr)
13893  {
13894  return std::move(owned_value);
13895  }
13896  return *value_ref;
13897  }
13898 
13899  value_type const& operator*() const
13900  {
13901  return value_ref ? *value_ref : owned_value;
13902  }
13903 
13904  value_type const* operator->() const
13905  {
13906  return &** this;
13907  }
13908 
13909  private:
13910  mutable value_type owned_value = nullptr;
13911  value_type const* value_ref = nullptr;
13912 };

13967 template<typename CharType> struct output_adapter_protocol
13968 {
13969  virtual void write_character(CharType c) = 0;
13970  virtual void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) = 0;
13971  virtual ~output_adapter_protocol() = default;
13972 
13973  output_adapter_protocol() = default;
13974  output_adapter_protocol(const output_adapter_protocol&) = default;
13975  output_adapter_protocol(output_adapter_protocol&&) noexcept = default;
13976  output_adapter_protocol& operator=(const output_adapter_protocol&) = default;
13977  output_adapter_protocol& operator=(output_adapter_protocol&&) noexcept = default;
13978 };

13985 template<typename CharType, typename AllocatorType = std::allocator<CharType>>
13986 class output_vector_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
13987 {
13988  public:
13989  explicit output_vector_adapter(std::vector<CharType, AllocatorType>& vec) noexcept
13990  : v(vec)
13991  {}
13992 
13993  void write_character(CharType c) override
13994  {
13995  v.push_back(c);
13996  }
13997 
13998  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
13999  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
14000  {
14001  std::copy(s, s + length, std::back_inserter(v));
14002  }
14003 
14004  private:
14005  std::vector<CharType, AllocatorType>& v;
14006 };

14008 #ifndef JSON_NO_IO
14010 template<typename CharType>
14011 class output_stream_adapter : public output_adapter_protocol<CharType>
14012 {
14013  public:
14014  explicit output_stream_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s) noexcept
14015  : stream(s)
14016  {}
14017 
14018  void write_character(CharType c) override
14019  {
14020  stream.put(c);
14021  }
14022 
14023  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
14024  void write_characters(const CharType* s, std::size_t length) override
14025  {
14026  stream.write(s, static_cast<std::streamsize>(length));
14027  }
14028 
14029  private:
14030  std::basic_ostream<CharType>& stream;
14031 };
14032 #endif // JSON_NO_IO

14058 template<typename CharType, typename StringType = std::basic_string<CharType>>
14059 class output_adapter
14060 {
14061  public:
14062  template<typename AllocatorType = std::allocator<CharType>>
14063  output_adapter(std::vector<CharType, AllocatorType>& vec)
14064  : oa(std::make_shared<output_vector_adapter<CharType, AllocatorType>>(vec)) {}
14065 
14066 #ifndef JSON_NO_IO
14067  output_adapter(std::basic_ostream<CharType>& s)
14068  : oa(std::make_shared<output_stream_adapter<CharType>>(s)) {}
14069 #endif // JSON_NO_IO
14070 
14071  output_adapter(StringType& s)
14072  : oa(std::make_shared<output_string_adapter<CharType, StringType>>(s)) {}
14073 
14074  operator output_adapter_t<CharType>()
14075  {
14076  return oa;
14077  }
14078 
14079  private:
14080  output_adapter_t<CharType> oa = nullptr;
14081 };
14082 } // namespace detail
14083 } // namespace nlohmann
14084 
14085 // #include <nlohmann/detail/string_concat.hpp>
14086 
14087 
14088 namespace nlohmann
14089 {
14090 namespace detail
14091 {
14093 // binary writer //
14095 
14099 template<typename BasicJsonType, typename CharType>
14100 class binary_writer
14101 {
14102  using string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
14103  using binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
14104  using number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
14105 
14106  public:
14112  explicit binary_writer(output_adapter_t<CharType> adapter) : oa(std::move(adapter))
14113  {
14114  JSON_ASSERT(oa);
14115  }
14116 
14121  void write_bson(const BasicJsonType& j)
14122  {
14123  switch (j.type())
14124  {
14125  case value_t::object:
14126  {
14127  write_bson_object(*j.m_value.object);
14128  break;
14129  }
14130 
14131  case value_t::null:
14132  case value_t::array:
14133  case value_t::string:
14134  case value_t::boolean:
14135  case value_t::number_integer:
14136  case value_t::number_unsigned:
14137  case value_t::number_float:
14138  case value_t::binary:
14139  case value_t::discarded:
14140  default:
14141  {
14142  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(317, concat("to serialize to BSON, top-level type must be object, but is ", j.type_name()), &j));
14143  }
14144  }
14145  }
14146 
14150  void write_cbor(const BasicJsonType& j)
14151  {
14152  switch (j.type())
14153  {
14154  case value_t::null:
14155  {
14156  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xF6));
14157  break;
14158  }
14159 
14160  case value_t::boolean:
14161  {
14162  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
14163  ? to_char_type(0xF5)
14164  : to_char_type(0xF4));
14165  break;
14166  }
14167 
14168  case value_t::number_integer:
14169  {
14170  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
14171  {
14172  // CBOR does not differentiate between positive signed
14173  // integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used the
14174  // code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
14175  if (j.m_value.number_integer <= 0x17)
14176  {
14177  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14178  }
14179  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14180  {
14181  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
14182  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14183  }
14184  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14185  {
14186  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
14187  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14188  }
14189  else if (j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14190  {
14191  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
14192  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14193  }
14194  else
14195  {
14196  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
14197  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14198  }
14199  }
14200  else
14201  {
14202  // The conversions below encode the sign in the first
14203  // byte, and the value is converted to a positive number.
14204  const auto positive_number = -1 - j.m_value.number_integer;
14205  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -24)
14206  {
14207  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x20 + positive_number));
14208  }
14209  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14210  {
14211  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x38));
14212  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(positive_number));
14213  }
14214  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14215  {
14216  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x39));
14217  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(positive_number));
14218  }
14219  else if (positive_number <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14220  {
14221  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3A));
14222  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(positive_number));
14223  }
14224  else
14225  {
14226  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x3B));
14227  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(positive_number));
14228  }
14229  }
14230  break;
14231  }
14232 
14233  case value_t::number_unsigned:
14234  {
14235  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= 0x17)
14236  {
14237  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
14238  }
14239  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14240  {
14241  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x18));
14242  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
14243  }
14244  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14245  {
14246  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x19));
14247  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
14248  }
14249  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14250  {
14251  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1A));
14252  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
14253  }
14254  else
14255  {
14256  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x1B));
14257  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned));
14258  }
14259  break;
14260  }
14261 
14262  case value_t::number_float:
14263  {
14264  if (std::isnan(j.m_value.number_float))
14265  {
14266  // NaN is 0xf97e00 in CBOR
14267  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xF9));
14268  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7E));
14269  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
14270  }
14271  else if (std::isinf(j.m_value.number_float))
14272  {
14273  // Infinity is 0xf97c00, -Infinity is 0xf9fc00
14274  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xf9));
14275  oa->write_character(j.m_value.number_float > 0 ? to_char_type(0x7C) : to_char_type(0xFC));
14276  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
14277  }
14278  else
14279  {
14280  write_compact_float(j.m_value.number_float, detail::input_format_t::cbor);
14281  }
14282  break;
14283  }
14284 
14285  case value_t::string:
14286  {
14287  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
14288  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
14289  if (N <= 0x17)
14290  {
14291  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x60 + N));
14292  }
14293  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14294  {
14295  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x78));
14296  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
14297  }
14298  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14299  {
14300  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x79));
14301  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
14302  }
14303  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14304  {
14305  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7A));
14306  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
14307  }
14308  // LCOV_EXCL_START
14309  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
14310  {
14311  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x7B));
14312  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
14313  }
14314  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
14315 
14316  // step 2: write the string
14317  oa->write_characters(
14318  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
14319  j.m_value.string->size());
14320  break;
14321  }
14322 
14323  case value_t::array:
14324  {
14325  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
14326  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
14327  if (N <= 0x17)
14328  {
14329  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 + N));
14330  }
14331  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14332  {
14333  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x98));
14334  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
14335  }
14336  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14337  {
14338  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x99));
14339  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
14340  }
14341  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14342  {
14343  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9A));
14344  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
14345  }
14346  // LCOV_EXCL_START
14347  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
14348  {
14349  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x9B));
14350  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
14351  }
14352  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
14353 
14354  // step 2: write each element
14355  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
14356  {
14357  write_cbor(el);
14358  }
14359  break;
14360  }
14361 
14362  case value_t::binary:
14363  {
14364  if (j.m_value.binary->has_subtype())
14365  {
14366  if (j.m_value.binary->subtype() <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14367  {
14368  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xd8));
14369  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.binary->subtype()));
14370  }
14371  else if (j.m_value.binary->subtype() <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14372  {
14373  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xd9));
14374  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.binary->subtype()));
14375  }
14376  else if (j.m_value.binary->subtype() <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14377  {
14378  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xda));
14379  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.binary->subtype()));
14380  }
14381  else if (j.m_value.binary->subtype() <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
14382  {
14383  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xdb));
14384  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.binary->subtype()));
14385  }
14386  }
14387 
14388  // step 1: write control byte and the binary array size
14389  const auto N = j.m_value.binary->size();
14390  if (N <= 0x17)
14391  {
14392  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x40 + N));
14393  }
14394  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14395  {
14396  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x58));
14397  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
14398  }
14399  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14400  {
14401  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x59));
14402  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
14403  }
14404  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14405  {
14406  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x5A));
14407  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
14408  }
14409  // LCOV_EXCL_START
14410  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
14411  {
14412  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x5B));
14413  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
14414  }
14415  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
14416 
14417  // step 2: write each element
14418  oa->write_characters(
14419  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.binary->data()),
14420  N);
14421 
14422  break;
14423  }
14424 
14425  case value_t::object:
14426  {
14427  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
14428  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
14429  if (N <= 0x17)
14430  {
14431  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 + N));
14432  }
14433  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14434  {
14435  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB8));
14436  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
14437  }
14438  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14439  {
14440  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xB9));
14441  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
14442  }
14443  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14444  {
14445  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBA));
14446  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
14447  }
14448  // LCOV_EXCL_START
14449  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
14450  {
14451  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xBB));
14452  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(N));
14453  }
14454  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
14455 
14456  // step 2: write each element
14457  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
14458  {
14459  write_cbor(el.first);
14460  write_cbor(el.second);
14461  }
14462  break;
14463  }
14464 
14465  case value_t::discarded:
14466  default:
14467  break;
14468  }
14469  }
14470 
14474  void write_msgpack(const BasicJsonType& j)
14475  {
14476  switch (j.type())
14477  {
14478  case value_t::null: // nil
14479  {
14480  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xC0));
14481  break;
14482  }
14483 
14484  case value_t::boolean: // true and false
14485  {
14486  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
14487  ? to_char_type(0xC3)
14488  : to_char_type(0xC2));
14489  break;
14490  }
14491 
14492  case value_t::number_integer:
14493  {
14494  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= 0)
14495  {
14496  // MessagePack does not differentiate between positive
14497  // signed integers and unsigned integers. Therefore, we used
14498  // the code from the value_t::number_unsigned case here.
14499  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
14500  {
14501  // positive fixnum
14502  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14503  }
14504  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14505  {
14506  // uint 8
14507  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
14508  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14509  }
14510  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14511  {
14512  // uint 16
14513  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
14514  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14515  }
14516  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14517  {
14518  // uint 32
14519  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
14520  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14521  }
14522  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
14523  {
14524  // uint 64
14525  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
14526  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14527  }
14528  }
14529  else
14530  {
14531  if (j.m_value.number_integer >= -32)
14532  {
14533  // negative fixnum
14534  write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14535  }
14536  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::min)() &&
14537  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int8_t>::max)())
14538  {
14539  // int 8
14540  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD0));
14541  write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14542  }
14543  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::min)() &&
14544  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int16_t>::max)())
14545  {
14546  // int 16
14547  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD1));
14548  write_number(static_cast<std::int16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14549  }
14550  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() &&
14551  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
14552  {
14553  // int 32
14554  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD2));
14555  write_number(static_cast<std::int32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14556  }
14557  else if (j.m_value.number_integer >= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::min)() &&
14558  j.m_value.number_integer <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)())
14559  {
14560  // int 64
14561  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD3));
14562  write_number(static_cast<std::int64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14563  }
14564  }
14565  break;
14566  }
14567 
14568  case value_t::number_unsigned:
14569  {
14570  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned < 128)
14571  {
14572  // positive fixnum
14573  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14574  }
14575  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14576  {
14577  // uint 8
14578  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCC));
14579  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14580  }
14581  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14582  {
14583  // uint 16
14584  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCD));
14585  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14586  }
14587  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14588  {
14589  // uint 32
14590  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCE));
14591  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14592  }
14593  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint64_t>::max)())
14594  {
14595  // uint 64
14596  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xCF));
14597  write_number(static_cast<std::uint64_t>(j.m_value.number_integer));
14598  }
14599  break;
14600  }
14601 
14602  case value_t::number_float:
14603  {
14604  write_compact_float(j.m_value.number_float, detail::input_format_t::msgpack);
14605  break;
14606  }
14607 
14608  case value_t::string:
14609  {
14610  // step 1: write control byte and the string length
14611  const auto N = j.m_value.string->size();
14612  if (N <= 31)
14613  {
14614  // fixstr
14615  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0xA0 | N));
14616  }
14617  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14618  {
14619  // str 8
14620  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xD9));
14621  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
14622  }
14623  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14624  {
14625  // str 16
14626  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDA));
14627  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
14628  }
14629  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14630  {
14631  // str 32
14632  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDB));
14633  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
14634  }
14635 
14636  // step 2: write the string
14637  oa->write_characters(
14638  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
14639  j.m_value.string->size());
14640  break;
14641  }
14642 
14643  case value_t::array:
14644  {
14645  // step 1: write control byte and the array size
14646  const auto N = j.m_value.array->size();
14647  if (N <= 15)
14648  {
14649  // fixarray
14650  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x90 | N));
14651  }
14652  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14653  {
14654  // array 16
14655  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDC));
14656  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
14657  }
14658  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14659  {
14660  // array 32
14661  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDD));
14662  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
14663  }
14664 
14665  // step 2: write each element
14666  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
14667  {
14668  write_msgpack(el);
14669  }
14670  break;
14671  }
14672 
14673  case value_t::binary:
14674  {
14675  // step 0: determine if the binary type has a set subtype to
14676  // determine whether or not to use the ext or fixext types
14677  const bool use_ext = j.m_value.binary->has_subtype();
14678 
14679  // step 1: write control byte and the byte string length
14680  const auto N = j.m_value.binary->size();
14681  if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint8_t>::max)())
14682  {
14683  std::uint8_t output_type{};
14684  bool fixed = true;
14685  if (use_ext)
14686  {
14687  switch (N)
14688  {
14689  case 1:
14690  output_type = 0xD4; // fixext 1
14691  break;
14692  case 2:
14693  output_type = 0xD5; // fixext 2
14694  break;
14695  case 4:
14696  output_type = 0xD6; // fixext 4
14697  break;
14698  case 8:
14699  output_type = 0xD7; // fixext 8
14700  break;
14701  case 16:
14702  output_type = 0xD8; // fixext 16
14703  break;
14704  default:
14705  output_type = 0xC7; // ext 8
14706  fixed = false;
14707  break;
14708  }
14709 
14710  }
14711  else
14712  {
14713  output_type = 0xC4; // bin 8
14714  fixed = false;
14715  }
14716 
14717  oa->write_character(to_char_type(output_type));
14718  if (!fixed)
14719  {
14720  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(N));
14721  }
14722  }
14723  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14724  {
14725  std::uint8_t output_type = use_ext
14726  ? 0xC8 // ext 16
14727  : 0xC5; // bin 16
14728 
14729  oa->write_character(to_char_type(output_type));
14730  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
14731  }
14732  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14733  {
14734  std::uint8_t output_type = use_ext
14735  ? 0xC9 // ext 32
14736  : 0xC6; // bin 32
14737 
14738  oa->write_character(to_char_type(output_type));
14739  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
14740  }
14741 
14742  // step 1.5: if this is an ext type, write the subtype
14743  if (use_ext)
14744  {
14745  write_number(static_cast<std::int8_t>(j.m_value.binary->subtype()));
14746  }
14747 
14748  // step 2: write the byte string
14749  oa->write_characters(
14750  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.binary->data()),
14751  N);
14752 
14753  break;
14754  }
14755 
14756  case value_t::object:
14757  {
14758  // step 1: write control byte and the object size
14759  const auto N = j.m_value.object->size();
14760  if (N <= 15)
14761  {
14762  // fixmap
14763  write_number(static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x80 | (N & 0xF)));
14764  }
14765  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint16_t>::max)())
14766  {
14767  // map 16
14768  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDE));
14769  write_number(static_cast<std::uint16_t>(N));
14770  }
14771  else if (N <= (std::numeric_limits<std::uint32_t>::max)())
14772  {
14773  // map 32
14774  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0xDF));
14775  write_number(static_cast<std::uint32_t>(N));
14776  }
14777 
14778  // step 2: write each element
14779  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
14780  {
14781  write_msgpack(el.first);
14782  write_msgpack(el.second);
14783  }
14784  break;
14785  }
14786 
14787  case value_t::discarded:
14788  default:
14789  break;
14790  }
14791  }
14792 
14800  void write_ubjson(const BasicJsonType& j, const bool use_count,
14801  const bool use_type, const bool add_prefix = true,
14802  const bool use_bjdata = false)
14803  {
14804  switch (j.type())
14805  {
14806  case value_t::null:
14807  {
14808  if (add_prefix)
14809  {
14810  oa->write_character(to_char_type('Z'));
14811  }
14812  break;
14813  }
14814 
14815  case value_t::boolean:
14816  {
14817  if (add_prefix)
14818  {
14819  oa->write_character(j.m_value.boolean
14820  ? to_char_type('T')
14821  : to_char_type('F'));
14822  }
14823  break;
14824  }
14825 
14826  case value_t::number_integer:
14827  {
14828  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_integer, add_prefix, use_bjdata);
14829  break;
14830  }
14831 
14832  case value_t::number_unsigned:
14833  {
14834  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_unsigned, add_prefix, use_bjdata);
14835  break;
14836  }
14837 
14838  case value_t::number_float:
14839  {
14840  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.number_float, add_prefix, use_bjdata);
14841  break;
14842  }
14843 
14844  case value_t::string:
14845  {
14846  if (add_prefix)
14847  {
14848  oa->write_character(to_char_type('S'));
14849  }
14850  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.string->size(), true, use_bjdata);
14851  oa->write_characters(
14852  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.string->c_str()),
14853  j.m_value.string->size());
14854  break;
14855  }
14856 
14857  case value_t::array:
14858  {
14859  if (add_prefix)
14860  {
14861  oa->write_character(to_char_type('['));
14862  }
14863 
14864  bool prefix_required = true;
14865  if (use_type && !j.m_value.array->empty())
14866  {
14867  JSON_ASSERT(use_count);
14868  const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front(), use_bjdata);
14869  const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin() + 1, j.end(),
14870  [this, first_prefix, use_bjdata](const BasicJsonType & v)
14871  {
14872  return ubjson_prefix(v, use_bjdata) == first_prefix;
14873  });
14874 
14875  std::vector<CharType> bjdx = {'[', '{', 'S', 'H', 'T', 'F', 'N', 'Z'}; // excluded markers in bjdata optimized type
14876 
14877  if (same_prefix && !(use_bjdata && std::find(bjdx.begin(), bjdx.end(), first_prefix) != bjdx.end()))
14878  {
14879  prefix_required = false;
14880  oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
14881  oa->write_character(first_prefix);
14882  }
14883  }
14884 
14885  if (use_count)
14886  {
14887  oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
14888  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.array->size(), true, use_bjdata);
14889  }
14890 
14891  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.array)
14892  {
14893  write_ubjson(el, use_count, use_type, prefix_required, use_bjdata);
14894  }
14895 
14896  if (!use_count)
14897  {
14898  oa->write_character(to_char_type(']'));
14899  }
14900 
14901  break;
14902  }
14903 
14904  case value_t::binary:
14905  {
14906  if (add_prefix)
14907  {
14908  oa->write_character(to_char_type('['));
14909  }
14910 
14911  if (use_type && !j.m_value.binary->empty())
14912  {
14913  JSON_ASSERT(use_count);
14914  oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
14915  oa->write_character('U');
14916  }
14917 
14918  if (use_count)
14919  {
14920  oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
14921  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.binary->size(), true, use_bjdata);
14922  }
14923 
14924  if (use_type)
14925  {
14926  oa->write_characters(
14927  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(j.m_value.binary->data()),
14928  j.m_value.binary->size());
14929  }
14930  else
14931  {
14932  for (size_t i = 0; i < j.m_value.binary->size(); ++i)
14933  {
14934  oa->write_character(to_char_type('U'));
14935  oa->write_character(j.m_value.binary->data()[i]);
14936  }
14937  }
14938 
14939  if (!use_count)
14940  {
14941  oa->write_character(to_char_type(']'));
14942  }
14943 
14944  break;
14945  }
14946 
14947  case value_t::object:
14948  {
14949  if (use_bjdata && j.m_value.object->size() == 3 && j.m_value.object->find("_ArrayType_") != j.m_value.object->end() && j.m_value.object->find("_ArraySize_") != j.m_value.object->end() && j.m_value.object->find("_ArrayData_") != j.m_value.object->end())
14950  {
14951  if (!write_bjdata_ndarray(*j.m_value.object, use_count, use_type)) // decode bjdata ndarray in the JData format (https://github.com/NeuroJSON/jdata)
14952  {
14953  break;
14954  }
14955  }
14956 
14957  if (add_prefix)
14958  {
14959  oa->write_character(to_char_type('{'));
14960  }
14961 
14962  bool prefix_required = true;
14963  if (use_type && !j.m_value.object->empty())
14964  {
14965  JSON_ASSERT(use_count);
14966  const CharType first_prefix = ubjson_prefix(j.front(), use_bjdata);
14967  const bool same_prefix = std::all_of(j.begin(), j.end(),
14968  [this, first_prefix, use_bjdata](const BasicJsonType & v)
14969  {
14970  return ubjson_prefix(v, use_bjdata) == first_prefix;
14971  });
14972 
14973  std::vector<CharType> bjdx = {'[', '{', 'S', 'H', 'T', 'F', 'N', 'Z'}; // excluded markers in bjdata optimized type
14974 
14975  if (same_prefix && !(use_bjdata && std::find(bjdx.begin(), bjdx.end(), first_prefix) != bjdx.end()))
14976  {
14977  prefix_required = false;
14978  oa->write_character(to_char_type('$'));
14979  oa->write_character(first_prefix);
14980  }
14981  }
14982 
14983  if (use_count)
14984  {
14985  oa->write_character(to_char_type('#'));
14986  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(j.m_value.object->size(), true, use_bjdata);
14987  }
14988 
14989  for (const auto& el : *j.m_value.object)
14990  {
14991  write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(el.first.size(), true, use_bjdata);
14992  oa->write_characters(
14993  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(el.first.c_str()),
14994  el.first.size());
14995  write_ubjson(el.second, use_count, use_type, prefix_required, use_bjdata);
14996  }
14997 
14998  if (!use_count)
14999  {
15000  oa->write_character(to_char_type('}'));
15001  }
15002 
15003  break;
15004  }
15005 
15006  case value_t::discarded:
15007  default:
15008  break;
15009  }
15010  }
15011 
15012  private:
15014  // BSON //
15016 
15021  static std::size_t calc_bson_entry_header_size(const string_t& name, const BasicJsonType& j)
15022  {
15023  const auto it = name.find(static_cast<typename string_t::value_type>(0));
15024  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(it != BasicJsonType::string_t::npos))
15025  {
15026  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(409, concat("BSON key cannot contain code point U+0000 (at byte ", std::to_string(it), ")"), &j));
15027  static_cast<void>(j);
15028  }
15029 
15030  return /*id*/ 1ul + name.size() + /*zero-terminator*/1u;
15031  }
15032 
15036  void write_bson_entry_header(const string_t& name,
15037  const std::uint8_t element_type)
15038  {
15039  oa->write_character(to_char_type(element_type)); // boolean
15040  oa->write_characters(
15041  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(name.c_str()),
15042  name.size() + 1u);
15043  }
15044 
15048  void write_bson_boolean(const string_t& name,
15049  const bool value)
15050  {
15051  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x08);
15052  oa->write_character(value ? to_char_type(0x01) : to_char_type(0x00));
15053  }
15054 
15058  void write_bson_double(const string_t& name,
15059  const double value)
15060  {
15061  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x01);
15062  write_number<double>(value, true);
15063  }
15064 
15068  static std::size_t calc_bson_string_size(const string_t& value)
15069  {
15070  return sizeof(std::int32_t) + value.size() + 1ul;
15071  }
15072 
15076  void write_bson_string(const string_t& name,
15077  const string_t& value)
15078  {
15079  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x02);
15080 
15081  write_number<std::int32_t>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value.size() + 1ul), true);
15082  oa->write_characters(
15083  reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(value.c_str()),
15084  value.size() + 1);
15085  }
15086 
15090  void write_bson_null(const string_t& name)
15091  {
15092  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x0A);
15093  }
15094 
15098  static std::size_t calc_bson_integer_size(const std::int64_t value)
15099  {
15100  return (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value && value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()
15101  ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
15102  : sizeof(std::int64_t);
15103  }
15104 
15108  void write_bson_integer(const string_t& name,
15109  const std::int64_t value)
15110  {
15111  if ((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::min)() <= value && value <= (std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)())
15112  {
15113  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10); // int32
15114  write_number<std::int32_t>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value), true);
15115  }
15116  else
15117  {
15118  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12); // int64
15119  write_number<std::int64_t>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(value), true);
15120  }
15121  }
15122 
15126  static constexpr std::size_t calc_bson_unsigned_size(const std::uint64_t value) noexcept
15127  {
15128  return (value <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
15129  ? sizeof(std::int32_t)
15130  : sizeof(std::int64_t);
15131  }
15132 
15136  void write_bson_unsigned(const string_t& name,
15137  const BasicJsonType& j)
15138  {
15139  if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int32_t>::max)()))
15140  {
15141  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x10 /* int32 */);
15142  write_number<std::int32_t>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned), true);
15143  }
15144  else if (j.m_value.number_unsigned <= static_cast<std::uint64_t>((std::numeric_limits<std::int64_t>::max)()))
15145  {
15146  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x12 /* int64 */);
15147  write_number<std::int64_t>(static_cast<std::int64_t>(j.m_value.number_unsigned), true);
15148  }
15149  else
15150  {
15151  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(407, concat("integer number ", std::to_string(j.m_value.number_unsigned), " cannot be represented by BSON as it does not fit int64"), &j));
15152  }
15153  }
15154 
15158  void write_bson_object_entry(const string_t& name,
15159  const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
15160  {
15161  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x03); // object
15162  write_bson_object(value);
15163  }
15164 
15168  static std::size_t calc_bson_array_size(const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value)
15169  {
15170  std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
15171 
15172  const std::size_t embedded_document_size = std::accumulate(std::begin(value), std::end(value), static_cast<std::size_t>(0), [&array_index](std::size_t result, const typename BasicJsonType::array_t::value_type & el)
15173  {
15174  return result + calc_bson_element_size(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
15175  });
15176 
15177  return sizeof(std::int32_t) + embedded_document_size + 1ul;
15178  }
15179 
15183  static std::size_t calc_bson_binary_size(const typename BasicJsonType::binary_t& value)
15184  {
15185  return sizeof(std::int32_t) + value.size() + 1ul;
15186  }
15187 
15191  void write_bson_array(const string_t& name,
15192  const typename BasicJsonType::array_t& value)
15193  {
15194  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x04); // array
15195  write_number<std::int32_t>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_array_size(value)), true);
15196 
15197  std::size_t array_index = 0ul;
15198 
15199  for (const auto& el : value)
15200  {
15201  write_bson_element(std::to_string(array_index++), el);
15202  }
15203 
15204  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
15205  }
15206 
15210  void write_bson_binary(const string_t& name,
15211  const binary_t& value)
15212  {
15213  write_bson_entry_header(name, 0x05);
15214 
15215  write_number<std::int32_t>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(value.size()), true);
15216  write_number(value.has_subtype() ? static_cast<std::uint8_t>(value.subtype()) : static_cast<std::uint8_t>(0x00));
15217 
15218  oa->write_characters(reinterpret_cast<const CharType*>(value.data()), value.size());
15219  }
15220 
15225  static std::size_t calc_bson_element_size(const string_t& name,
15226  const BasicJsonType& j)
15227  {
15228  const auto header_size = calc_bson_entry_header_size(name, j);
15229  switch (j.type())
15230  {
15231  case value_t::object:
15232  return header_size + calc_bson_object_size(*j.m_value.object);
15233 
15234  case value_t::array:
15235  return header_size + calc_bson_array_size(*j.m_value.array);
15236 
15237  case value_t::binary:
15238  return header_size + calc_bson_binary_size(*j.m_value.binary);
15239 
15240  case value_t::boolean:
15241  return header_size + 1ul;
15242 
15243  case value_t::number_float:
15244  return header_size + 8ul;
15245 
15246  case value_t::number_integer:
15247  return header_size + calc_bson_integer_size(j.m_value.number_integer);
15248 
15249  case value_t::number_unsigned:
15250  return header_size + calc_bson_unsigned_size(j.m_value.number_unsigned);
15251 
15252  case value_t::string:
15253  return header_size + calc_bson_string_size(*j.m_value.string);
15254 
15255  case value_t::null:
15256  return header_size + 0ul;
15257 
15258  // LCOV_EXCL_START
15259  case value_t::discarded:
15260  default:
15261  JSON_ASSERT(false); // NOLINT(cert-dcl03-c,hicpp-static-assert,misc-static-assert)
15262  return 0ul;
15263  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
15264  }
15265  }
15266 
15273  void write_bson_element(const string_t& name,
15274  const BasicJsonType& j)
15275  {
15276  switch (j.type())
15277  {
15278  case value_t::object:
15279  return write_bson_object_entry(name, *j.m_value.object);
15280 
15281  case value_t::array:
15282  return write_bson_array(name, *j.m_value.array);
15283 
15284  case value_t::binary:
15285  return write_bson_binary(name, *j.m_value.binary);
15286 
15287  case value_t::boolean:
15288  return write_bson_boolean(name, j.m_value.boolean);
15289 
15290  case value_t::number_float:
15291  return write_bson_double(name, j.m_value.number_float);
15292 
15293  case value_t::number_integer:
15294  return write_bson_integer(name, j.m_value.number_integer);
15295 
15296  case value_t::number_unsigned:
15297  return write_bson_unsigned(name, j);
15298 
15299  case value_t::string:
15300  return write_bson_string(name, *j.m_value.string);
15301 
15302  case value_t::null:
15303  return write_bson_null(name);
15304 
15305  // LCOV_EXCL_START
15306  case value_t::discarded:
15307  default:
15308  JSON_ASSERT(false); // NOLINT(cert-dcl03-c,hicpp-static-assert,misc-static-assert)
15309  return;
15310  // LCOV_EXCL_STOP
15311  }
15312  }
15313 
15320  static std::size_t calc_bson_object_size(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
15321  {
15322  std::size_t document_size = std::accumulate(value.begin(), value.end(), static_cast<std::size_t>(0),
15323  [](size_t result, const typename BasicJsonType::object_t::value_type & el)
15324  {
15325  return result += calc_bson_element_size(el.first, el.second);
15326  });
15327 
15328  return sizeof(std::int32_t) + document_size + 1ul;
15329  }
15330 
15335  void write_bson_object(const typename BasicJsonType::object_t& value)
15336  {
15337  write_number<std::int32_t>(static_cast<std::int32_t>(calc_bson_object_size(value)), true);
15338 
15339  for (const auto& el : value)
15340  {
15341  write_bson_element(el.first, el.second);
15342  }
15343 
15344  oa->write_character(to_char_type(0x00));
15345  }
15346 
15348  // CBOR //
15350 
15351  static constexpr CharType get_cbor_float_prefix(float /*unused*/)
15352  {
15353  return to_char_type(0xFA); // Single-Precision Float
15354  }
15355 
15356  static constexpr CharType get_cbor_float_prefix(double /*unused*/)
15357  {
15358  return to_char_type(0xFB); // Double-Precision Float
15359  }
15360 
15362  // MsgPack //
15364 
15365  static constexpr CharType get_msgpack_float_prefix(float /*unused*/)
15366  {
15367  return to_char_type(0xCA); // float 32
15368  }
15369 
15370  static constexpr CharType get_msgpack_float_prefix(double /*unused*/)
15371  {
15372  return to_char_type(0xCB); // float 64
15373  }
15374 
15376  // UBJSON //
15378 
15379  // UBJSON: write number (floating point)
15380  template<typename NumberType, typename std::enable_if<
15381  std::is_floating_point<NumberType>::value, int>::type = 0>
15382  void write_number_with_ubjson_prefix(const NumberType n,
15383  const bool add_prefix,
15384  const bool use_bjdata)
15385  {
15386  if (add_prefix)
15387  {
15388  oa->write_character(get_ubjson_float_prefix(n));
15389  }
15390  write_number(n, use_bjdata);
15391  }
