18025 template <class Key, class T, class IgnoredLess = std::less<Key>,
18026  class Allocator = std::allocator<std::pair<const Key, T>>>
18027  struct ordered_map : std::vector<std::pair<const Key, T>, Allocator>
18028 {
18029  using key_type = Key;
18030  using mapped_type = T;
18031  using Container = std::vector<std::pair<const Key, T>, Allocator>;
18032  using iterator = typename Container::iterator;
18033  using const_iterator = typename Container::const_iterator;
18034  using size_type = typename Container::size_type;
18035  using value_type = typename Container::value_type;
18036 #ifdef JSON_HAS_CPP_14
18037  using key_compare = std::equal_to<>;
18038 #else
18039  using key_compare = std::equal_to<Key>;
18040 #endif
18041 
18042  // Explicit constructors instead of `using Container::Container`
18043  // otherwise older compilers choke on it (GCC <= 5.5, xcode <= 9.4)
18044  ordered_map() noexcept(noexcept(Container())) : Container{} {}
18045  explicit ordered_map(const Allocator& alloc) noexcept(noexcept(Container(alloc))) : Container{alloc} {}
18046  template <class It>
18047  ordered_map(It first, It last, const Allocator& alloc = Allocator())
18048  : Container{first, last, alloc} {}
18049  ordered_map(std::initializer_list<value_type> init, const Allocator& alloc = Allocator() )
18050  : Container{init, alloc} {}
18051 
18052  std::pair<iterator, bool> emplace(const key_type& key, T&& t)
18053  {
18054  for (auto it = this->begin(); it != this->end(); ++it)
18055  {
18056  if (m_compare(it->first, key))
18057  {
18058  return {it, false};
18059  }
18060  }
18061  Container::emplace_back(key, t);
18062  return {--this->end(), true};
18063  }
18064 
18065  T& operator[](const Key& key)
18066  {
18067  return emplace(key, T{}).first->second;
18068  }
18069 
18070  const T& operator[](const Key& key) const
18071  {
18072  return at(key);
18073  }
18074 
18075  T& at(const Key& key)
18076  {
18077  for (auto it = this->begin(); it != this->end(); ++it)
18078  {
18079  if (m_compare(it->first, key))
18080  {
18081  return it->second;
18082  }
18083  }
18084 
18085  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("key not found"));
18086  }
18087 
18088  const T& at(const Key& key) const
18089  {
18090  for (auto it = this->begin(); it != this->end(); ++it)
18091  {
18092  if (m_compare(it->first, key))
18093  {
18094  return it->second;
18095  }
18096  }
18097 
18098  JSON_THROW(std::out_of_range("key not found"));
18099  }
18100 
18101  size_type erase(const Key& key)
18102  {
18103  for (auto it = this->begin(); it != this->end(); ++it)
18104  {
18105  if (m_compare(it->first, key))
18106  {
18107  // Since we cannot move const Keys, re-construct them in place
18108  for (auto next = it; ++next != this->end(); ++it)
18109  {
18110  it->~value_type(); // Destroy but keep allocation
18111  new (&*it) value_type{std::move(*next)};
18112  }
18113  Container::pop_back();
18114  return 1;
18115  }
18116  }
18117  return 0;
18118  }
18119 
18120  iterator erase(iterator pos)
18121  {
18122  return erase(pos, std::next(pos));
18123  }
18124 
18125  iterator erase(iterator first, iterator last)
18126  {
18127  const auto elements_affected = std::distance(first, last);
18128  const auto offset = std::distance(Container::begin(), first);
18129 
18130  // This is the start situation. We need to delete elements_affected
18131  // elements (3 in this example: e, f, g), and need to return an
18132  // iterator past the last deleted element (h in this example).
18133  // Note that offset is the distance from the start of the vector
18134  // to first. We will need this later.
18135 
18136  // [ a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i, j ]
18137  // ^ ^
18138  // first last
18139 
18140  // Since we cannot move const Keys, we re-construct them in place.
18141  // We start at first and re-construct (viz. copy) the elements from
18142  // the back of the vector. Example for first iteration:
18143 
18144  // ,--------.
18145  // v | destroy e and re-construct with h
18146  // [ a, b, c, d, e, f, g, h, i, j ]
18147  // ^ ^
18148  // it it + elements_affected
18149 
18150  for (auto it = first; std::next(it, elements_affected) != Container::end(); ++it)
18151  {
18152  it->~value_type(); // destroy but keep allocation
18153  new (&*it) value_type{std::move(*std::next(it, elements_affected))}; // "move" next element to it
18154  }
18155 
18156  // [ a, b, c, d, h, i, j, h, i, j ]
18157  // ^ ^
18158  // first last
18159 
18160  // remove the unneeded elements at the end of the vector
18161  Container::resize(this->size() - static_cast<size_type>(elements_affected));
18162 
18163  // [ a, b, c, d, h, i, j ]
18164  // ^ ^
18165  // first last
18166 
18167  // first is now pointing past the last deleted element, but we cannot
18168  // use this iterator, because it may have been invalidated by the
18169  // resize call. Instead, we can return begin() + offset.
18170  return Container::begin() + offset;
18171  }
18172 
18173  size_type count(const Key& key) const
18174  {
18175  for (auto it = this->begin(); it != this->end(); ++it)
18176  {
18177  if (m_compare(it->first, key))
18178  {
18179  return 1;
18180  }
18181  }
18182  return 0;
18183  }
18184 
18185  iterator find(const Key& key)
18186  {
18187  for (auto it = this->begin(); it != this->end(); ++it)
18188  {
18189  if (m_compare(it->first, key))
18190  {
18191  return it;
18192  }
18193  }
18194  return Container::end();
18195  }
18196 
18197  const_iterator find(const Key& key) const
18198  {
18199  for (auto it = this->begin(); it != this->end(); ++it)
18200  {
18201  if (m_compare(it->first, key))
18202  {
18203  return it;
18204  }
18205  }
18206  return Container::end();
18207  }
18208 
18209  std::pair<iterator, bool> insert( value_type&& value )
18210  {
18211  return emplace(value.first, std::move(value.second));
18212  }
18213 
18214  std::pair<iterator, bool> insert( const value_type& value )
18215  {
18216  for (auto it = this->begin(); it != this->end(); ++it)
18217  {
18218  if (m_compare(it->first, value.first))
18219  {
18220  return {it, false};
18221  }
18222  }
18223  Container::push_back(value);
18224  return {--this->end(), true};
18225  }
18226 
18227  template<typename InputIt>
18228  using require_input_iter = typename std::enable_if<std::is_convertible<typename std::iterator_traits<InputIt>::iterator_category,
18229  std::input_iterator_tag>::value>::type;
18230 
18231  template<typename InputIt, typename = require_input_iter<InputIt>>
18232  void insert(InputIt first, InputIt last)
18233  {
18234  for (auto it = first; it != last; ++it)
18235  {
18236  insert(*it);
18237  }
18238  }
18239 
18240 private:
18241  JSON_NO_UNIQUE_ADDRESS key_compare m_compare = key_compare();
18242 };
18243

18460  result["compiler"] = {{"family", "clang"}, {"version", __clang_version__}};
18461 #elif defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__GNUG__)
18462  result["compiler"] = {{"family", "gcc"}, {"version", detail::concat(
18463  std::to_string(__GNUC__), '.',
18464  std::to_string(__GNUC_MINOR__), '.',
18465  std::to_string(__GNUC_PATCHLEVEL__))
18466  }
18467  };
18468 #elif defined(__HP_cc) || defined(__HP_aCC)
18469  result["compiler"] = "hp"
18470 #elif defined(__IBMCPP__)
18471  result["compiler"] = {{"family", "ilecpp"}, {"version", __IBMCPP__}};
18472 #elif defined(_MSC_VER)
18473  result["compiler"] = {{"family", "msvc"}, {"version", _MSC_VER}};
18474 #elif defined(__PGI)
18475  result["compiler"] = {{"family", "pgcpp"}, {"version", __PGI}};
18476 #elif defined(__SUNPRO_CC)
18477  result["compiler"] = {{"family", "sunpro"}, {"version", __SUNPRO_CC}};
18478 #else
18479  result["compiler"] = {{"family", "unknown"}, {"version", "unknown"}};
18480 #endif
18481 
18482 
18483 #if defined(_MSVC_LANG)
18484  result["compiler"]["c++"] = std::to_string(_MSVC_LANG);
18485 #elif defined(__cplusplus)
18486  result["compiler"]["c++"] = std::to_string(__cplusplus);
18487 #else
18488  result["compiler"]["c++"] = "unknown";
18489 #endif
18490  return result;
18491  }

18495  // JSON value data types //
18497 
18502 
18507 #if defined(JSON_HAS_CPP_14)
18508  // use of transparent comparator avoids unnecessary repeated construction of temporaries
18509  // in functions involving lookup by key with types other than object_t::key_type (aka. StringType)
18510  using default_object_comparator_t = std::less<>;
18511 #else
18512  using default_object_comparator_t = std::less<StringType>;
18513 #endif
18514 
18517  using object_t = ObjectType<StringType,
18518  basic_json,
18519  default_object_comparator_t,
18520  AllocatorType<std::pair<const StringType,
18521  basic_json>>>;
18522

18526 
18529  using string_t = StringType;
18530 
18533  using boolean_t = BooleanType;
18534

18538 
18541  using number_unsigned_t = NumberUnsignedType;
18542

18557  private:
18558 
18560  template<typename T, typename... Args>
18561  JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
18562  static T* create(Args&& ... args)
18563  {
18564  AllocatorType<T> alloc;
18565  using AllocatorTraits = std::allocator_traits<AllocatorType<T>>;
18566 
18567  auto deleter = [&](T * obj)
18568  {
18569  AllocatorTraits::deallocate(alloc, obj, 1);
18570  };
18571  std::unique_ptr<T, decltype(deleter)> obj(AllocatorTraits::allocate(alloc, 1), deleter);
18572  AllocatorTraits::construct(alloc, obj.get(), std::forward<Args>(args)...);
18573  JSON_ASSERT(obj != nullptr);
18574  return obj.release();
18575  }
18576 
18578  // JSON value storage //
18580 
18581  JSON_PRIVATE_UNLESS_TESTED:
18607  union json_value
18608  {
18610  object_t* object;
18612  array_t* array;
18614  string_t* string;
18616  binary_t* binary;
18618  boolean_t boolean;
18620  number_integer_t number_integer;
18622  number_unsigned_t number_unsigned;
18624  number_float_t number_float;
18625 
18627  json_value() = default;
18629  json_value(boolean_t v) noexcept : boolean(v) {}
18631  json_value(number_integer_t v) noexcept : number_integer(v) {}
18633  json_value(number_unsigned_t v) noexcept : number_unsigned(v) {}
18635  json_value(number_float_t v) noexcept : number_float(v) {}
18637  json_value(value_t t)
18638  {
18639  switch (t)
18640  {
18641  case value_t::object:
18642  {
18643  object = create<object_t>();
18644  break;
18645  }
18646 
18647  case value_t::array:
18648  {
18649  array = create<array_t>();
18650  break;
18651  }
18652 
18653  case value_t::string:
18654  {
18655  string = create<string_t>("");
18656  break;
18657  }
18658 
18659  case value_t::binary:
18660  {
18661  binary = create<binary_t>();
18662  break;
18663  }
18664 
18665  case value_t::boolean:
18666  {
18667  boolean = static_cast<boolean_t>(false);
18668  break;
18669  }
18670 
18671  case value_t::number_integer:
18672  {
18673  number_integer = static_cast<number_integer_t>(0);
18674  break;
18675  }
18676 
18677  case value_t::number_unsigned:
18678  {
18679  number_unsigned = static_cast<number_unsigned_t>(0);
18680  break;
18681  }
18682 
18683  case value_t::number_float:
18684  {
18685  number_float = static_cast<number_float_t>(0.0);
18686  break;
18687  }
18688 
18689  case value_t::null:
18690  {
18691  object = nullptr; // silence warning, see #821
18692  break;
18693  }
18694 
18695  case value_t::discarded:
18696  default:
18697  {
18698  object = nullptr; // silence warning, see #821
18699  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(t == value_t::null))
18700  {
18701  JSON_THROW(other_error::create(500, "961c151d2e87f2686a955a9be24d316f1362bf21 3.10.5", nullptr)); // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
18702  }
18703  break;
18704  }
18705  }
18706  }
18707 
18709  json_value(const string_t& value) : string(create<string_t>(value)) {}
18710 
18712  json_value(string_t&& value) : string(create<string_t>(std::move(value))) {}
18713 
18715  json_value(const object_t& value) : object(create<object_t>(value)) {}
18716 
18718  json_value(object_t&& value) : object(create<object_t>(std::move(value))) {}
18719 
18721  json_value(const array_t& value) : array(create<array_t>(value)) {}
18722 
18724  json_value(array_t&& value) : array(create<array_t>(std::move(value))) {}
18725 
18727  json_value(const typename binary_t::container_type& value) : binary(create<binary_t>(value)) {}
18728 
18730  json_value(typename binary_t::container_type&& value) : binary(create<binary_t>(std::move(value))) {}
18731 
18733  json_value(const binary_t& value) : binary(create<binary_t>(value)) {}
18734 
18736  json_value(binary_t&& value) : binary(create<binary_t>(std::move(value))) {}
18737 
18738  void destroy(value_t t)
18739  {
18740  if (t == value_t::array || t == value_t::object)
18741  {
18742  // flatten the current json_value to a heap-allocated stack
18743  std::vector<basic_json> stack;
18744 
18745  // move the top-level items to stack
18746  if (t == value_t::array)
18747  {
18748  stack.reserve(array->size());
18749  std::move(array->begin(), array->end(), std::back_inserter(stack));
18750  }
18751  else
18752  {
18753  stack.reserve(object->size());
18754  for (auto&& it : *object)
18755  {
18756  stack.push_back(std::move(it.second));
18757  }
18758  }
18759 
18760  while (!stack.empty())
18761  {
18762  // move the last item to local variable to be processed
18763  basic_json current_item(std::move(stack.back()));
18764  stack.pop_back();
18765 
18766  // if current_item is array/object, move
18767  // its children to the stack to be processed later
18768  if (current_item.is_array())
18769  {
18770  std::move(current_item.m_value.array->begin(), current_item.m_value.array->end(), std::back_inserter(stack));
18771 
18772  current_item.m_value.array->clear();
18773  }
18774  else if (current_item.is_object())
18775  {
18776  for (auto&& it : *current_item.m_value.object)
18777  {
18778  stack.push_back(std::move(it.second));
18779  }
18780 
18781  current_item.m_value.object->clear();
18782  }
18783 
18784  // it's now safe that current_item get destructed
18785  // since it doesn't have any children
18786  }
18787  }
18788 
18789  switch (t)
18790  {
18791  case value_t::object:
18792  {
18793  AllocatorType<object_t> alloc;
18794  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, object);
18795  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, object, 1);
18796  break;
18797  }
18798 
18799  case value_t::array:
18800  {
18801  AllocatorType<array_t> alloc;
18802  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, array);
18803  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, array, 1);
18804  break;
18805  }
18806 
18807  case value_t::string:
18808  {
18809  AllocatorType<string_t> alloc;
18810  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, string);
18811  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, string, 1);
18812  break;
18813  }
18814 
18815  case value_t::binary:
18816  {
18817  AllocatorType<binary_t> alloc;
18818  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, binary);
18819  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, binary, 1);
18820  break;
18821  }
18822 
18823  case value_t::null:
18824  case value_t::boolean:
18825  case value_t::number_integer:
18826  case value_t::number_unsigned:
18827  case value_t::number_float:
18828  case value_t::discarded:
18829  default:
18830  {
18831  break;
18832  }
18833  }
18834  }
18835  };
18836 
18837  private:
18856  void assert_invariant(bool check_parents = true) const noexcept
18857  {
18858  JSON_ASSERT(m_type != value_t::object || m_value.object != nullptr);
18859  JSON_ASSERT(m_type != value_t::array || m_value.array != nullptr);
18860  JSON_ASSERT(m_type != value_t::string || m_value.string != nullptr);
18861  JSON_ASSERT(m_type != value_t::binary || m_value.binary != nullptr);
18862 
18863 #if JSON_DIAGNOSTICS
18864  JSON_TRY
18865  {
18866  // cppcheck-suppress assertWithSideEffect
18867  JSON_ASSERT(!check_parents || !is_structured() || std::all_of(begin(), end(), [this](const basic_json & j)
18868  {
18869  return j.m_parent == this;
18870  }));
18871  }
18872  JSON_CATCH(...) {} // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
18873 #endif
18874  static_cast<void>(check_parents);
18875  }
18876 
18877  void set_parents()
18878  {
18879 #if JSON_DIAGNOSTICS
18880  switch (m_type)
18881  {
18882  case value_t::array:
18883  {
18884  for (auto& element : *m_value.array)
18885  {
18886  element.m_parent = this;
18887  }
18888  break;
18889  }
18890 
18891  case value_t::object:
18892  {
18893  for (auto& element : *m_value.object)
18894  {
18895  element.second.m_parent = this;
18896  }
18897  break;
18898  }
18899 
18900  case value_t::null:
18901  case value_t::string:
18902  case value_t::boolean:
18903  case value_t::number_integer:
18904  case value_t::number_unsigned:
18905  case value_t::number_float:
18906  case value_t::binary:
18907  case value_t::discarded:
18908  default:
18909  break;
18910  }
18911 #endif
18912  }
18913 
18914  iterator set_parents(iterator it, typename iterator::difference_type count_set_parents)
18915  {
18916 #if JSON_DIAGNOSTICS
18917  for (typename iterator::difference_type i = 0; i < count_set_parents; ++i)
18918  {
18919  (it + i)->m_parent = this;
18920  }
18921 #else
18922  static_cast<void>(count_set_parents);
18923 #endif
18924  return it;
18925  }
18926 
18927  reference set_parent(reference j, std::size_t old_capacity = static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))
18928  {
18929 #if JSON_DIAGNOSTICS
18930  if (old_capacity != static_cast<std::size_t>(-1))
18931  {
18932  // see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/2838
18933  JSON_ASSERT(type() == value_t::array);
18934  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(m_value.array->capacity() != old_capacity))
18935  {
18936  // capacity has changed: update all parents
18937  set_parents();
18938  return j;
18939  }
18940  }
18941 
18942  // ordered_json uses a vector internally, so pointers could have
18943  // been invalidated; see https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/2962
18944 #ifdef JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION
18945 #pragma warning(push )
18946 #pragma warning(disable : 4127) // ignore warning to replace if with if constexpr
18947 #endif
18948  if (detail::is_ordered_map<object_t>::value)
18949  {
18950  set_parents();
18951  return j;
18952  }
18953 #ifdef JSON_HEDLEY_MSVC_VERSION
18954 #pragma warning( pop )
18955 #endif
18956 
18957  j.m_parent = this;
18958 #else
18959  static_cast<void>(j);
18960  static_cast<void>(old_capacity);
18961 #endif
18962  return j;
18963  }

18967  // JSON parser callback //
18969 
18972  using parse_event_t = detail::parse_event_t;
18973 
18976  using parser_callback_t = detail::parser_callback_t<basic_json>;
18977 
18979  // constructors //
18981 
18986 
18989  basic_json(const value_t v)
18990  : m_type(v), m_value(v)
18991  {
18992  assert_invariant();
18993  }
18994 
18997  basic_json(std::nullptr_t = nullptr) noexcept // NOLINT(bugprone-exception-escape)
18998  : basic_json(value_t::null)
18999  {
19000  assert_invariant();
19001  }
19002 
19005  template < typename CompatibleType,
19006  typename U = detail::uncvref_t<CompatibleType>,
19007  detail::enable_if_t <
19008  !detail::is_basic_json<U>::value && detail::is_compatible_type<basic_json_t, U>::value, int > = 0 >
19009  basic_json(CompatibleType && val) noexcept(noexcept( // NOLINT(bugprone-forwarding-reference-overload,bugprone-exception-escape)
19010  JSONSerializer<U>::to_json(std::declval<basic_json_t&>(),
19011  std::forward<CompatibleType>(val))))
19012  {
19013  JSONSerializer<U>::to_json(*this, std::forward<CompatibleType>(val));
19014  set_parents();
19015  assert_invariant();
19016  }
19017 
19020  template < typename BasicJsonType,
19021  detail::enable_if_t <
19022  detail::is_basic_json<BasicJsonType>::value&& !std::is_same<basic_json, BasicJsonType>::value, int > = 0 >
19023  basic_json(const BasicJsonType& val)
19024  {
19025  using other_boolean_t = typename BasicJsonType::boolean_t;
19026  using other_number_float_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_float_t;
19027  using other_number_integer_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_integer_t;
19028  using other_number_unsigned_t = typename BasicJsonType::number_unsigned_t;
19029  using other_string_t = typename BasicJsonType::string_t;
19030  using other_object_t = typename BasicJsonType::object_t;
19031  using other_array_t = typename BasicJsonType::array_t;
19032  using other_binary_t = typename BasicJsonType::binary_t;
19033 
19034  switch (val.type())
19035  {
19036  case value_t::boolean:
19037  JSONSerializer<other_boolean_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get<other_boolean_t>());
19038  break;
19039  case value_t::number_float:
19040  JSONSerializer<other_number_float_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get<other_number_float_t>());
19041  break;
19042  case value_t::number_integer:
19043  JSONSerializer<other_number_integer_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get<other_number_integer_t>());
19044  break;
19045  case value_t::number_unsigned:
19046  JSONSerializer<other_number_unsigned_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get<other_number_unsigned_t>());
19047  break;
19048  case value_t::string:
19049  JSONSerializer<other_string_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get_ref<const other_string_t&>());
19050  break;
19051  case value_t::object:
19052  JSONSerializer<other_object_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get_ref<const other_object_t&>());
19053  break;
19054  case value_t::array:
19055  JSONSerializer<other_array_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get_ref<const other_array_t&>());
19056  break;
19057  case value_t::binary:
19058  JSONSerializer<other_binary_t>::to_json(*this, val.template get_ref<const other_binary_t&>());
19059  break;
19060  case value_t::null:
19061  *this = nullptr;
19062  break;
19063  case value_t::discarded:
19064  m_type = value_t::discarded;
19065  break;
19066  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
19067  JSON_ASSERT(false); // NOLINT(cert-dcl03-c,hicpp-static-assert,misc-static-assert) LCOV_EXCL_LINE
19068  }
19069  set_parents();
19070  assert_invariant();
19071  }
19072 
19075  basic_json(initializer_list_t init,
19076  bool type_deduction = true,
19077  value_t manual_type = value_t::array)
19078  {
19079  // check if each element is an array with two elements whose first
19080  // element is a string
19081  bool is_an_object = std::all_of(init.begin(), init.end(),
19082  [](const detail::json_ref<basic_json>& element_ref)
19083  {
19084  return element_ref->is_array() && element_ref->size() == 2 && (*element_ref)[0].is_string();
19085  });
19086 
19087  // adjust type if type deduction is not wanted
19088  if (!type_deduction)
19089  {
19090  // if array is wanted, do not create an object though possible
19091  if (manual_type == value_t::array)
19092  {
19093  is_an_object = false;
19094  }
19095 
19096  // if object is wanted but impossible, throw an exception
19097  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(manual_type == value_t::object && !is_an_object))
19098  {
19099  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(301, "cannot create object from initializer list", nullptr));
19100  }
19101  }
19102 
19103  if (is_an_object)
19104  {
19105  // the initializer list is a list of pairs -> create object
19106  m_type = value_t::object;
19107  m_value = value_t::object;
19108 
19109  for (auto& element_ref : init)
19110  {
19111  auto element = element_ref.moved_or_copied();
19112  m_value.object->emplace(
19113  std::move(*((*element.m_value.array)[0].m_value.string)),
19114  std::move((*element.m_value.array)[1]));
19115  }
19116  }
19117  else
19118  {
19119  // the initializer list describes an array -> create array
19120  m_type = value_t::array;
19121  m_value.array = create<array_t>(init.begin(), init.end());
19122  }
19123 
19124  set_parents();
19125  assert_invariant();
19126  }
19127 
19130  JSON_HEDLEY_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
19131  static basic_json binary(const typename binary_t::container_type& init)
19132  {
19133  auto res = basic_json();
19134  res.m_type = value_t::binary;
19135  res.m_value = init;
19136  return res;
19137  }

19178  }
19179 
19182  JSON_HEDLEY_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
19183  static basic_json object(initializer_list_t init = {})
19184  {
19185  return basic_json(init, false, value_t::object);
19186  }
19187 
19190  basic_json(size_type cnt, const basic_json& val)
19191  : m_type(value_t::array)
19192  {
19193  m_value.array = create<array_t>(cnt, val);
19194  set_parents();
19195  assert_invariant();
19196  }
19197 
19200  template < class InputIT, typename std::enable_if <
19201  std::is_same<InputIT, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value ||
19202  std::is_same<InputIT, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int >::type = 0 >
19203  basic_json(InputIT first, InputIT last)
19204  {
19205  JSON_ASSERT(first.m_object != nullptr);
19206  JSON_ASSERT(last.m_object != nullptr);
19207 
19208  // make sure iterator fits the current value
19209  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(first.m_object != last.m_object))
19210  {
19211  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(201, "iterators are not compatible", nullptr));
19212  }
19213 
19214  // copy type from first iterator
19215  m_type = first.m_object->m_type;
19216 
19217  // check if iterator range is complete for primitive values
19218  switch (m_type)
19219  {
19220  case value_t::boolean:
19221  case value_t::number_float:
19222  case value_t::number_integer:
19223  case value_t::number_unsigned:
19224  case value_t::string:
19225  {
19226  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!first.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()
19227  || !last.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_end()))
19228  {
19229  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(204, "iterators out of range", first.m_object));
19230  }
19231  break;
19232  }
19233 
19234  case value_t::null:
19235  case value_t::object:
19236  case value_t::array:
19237  case value_t::binary:
19238  case value_t::discarded:
19239  default:
19240  break;
19241  }
19242 
19243  switch (m_type)
19244  {
19245  case value_t::number_integer:
19246  {
19247  m_value.number_integer = first.m_object->m_value.number_integer;
19248  break;
19249  }
19250 
19251  case value_t::number_unsigned:
19252  {
19253  m_value.number_unsigned = first.m_object->m_value.number_unsigned;
19254  break;
19255  }
19256 
19257  case value_t::number_float:
19258  {
19259  m_value.number_float = first.m_object->m_value.number_float;
19260  break;
19261  }
19262 
19263  case value_t::boolean:
19264  {
19265  m_value.boolean = first.m_object->m_value.boolean;
19266  break;
19267  }
19268 
19269  case value_t::string:
19270  {
19271  m_value = *first.m_object->m_value.string;
19272  break;
19273  }
19274 
19275  case value_t::object:
19276  {
19277  m_value.object = create<object_t>(first.m_it.object_iterator,
19278  last.m_it.object_iterator);
19279  break;
19280  }
19281 
19282  case value_t::array:
19283  {
19284  m_value.array = create<array_t>(first.m_it.array_iterator,
19285  last.m_it.array_iterator);
19286  break;
19287  }
19288 
19289  case value_t::binary:
19290  {
19291  m_value = *first.m_object->m_value.binary;
19292  break;
19293  }
19294 
19295  case value_t::null:
19296  case value_t::discarded:
19297  default:
19298  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(206, detail::concat("cannot construct with iterators from ", first.m_object->type_name()), first.m_object));
19299  }
19300 
19301  set_parents();
19302  assert_invariant();
19303  }
19304 
19305

19309 
19310  template<typename JsonRef,
19311  detail::enable_if_t<detail::conjunction<detail::is_json_ref<JsonRef>,
19312  std::is_same<typename JsonRef::value_type, basic_json>>::value, int> = 0 >
19313  basic_json(const JsonRef& ref) : basic_json(ref.moved_or_copied()) {}
19314 
19317  basic_json(const basic_json& other)
19318  : m_type(other.m_type)
19319  {
19320  // check of passed value is valid
19321  other.assert_invariant();
19322 
19323  switch (m_type)
19324  {
19325  case value_t::object:
19326  {
19327  m_value = *other.m_value.object;
19328  break;
19329  }
19330 
19331  case value_t::array:
19332  {
19333  m_value = *other.m_value.array;
19334  break;
19335  }
19336 
19337  case value_t::string:
19338  {
19339  m_value = *other.m_value.string;
19340  break;
19341  }
19342 
19343  case value_t::boolean:
19344  {
19345  m_value = other.m_value.boolean;
19346  break;
19347  }
19348 
19349  case value_t::number_integer:
19350  {
19351  m_value = other.m_value.number_integer;
19352  break;
19353  }
19354 
19355  case value_t::number_unsigned:
19356  {
19357  m_value = other.m_value.number_unsigned;
19358  break;
19359  }
19360 
19361  case value_t::number_float:
19362  {
19363  m_value = other.m_value.number_float;
19364  break;
19365  }
19366 
19367  case value_t::binary:
19368  {
19369  m_value = *other.m_value.binary;
19370  break;
19371  }
19372 
19373  case value_t::null:
19374  case value_t::discarded:
19375  default:
19376  break;
19377  }
19378 
19379  set_parents();
19380  assert_invariant();
19381  }
19382 
19385  basic_json(basic_json&& other) noexcept
19386  : m_type(std::move(other.m_type)),
19387  m_value(std::move(other.m_value))
19388  {
19389  // check that passed value is valid
19390  other.assert_invariant(false);
19391 
19392  // invalidate payload
19393  other.m_type = value_t::null;
19394  other.m_value = {};
19395 
19396  set_parents();
19397  assert_invariant();
19398  }
19399 
19402  basic_json& operator=(basic_json other) noexcept (
19403  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<value_t>::value&&
19404  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<value_t>::value&&
19405  std::is_nothrow_move_constructible<json_value>::value&&
19406  std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<json_value>::value
19407  )
19408  {
19409  // check that passed value is valid
19410  other.assert_invariant();
19411 
19412  using std::swap;
19413  swap(m_type, other.m_type);
19414  swap(m_value, other.m_value);
19415 
19416  set_parents();
19417  assert_invariant();
19418  return *this;
19419  }
19420 
19423  ~basic_json() noexcept
19424  {
19425  assert_invariant(false);
19426  m_value.destroy(m_type);
19427  }

19442  string_t dump(const int indent = -1,
19443  const char indent_char = ' ',
19444  const bool ensure_ascii = false,
19445  const error_handler_t error_handler = error_handler_t::strict) const
19446  {
19447  string_t result;
19448  serializer s(detail::output_adapter<char, string_t>(result), indent_char, error_handler);
19449 
19450  if (indent >= 0)
19451  {
19452  s.dump(*this, true, ensure_ascii, static_cast<unsigned int>(indent));
19453  }
19454  else
19455  {
19456  s.dump(*this, false, ensure_ascii, 0);
19457  }
19458 
19459  return result;
19460  }

19692  template<typename ReferenceType, typename ThisType>
19693  static ReferenceType get_ref_impl(ThisType& obj)
19694  {
19695  // delegate the call to get_ptr<>()
19696  auto* ptr = obj.template get_ptr<typename std::add_pointer<ReferenceType>::type>();
19697 
19698  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(ptr != nullptr))
19699  {
19700  return *ptr;
19701  }
19702 
19703  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(303, detail::concat("incompatible ReferenceType for get_ref, actual type is ", obj.type_name()), &obj));
19704  }

20110  reference at(size_type idx)
20111  {
20112  // at only works for arrays
20113  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(is_array()))
20114  {
20115  JSON_TRY
20116  {
20117  return set_parent(m_value.array->at(idx));
20118  }
20119  JSON_CATCH (std::out_of_range&)
20120  {
20121  // create better exception explanation
20122  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(401, detail::concat("array index ", std::to_string(idx), " is out of range"), this));
20123  }
20124  }
20125  else
20126  {
20127  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(304, detail::concat("cannot use at() with ", type_name()), this));
20128  }
20129  }

20146  }

20151  }

20153 
20156  reference at(const typename object_t::key_type& key)
20157  {
20158  // at only works for objects
20159  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!is_object()))
20160  {
20161  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(304, detail::concat("cannot use at() with ", type_name()), this));
20162  }
20163 
20164  auto it = m_value.object->find(key);
20165  if (it == m_value.object->end())
20166  {
20167  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(403, detail::concat("key '", key, "' not found"), this));
20168  }
20169  return set_parent(it->second);
20170  }
20171 
20174  template<class KeyType, detail::enable_if_t<
20175  detail::is_usable_as_key_type<basic_json_t, KeyType>::value, int> = 0>
20176  reference at(KeyType && key)
20177  {
20178  // at only works for objects
20179  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!is_object()))
20180  {
20181  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(304, detail::concat("cannot use at() with ", type_name()), this));
20182  }
20183 
20184  auto it = m_value.object->find(std::forward<KeyType>(key));
20185  if (it == m_value.object->end())
20186  {
20187  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(403, detail::concat("key '", string_t(std::forward<KeyType>(key)), "' not found"), this));
20188  }
20189  return set_parent(it->second);
20190  }

20194  const_reference at(const typename object_t::key_type& key) const
20195  {
20196  // at only works for objects
20197  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!is_object()))
20198  {
20199  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(304, detail::concat("cannot use at() with ", type_name()), this));
20200  }
20201 
20202  auto it = m_value.object->find(key);
20203  if (it == m_value.object->end())
20204  {
20205  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(403, detail::concat("key '", key, "' not found"), this));
20206  }
20207  return it->second;
20208  }

20212  template<class KeyType, detail::enable_if_t<
20213  detail::is_usable_as_key_type<basic_json_t, KeyType>::value, int> = 0>
20214  const_reference at(KeyType && key) const
20215  {
20216  // at only works for objects
20217  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!is_object()))
20218  {
20219  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(304, detail::concat("cannot use at() with ", type_name()), this));
20220  }
20221 
20222  auto it = m_value.object->find(std::forward<KeyType>(key));
20223  if (it == m_value.object->end())
20224  {
20225  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(403, detail::concat("key '", string_t(std::forward<KeyType>(key)), "' not found"), this));
20226  }
20227  return it->second;

20232  reference operator[](size_type idx)
20233  {
20234  // implicitly convert null value to an empty array
20235  if (is_null())
20236  {
20237  m_type = value_t::array;
20238  m_value.array = create<array_t>();
20239  assert_invariant();
20240  }
20241 
20242  // operator[] only works for arrays
20243  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(is_array()))
20244  {
20245  // fill up array with null values if given idx is outside range
20246  if (idx >= m_value.array->size())
20247  {
20248 #if JSON_DIAGNOSTICS
20249  // remember array size & capacity before resizing
20250  const auto old_size = m_value.array->size();
20251  const auto old_capacity = m_value.array->capacity();
20252 #endif
20253  m_value.array->resize(idx + 1);
20254 
20255 #if JSON_DIAGNOSTICS
20256  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(m_value.array->capacity() != old_capacity))
20257  {
20258  // capacity has changed: update all parents
20259  set_parents();
20260  }
20261  else
20262  {
20263  // set parent for values added above
20264  set_parents(begin() + static_cast<typename iterator::difference_type>(old_size), static_cast<typename iterator::difference_type>(idx + 1 - old_size));
20265  }
20266 #endif
20267  assert_invariant();
20268  }
20269 
20270  return m_value.array->operator[](idx);
20271  }
20272 
20273  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(305, detail::concat("cannot use operator[] with a numeric argument with ", type_name()), this));
20274  }
20275

20279  {
20280  // const operator[] only works for arrays
20281  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(is_array()))
20282  {
20283  return m_value.array->operator[](idx);
20284  }
20285 
20286  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(305, detail::concat("cannot use operator[] with a numeric argument with ", type_name()), this));
20287  }

20547  template < class IteratorType, detail::enable_if_t <
20548  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value ||
20549  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int > = 0 >
20550  IteratorType erase(IteratorType pos)
20551  {
20552  // make sure iterator fits the current value
20553  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(this != pos.m_object))
20554  {
20555  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(202, "iterator does not fit current value", this));
20556  }
20557 
20558  IteratorType result = end();
20559 
20560  switch (m_type)
20561  {
20562  case value_t::boolean:
20563  case value_t::number_float:
20564  case value_t::number_integer:
20565  case value_t::number_unsigned:
20566  case value_t::string:
20567  case value_t::binary:
20568  {
20569  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!pos.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()))
20570  {
20571  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(205, "iterator out of range", this));
20572  }
20573 
20574  if (is_string())
20575  {
20576  AllocatorType<string_t> alloc;
20577  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, m_value.string);
20578  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, m_value.string, 1);
20579  m_value.string = nullptr;
20580  }
20581  else if (is_binary())
20582  {
20583  AllocatorType<binary_t> alloc;
20584  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, m_value.binary);
20585  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, m_value.binary, 1);
20586  m_value.binary = nullptr;
20587  }
20588 
20589  m_type = value_t::null;
20590  assert_invariant();
20591  break;
20592  }
20593 
20594  case value_t::object:
20595  {
20596  result.m_it.object_iterator = m_value.object->erase(pos.m_it.object_iterator);
20597  break;
20598  }
20599 
20600  case value_t::array:
20601  {
20602  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->erase(pos.m_it.array_iterator);
20603  break;
20604  }
20605 
20606  case value_t::null:
20607  case value_t::discarded:
20608  default:
20609  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(307, detail::concat("cannot use erase() with ", type_name()), this));
20610  }
20611 
20612  return result;
20613  }
20614 
20617  template < class IteratorType, detail::enable_if_t <
20618  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::iterator>::value ||
20619  std::is_same<IteratorType, typename basic_json_t::const_iterator>::value, int > = 0 >
20620  IteratorType erase(IteratorType first, IteratorType last)
20621  {
20622  // make sure iterator fits the current value
20623  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(this != first.m_object || this != last.m_object))
20624  {
20625  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(203, "iterators do not fit current value", this));
20626  }
20627 
20628  IteratorType result = end();
20629 
20630  switch (m_type)
20631  {
20632  case value_t::boolean:
20633  case value_t::number_float:
20634  case value_t::number_integer:
20635  case value_t::number_unsigned:
20636  case value_t::string:
20637  case value_t::binary:
20638  {
20639  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(!first.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_begin()
20640  || !last.m_it.primitive_iterator.is_end()))
20641  {
20642  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(204, "iterators out of range", this));
20643  }
20644 
20645  if (is_string())
20646  {
20647  AllocatorType<string_t> alloc;
20648  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, m_value.string);
20649  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, m_value.string, 1);
20650  m_value.string = nullptr;
20651  }
20652  else if (is_binary())
20653  {
20654  AllocatorType<binary_t> alloc;
20655  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::destroy(alloc, m_value.binary);
20656  std::allocator_traits<decltype(alloc)>::deallocate(alloc, m_value.binary, 1);
20657  m_value.binary = nullptr;
20658  }
20659 
20660  m_type = value_t::null;
20661  assert_invariant();
20662  break;
20663  }
20664 
20665  case value_t::object:
20666  {
20667  result.m_it.object_iterator = m_value.object->erase(first.m_it.object_iterator,
20668  last.m_it.object_iterator);
20669  break;
20670  }
20671 
20672  case value_t::array:
20673  {
20674  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->erase(first.m_it.array_iterator,
20675  last.m_it.array_iterator);
20676  break;
20677  }
20678 
20679  case value_t::null:
20680  case value_t::discarded:
20681  default:
20682  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(307, detail::concat("cannot use erase() with ", type_name()), this));
20683  }
20684 
20685  return result;
20686  }
20687 
20688  private:
20689  template < typename KeyType, detail::enable_if_t <
20690  detail::has_erase_with_key_type<basic_json_t, KeyType>::value, int > = 0 >
20691  size_type erase_internal(KeyType && key)
20692  {
20693  // this erase only works for objects
20694  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!is_object()))
20695  {
20696  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(307, detail::concat("cannot use erase() with ", type_name()), this));
20697  }
20698 
20699  return m_value.object->erase(std::forward<KeyType>(key));
20700  }
20701 
20702  template < typename KeyType, detail::enable_if_t <
20703  !detail::has_erase_with_key_type<basic_json_t, KeyType>::value, int > = 0 >
20704  size_type erase_internal(KeyType && key)
20705  {
20706  // this erase only works for objects
20707  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!is_object()))
20708  {
20709  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(307, detail::concat("cannot use erase() with ", type_name()), this));
20710  }
20711 
20712  const auto it = m_value.object->find(std::forward<KeyType>(key));
20713  if (it != m_value.object->end())
20714  {
20715  m_value.object->erase(it);
20716  return 1;
20717  }
20718  return 0;
20719  }

20743  void erase(const size_type idx)

20745  // this erase only works for arrays

20747  {
20748  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(idx >= size()))

20750  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(401, detail::concat("array index ", std::to_string(idx), " is out of range"), this));
20751  }
20752 
20753  m_value.array->erase(m_value.array->begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(idx));
20754  }
20755  else
20756  {
20757  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(307, detail::concat("cannot use erase() with ", type_name()), this));
20758  }

21030  bool empty() const noexcept
21031  {
21032  switch (m_type)
21033  {
21034  case value_t::null:
21035  {
21036  // null values are empty
21037  return true;
21038  }
21039 
21040  case value_t::array:
21041  {
21042  // delegate call to array_t::empty()
21043  return m_value.array->empty();
21044  }
21045 
21046  case value_t::object:
21047  {
21048  // delegate call to object_t::empty()
21049  return m_value.object->empty();
21050  }
21051 
21052  case value_t::string:
21053  case value_t::boolean:
21054  case value_t::number_integer:
21055  case value_t::number_unsigned:
21056  case value_t::number_float:
21057  case value_t::binary:
21058  case value_t::discarded:
21059  default:
21060  {
21061  // all other types are nonempty
21062  return false;
21063  }
21064  }
21065  }

21074  {

21076  return 0;
21077  }

21079  case value_t::array:

21083  }

21086  {

21213  void push_back(basic_json&& val)
21214  {
21215  // push_back only works for null objects or arrays
21216  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(is_null() || is_array())))
21217  {
21218  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(308, detail::concat("cannot use push_back() with ", type_name()), this));
21219  }
21220 
21221  // transform null object into an array
21222  if (is_null())
21223  {
21224  m_type = value_t::array;
21225  m_value = value_t::array;
21226  assert_invariant();
21227  }
21228 
21229  // add element to array (move semantics)
21230  const auto old_capacity = m_value.array->capacity();
21231  m_value.array->push_back(std::move(val));
21232  set_parent(m_value.array->back(), old_capacity);
21233  // if val is moved from, basic_json move constructor marks it null, so we do not call the destructor
21234  }
21235 
21238  reference operator+=(basic_json&& val)
21239  {
21240  push_back(std::move(val));
21241  return *this;
21242  }
21243

21309  void push_back(initializer_list_t init)
21310  {

21312  {
21313  basic_json&& key = init.begin()->moved_or_copied();
21314  push_back(typename object_t::value_type(
21315  std::move(key.get_ref<string_t&>()), (init.begin() + 1)->moved_or_copied()));
21316  }
21317  else
21318  {
21319  push_back(basic_json(init));
21320  }
21321  }

21333  template<class... Args>
21334  reference emplace_back(Args&& ... args)
21335  {
21336  // emplace_back only works for null objects or arrays
21337  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(is_null() || is_array())))
21338  {
21339  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(311, detail::concat("cannot use emplace_back() with ", type_name()), this));
21340  }
21341 
21342  // transform null object into an array
21343  if (is_null())
21344  {
21345  m_type = value_t::array;
21346  m_value = value_t::array;
21347  assert_invariant();
21348  }
21349 
21350  // add element to array (perfect forwarding)
21351  const auto old_capacity = m_value.array->capacity();
21352  m_value.array->emplace_back(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
21353  return set_parent(m_value.array->back(), old_capacity);
21354  }
21355 
21358  template<class... Args>
21359  std::pair<iterator, bool> emplace(Args&& ... args)
21360  {
21361  // emplace only works for null objects or arrays
21362  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!(is_null() || is_object())))
21363  {
21364  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(311, detail::concat("cannot use emplace() with ", type_name()), this));
21365  }
21366 
21367  // transform null object into an object
21368  if (is_null())
21369  {
21370  m_type = value_t::object;
21371  m_value = value_t::object;
21372  assert_invariant();
21373  }
21374 
21375  // add element to array (perfect forwarding)
21376  auto res = m_value.object->emplace(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
21377  set_parent(res.first->second);
21378 
21379  // create result iterator and set iterator to the result of emplace
21380  auto it = begin();
21381  it.m_it.object_iterator = res.first;
21382 
21383  // return pair of iterator and boolean
21384  return {it, res.second};
21385  }
21386 
21390  template<typename... Args>
21391  iterator insert_iterator(const_iterator pos, Args&& ... args)
21392  {
21393  iterator result(this);
21394  JSON_ASSERT(m_value.array != nullptr);
21395 
21396  auto insert_pos = std::distance(m_value.array->begin(), pos.m_it.array_iterator);
21397  m_value.array->insert(pos.m_it.array_iterator, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
21398  result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->begin() + insert_pos;
21399 
21400  // This could have been written as:
21401  // result.m_it.array_iterator = m_value.array->insert(pos.m_it.array_iterator, cnt, val);
21402  // but the return value of insert is missing in GCC 4.8, so it is written this way instead.
21403 
21404  set_parents();
21405  return result;
21406  }

21426  }

21457  iterator insert(const_iterator pos, const_iterator first, const_iterator last)
21458  {
21459  // insert only works for arrays
21460  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!is_array()))
21461  {
21462  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(309, detail::concat("cannot use insert() with ", type_name()), this));
21463  }
21464 
21465  // check if iterator pos fits to this JSON value
21466  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(pos.m_object != this))
21467  {
21468  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(202, "iterator does not fit current value", this));
21469  }
21470 
21471  // check if range iterators belong to the same JSON object
21472  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(first.m_object != last.m_object))
21473  {
21474  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(210, "iterators do not fit", this));
21475  }
21476 
21477  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(first.m_object == this))
21478  {
21479  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(211, "passed iterators may not belong to container", this));
21480  }
21481

21483  return insert_iterator(pos, first.m_it.array_iterator, last.m_it.array_iterator);

21518  {
21519  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(210, "iterators do not fit", this));

21523  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!first.m_object->is_object()))

21533  void update(const_reference j, bool merge_objects = false)
21534  {
21535  update(j.begin(), j.end(), merge_objects);
21536  }
21537 
21540  void update(const_iterator first, const_iterator last, bool merge_objects = false)
21541  {
21542  // implicitly convert null value to an empty object
21543  if (is_null())
21544  {
21545  m_type = value_t::object;
21546  m_value.object = create<object_t>();
21547  assert_invariant();
21548  }
21549 
21550  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!is_object()))
21551  {
21552  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(312, detail::concat("cannot use update() with ", type_name()), this));
21553  }
21554 
21555  // check if range iterators belong to the same JSON object
21556  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(first.m_object != last.m_object))
21557  {
21558  JSON_THROW(invalid_iterator::create(210, "iterators do not fit", this));
21559  }
21560 
21561  // passed iterators must belong to objects
21562  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!first.m_object->is_object()))
21563  {
21564  JSON_THROW(type_error::create(312, detail::concat("cannot use update() with ", first.m_object->type_name()), first.m_object));
21565  }
21566 
21567  for (auto it = first; it != last; ++it)
21568  {
21569  if (merge_objects && it.value().is_object())
21570  {
21571  auto it2 = m_value.object->find(it.key());
21572  if (it2 != m_value.object->end())
21573  {
21574  it2->second.update(it.value(), true);
21575  continue;
21576  }
21577  }
21578  m_value.object->operator[](it.key()) = it.value();
21579 #if JSON_DIAGNOSTICS
21580  m_value.object->operator[](it.key()).m_parent = this;
21581 #endif
21582  }
21583  }

21691  public:
21693  // lexicographical comparison operators //
21695 
21698 
21701  friend bool operator==(const_reference lhs, const_reference rhs) noexcept
21702  {
21703 #ifdef __GNUC__
21704 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
21705 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wfloat-equal"
21706 #endif
21707  const auto lhs_type = lhs.type();
21708  const auto rhs_type = rhs.type();
21709 
21710  if (lhs_type == rhs_type)
21711  {
21712  switch (lhs_type)
21713  {
21714  case value_t::array:
21715  return *lhs.m_value.array == *rhs.m_value.array;
21716 
21717  case value_t::object:
21718  return *lhs.m_value.object == *rhs.m_value.object;
21719 
21720  case value_t::null:
21721  return true;
21722 
21723  case value_t::string:
21724  return *lhs.m_value.string == *rhs.m_value.string;
21725 
21726  case value_t::boolean:
21727  return lhs.m_value.boolean == rhs.m_value.boolean;
21728 
21729  case value_t::number_integer:
21730  return lhs.m_value.number_integer == rhs.m_value.number_integer;
21731 
21732  case value_t::number_unsigned:
21733  return lhs.m_value.number_unsigned == rhs.m_value.number_unsigned;
21734 
21735  case value_t::number_float:
21736  return lhs.m_value.number_float == rhs.m_value.number_float;
21737 
21738  case value_t::binary:
21739  return *lhs.m_value.binary == *rhs.m_value.binary;
21740 
21741  case value_t::discarded:
21742  default:
21743  return false;
21744  }
21745  }
21746  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer && rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
21747  {
21748  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_integer) == rhs.m_value.number_float;
21749  }
21750  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float && rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
21751  {
21752  return lhs.m_value.number_float == static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_integer);
21753  }
21754  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned && rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
21755  {
21756  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) == rhs.m_value.number_float;
21757  }
21758  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float && rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
21759  {
21760  return lhs.m_value.number_float == static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
21761  }
21762  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned && rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
21763  {
21764  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) == rhs.m_value.number_integer;
21765  }
21766  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer && rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
21767  {
21768  return lhs.m_value.number_integer == static_cast<number_integer_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
21769  }
21770 
21771  return false;
21772 #ifdef __GNUC__
21773 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
21774 #endif
21775  }
21776 
21779  template<typename ScalarType, typename std::enable_if<
21780  std::is_scalar<ScalarType>::value, int>::type = 0>
21781  friend bool operator==(const_reference lhs, ScalarType rhs) noexcept
21782  {
21783  return lhs == basic_json(rhs);
21784  }

21819 
21822  friend bool operator<(const_reference lhs, const_reference rhs) noexcept
21823  {
21824  const auto lhs_type = lhs.type();
21825  const auto rhs_type = rhs.type();
21826 
21827  if (lhs_type == rhs_type)
21828  {
21829  switch (lhs_type)
21830  {
21831  case value_t::array:
21832  // note parentheses are necessary, see
21833  // https://github.com/nlohmann/json/issues/1530
21834  return (*lhs.m_value.array) < (*rhs.m_value.array);
21835 
21836  case value_t::object:
21837  return (*lhs.m_value.object) < (*rhs.m_value.object);
21838 
21839  case value_t::null:
21840  return false;
21841 
21842  case value_t::string:
21843  return (*lhs.m_value.string) < (*rhs.m_value.string);
21844 
21845  case value_t::boolean:
21846  return (lhs.m_value.boolean) < (rhs.m_value.boolean);
21847 
21848  case value_t::number_integer:
21849  return (lhs.m_value.number_integer) < (rhs.m_value.number_integer);
21850 
21851  case value_t::number_unsigned:
21852  return (lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) < (rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
21853 
21854  case value_t::number_float:
21855  return (lhs.m_value.number_float) < (rhs.m_value.number_float);
21856 
21857  case value_t::binary:
21858  return (*lhs.m_value.binary) < (*rhs.m_value.binary);
21859 
21860  case value_t::discarded:
21861  default:
21862  return false;
21863  }
21864  }
21865  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer && rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
21866  {
21867  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_integer) < rhs.m_value.number_float;
21868  }
21869  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float && rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
21870  {
21871  return lhs.m_value.number_float < static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_integer);
21872  }
21873  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned && rhs_type == value_t::number_float)
21874  {
21875  return static_cast<number_float_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) < rhs.m_value.number_float;
21876  }
21877  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_float && rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
21878  {
21879  return lhs.m_value.number_float < static_cast<number_float_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
21880  }
21881  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_integer && rhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned)
21882  {
21883  return lhs.m_value.number_integer < static_cast<number_integer_t>(rhs.m_value.number_unsigned);
21884  }
21885  else if (lhs_type == value_t::number_unsigned && rhs_type == value_t::number_integer)
21886  {
21887  return static_cast<number_integer_t>(lhs.m_value.number_unsigned) < rhs.m_value.number_integer;
21888  }
21889 
21890  // We only reach this line if we cannot compare values. In that case,
21891  // we compare types. Note we have to call the operator explicitly,
21892  // because MSVC has problems otherwise.
21893  return operator<(lhs_type, rhs_type);
21894  }
21895

21899  std::is_scalar<ScalarType>::value, int>::type = 0>
21900  friend bool operator<(const_reference lhs, ScalarType rhs) noexcept
21901  {
21902  return lhs < basic_json(rhs);
21903  }

21992  // serialization //
21994 
21997 #ifndef JSON_NO_IO
22000  friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& o, const basic_json& j)
22001  {
22002  // read width member and use it as indentation parameter if nonzero
22003  const bool pretty_print = o.width() > 0;
22004  const auto indentation = pretty_print ? o.width() : 0;
22005 
22006  // reset width to 0 for subsequent calls to this stream
22007  o.width(0);
22008 
22009  // do the actual serialization
22010  serializer s(detail::output_adapter<char>(o), o.fill());
22011  s.dump(j, pretty_print, false, static_cast<unsigned int>(indentation));
22012  return o;
22013  }

22106  template <typename InputType, typename SAX>
22107  JSON_HEDLEY_NON_NULL(2)
22108  static bool sax_parse(InputType&& i, SAX* sax,
22109  input_format_t format = input_format_t::json,
22110  const bool strict = true,
22111  const bool ignore_comments = false)
22112  {
22113  auto ia = detail::input_adapter(std::forward<InputType>(i));
22114  return format == input_format_t::json
22115  ? parser(std::move(ia), nullptr, true, ignore_comments).sax_parse(sax, strict)
22116  : detail::binary_reader<basic_json, decltype(ia), SAX>(std::move(ia), format).sax_parse(format, sax, strict);
22117  }

22183  JSON_HEDLEY_RETURNS_NON_NULL
22184  const char* type_name() const noexcept
22185  {
22186  switch (m_type)
22187  {
22188  case value_t::null:
22189  return "null";
22190  case value_t::object:
22191  return "object";
22192  case value_t::array:
22193  return "array";
22194  case value_t::string:
22195  return "string";
22196  case value_t::boolean:
22197  return "boolean";
22198  case value_t::binary:
22199  return "binary";
22200  case value_t::discarded:
22201  return "discarded";
22202  case value_t::number_integer:
22203  case value_t::number_unsigned:
22204  case value_t::number_float:
22205  default:
22206  return "number";
22207  }
22208  }

22360  template<typename InputType>
22361  JSON_HEDLEY_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
22362  static basic_json from_cbor(InputType&& i,
22363  const bool strict = true,
22364  const bool allow_exceptions = true,
22365  const cbor_tag_handler_t tag_handler = cbor_tag_handler_t::error)
22366  {
22367  basic_json result;
22368  detail::json_sax_dom_parser<basic_json> sdp(result, allow_exceptions);
22369  auto ia = detail::input_adapter(std::forward<InputType>(i));
22370  const bool res = binary_reader<decltype(ia)>(std::move(ia), input_format_t::cbor).sax_parse(input_format_t::cbor, &sdp, strict, tag_handler);
22371  return res ? result : basic_json(value_t::discarded);
22372  }

22424  {
22425  basic_json result;
22426  detail::json_sax_dom_parser<basic_json> sdp(result, allow_exceptions);
22427  auto ia = detail::input_adapter(std::forward<InputType>(i));
22428  const bool res = binary_reader<decltype(ia)>(std::move(ia), input_format_t::msgpack).sax_parse(input_format_t::msgpack, &sdp, strict);
22429  return res ? result : basic_json(value_t::discarded);
22430  }

22689 
22691 
22693  // JSON Patch functions //
22695 
22698 
22701  basic_json patch(const basic_json& json_patch) const
22702  {
22703  // make a working copy to apply the patch to
22704  basic_json result = *this;
22705 
22706  // the valid JSON Patch operations
22707  enum class patch_operations {add, remove, replace, move, copy, test, invalid};
22708 
22709  const auto get_op = [](const std::string & op)
22710  {
22711  if (op == "add")
22712  {
22713  return patch_operations::add;
22714  }
22715  if (op == "remove")
22716  {
22717  return patch_operations::remove;
22718  }
22719  if (op == "replace")
22720  {
22721  return patch_operations::replace;
22722  }
22723  if (op == "move")
22724  {
22725  return patch_operations::move;
22726  }
22727  if (op == "copy")
22728  {
22729  return patch_operations::copy;
22730  }
22731  if (op == "test")
22732  {
22733  return patch_operations::test;
22734  }
22735 
22736  return patch_operations::invalid;
22737  };
22738 
22739  // wrapper for "add" operation; add value at ptr
22740  const auto operation_add = [&result](json_pointer & ptr, basic_json val)
22741  {
22742  // adding to the root of the target document means replacing it
22743  if (ptr.empty())
22744  {
22745  result = val;
22746  return;
22747  }
22748 
22749  // make sure the top element of the pointer exists
22750  json_pointer top_pointer = ptr.top();
22751  if (top_pointer != ptr)
22752  {
22753  result.at(top_pointer);
22754  }
22755 
22756  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
22757  const auto last_path = ptr.back();
22758  ptr.pop_back();
22759  basic_json& parent = result[ptr];
22760 
22761  switch (parent.m_type)
22762  {
22763  case value_t::null:
22764  case value_t::object:
22765  {
22766  // use operator[] to add value
22767  parent[last_path] = val;
22768  break;
22769  }
22770 
22771  case value_t::array:
22772  {
22773  if (last_path == "-")
22774  {
22775  // special case: append to back
22776  parent.push_back(val);
22777  }
22778  else
22779  {
22780  const auto idx = json_pointer::template array_index<basic_json_t>(last_path);
22781  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(idx > parent.size()))
22782  {
22783  // avoid undefined behavior
22784  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(401, detail::concat("array index ", std::to_string(idx), " is out of range"), &parent));
22785  }
22786 
22787  // default case: insert add offset
22788  parent.insert(parent.begin() + static_cast<difference_type>(idx), val);
22789  }
22790  break;
22791  }
22792 
22793  // if there exists a parent it cannot be primitive
22794  case value_t::string: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
22795  case value_t::boolean: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
22796  case value_t::number_integer: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
22797  case value_t::number_unsigned: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
22798  case value_t::number_float: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
22799  case value_t::binary: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
22800  case value_t::discarded: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
22801  default: // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
22802  JSON_ASSERT(false); // NOLINT(cert-dcl03-c,hicpp-static-assert,misc-static-assert) LCOV_EXCL_LINE
22803  }
22804  };
22805 
22806  // wrapper for "remove" operation; remove value at ptr
22807  const auto operation_remove = [this, &result](json_pointer & ptr)
22808  {
22809  // get reference to parent of JSON pointer ptr
22810  const auto last_path = ptr.back();
22811  ptr.pop_back();
22812  basic_json& parent = result.at(ptr);
22813 
22814  // remove child
22815  if (parent.is_object())
22816  {
22817  // perform range check
22818  auto it = parent.find(last_path);
22819  if (JSON_HEDLEY_LIKELY(it != parent.end()))
22820  {
22821  parent.erase(it);
22822  }
22823  else
22824  {
22825  JSON_THROW(out_of_range::create(403, detail::concat("key '", last_path, "' not found"), this));
22826  }
22827  }
22828  else if (parent.is_array())
22829  {
22830  // note erase performs range check
22831  parent.erase(json_pointer::template array_index<basic_json_t>(last_path));
22832  }
22833  };
22834 
22835  // type check: top level value must be an array
22836  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!json_patch.is_array()))
22837  {
22838  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects", &json_patch));
22839  }
22840 
22841  // iterate and apply the operations
22842  for (const auto& val : json_patch)
22843  {
22844  // wrapper to get a value for an operation
22845  const auto get_value = [&val](const std::string & op,
22846  const std::string & member,
22847  bool string_type) -> basic_json &
22848  {
22849  // find value
22850  auto it = val.m_value.object->find(member);
22851 
22852  // context-sensitive error message
22853  const auto error_msg = (op == "op") ? "operation" : detail::concat("operation '", op, '\'');
22854 
22855  // check if desired value is present
22856  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(it == val.m_value.object->end()))
22857  {
22858  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(performance-inefficient-string-concatenation)
22859  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, detail::concat(error_msg, " must have member '", member, "'"), &val));
22860  }
22861 
22862  // check if result is of type string
22863  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(string_type && !it->second.is_string()))
22864  {
22865  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(performance-inefficient-string-concatenation)
22866  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, detail::concat(error_msg, " must have string member '", member, "'"), &val));
22867  }
22868 
22869  // no error: return value
22870  return it->second;
22871  };
22872 
22873  // type check: every element of the array must be an object
22874  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!val.is_object()))
22875  {
22876  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(104, 0, "JSON patch must be an array of objects", &val));
22877  }
22878 
22879  // collect mandatory members
22880  const auto op = get_value("op", "op", true).template get<std::string>();
22881  const auto path = get_value(op, "path", true).template get<std::string>();
22882  json_pointer ptr(path);
22883 
22884  switch (get_op(op))
22885  {
22886  case patch_operations::add:
22887  {
22888  operation_add(ptr, get_value("add", "value", false));
22889  break;
22890  }
22891 
22892  case patch_operations::remove:
22893  {
22894  operation_remove(ptr);
22895  break;
22896  }
22897 
22898  case patch_operations::replace:
22899  {
22900  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
22901  result.at(ptr) = get_value("replace", "value", false);
22902  break;
22903  }
22904 
22905  case patch_operations::move:
22906  {
22907  const auto from_path = get_value("move", "from", true).template get<std::string>();
22908  json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
22909 
22910  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
22911  basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
22912 
22913  // The move operation is functionally identical to a
22914  // "remove" operation on the "from" location, followed
22915  // immediately by an "add" operation at the target
22916  // location with the value that was just removed.
22917  operation_remove(from_ptr);
22918  operation_add(ptr, v);
22919  break;
22920  }
22921 
22922  case patch_operations::copy:
22923  {
22924  const auto from_path = get_value("copy", "from", true).template get<std::string>();
22925  const json_pointer from_ptr(from_path);
22926 
22927  // the "from" location must exist - use at()
22928  basic_json v = result.at(from_ptr);
22929 
22930  // The copy is functionally identical to an "add"
22931  // operation at the target location using the value
22932  // specified in the "from" member.
22933  operation_add(ptr, v);
22934  break;
22935  }
22936 
22937  case patch_operations::test:
22938  {
22939  bool success = false;
22940  JSON_TRY
22941  {
22942  // check if "value" matches the one at "path"
22943  // the "path" location must exist - use at()
22944  success = (result.at(ptr) == get_value("test", "value", false));
22945  }
22946  JSON_INTERNAL_CATCH (out_of_range&)
22947  {
22948  // ignore out of range errors: success remains false
22949  }
22950 
22951  // throw an exception if test fails
22952  if (JSON_HEDLEY_UNLIKELY(!success))
22953  {
22954  JSON_THROW(other_error::create(501, detail::concat("unsuccessful: ", val.dump()), &val));
22955  }
22956 
22957  break;
22958  }
22959 
22960  case patch_operations::invalid:
22961  default:
22962  {
22963  // op must be "add", "remove", "replace", "move", "copy", or
22964  // "test"
22965  JSON_THROW(parse_error::create(105, 0, detail::concat("operation value '", op, "' is invalid"), &val));
22966  }
22967  }
22968  }
22969 
22970  return result;
22971  }
22972 
22975  JSON_HEDLEY_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT
22976  static basic_json diff(const basic_json& source, const basic_json& target,
22977  const std::string& path = "")
22978  {
22979  // the patch
22980  basic_json result(value_t::array);
22981 
22982  // if the values are the same, return empty patch
22983  if (source == target)
22984  {
22985  return result;
22986  }
22987 
22988  if (source.type() != target.type())
22989  {
22990  // different types: replace value
22991  result.push_back(
22992  {
22993  {"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}
22994  });
22995  return result;
22996  }
22997 
22998  switch (source.type())
22999  {
23000  case value_t::array:
23001  {
23002  // first pass: traverse common elements
23003  std::size_t i = 0;
23004  while (i < source.size() && i < target.size())
23005  {
23006  // recursive call to compare array values at index i
23007  auto temp_diff = diff(source[i], target[i], detail::concat(path, '/', std::to_string(i)));
23008  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
23009  ++i;
23010  }
23011 
23012  // We now reached the end of at least one array
23013  // in a second pass, traverse the remaining elements
23014 
23015  // remove my remaining elements
23016  const auto end_index = static_cast<difference_type>(result.size());
23017  while (i < source.size())
23018  {
23019  // add operations in reverse order to avoid invalid
23020  // indices
23021  result.insert(result.begin() + end_index, object(
23022  {
23023  {"op", "remove"},
23024  {"path", detail::concat(path, '/', std::to_string(i))}
23025  }));
23026  ++i;
23027  }
23028 
23029  // add other remaining elements
23030  while (i < target.size())
23031  {
23032  result.push_back(
23033  {
23034  {"op", "add"},
23035  {"path", detail::concat(path, "/-")},
23036  {"value", target[i]}
23037  });
23038  ++i;
23039  }
23040 
23041  break;
23042  }
23043 
23044  case value_t::object:
23045  {
23046  // first pass: traverse this object's elements
23047  for (auto it = source.cbegin(); it != source.cend(); ++it)
23048  {
23049  // escape the key name to be used in a JSON patch
23050  const auto path_key = detail::concat(path, '/', detail::escape(it.key()));
23051 
23052  if (target.find(it.key()) != target.end())
23053  {
23054  // recursive call to compare object values at key it
23055  auto temp_diff = diff(it.value(), target[it.key()], path_key);
23056  result.insert(result.end(), temp_diff.begin(), temp_diff.end());
23057  }
23058  else
23059  {
23060  // found a key that is not in o -> remove it
23061  result.push_back(object(
23062  {
23063  {"op", "remove"}, {"path", path_key}
23064  }));
23065  }
23066  }
23067 
23068  // second pass: traverse other object's elements
23069  for (auto it = target.cbegin(); it != target.cend(); ++it)
23070  {
23071  if (source.find(it.key()) == source.end())
23072  {
23073  // found a key that is not in this -> add it
23074  const auto path_key = detail::concat(path, '/', detail::escape(it.key()));
23075  result.push_back(
23076  {
23077  {"op", "add"}, {"path", path_key},
23078  {"value", it.value()}
23079  });
23080  }
23081  }
23082 
23083  break;
23084  }
23085 
23086  case value_t::null:
23087  case value_t::string:
23088  case value_t::boolean:
23089  case value_t::number_integer:
23090  case value_t::number_unsigned:
23091  case value_t::number_float:
23092  case value_t::binary:
23093  case value_t::discarded:
23094  default:
23095  {
23096  // both primitive type: replace value
23097  result.push_back(
23098  {
23099  {"op", "replace"}, {"path", path}, {"value", target}
23100  });
23101  break;
23102  }
23103  }
23104 
23105  return result;
23106  }
23107 
23109 
23111  // JSON Merge Patch functions //
23113 
23116 
23119  void merge_patch(const basic_json& apply_patch)
23120  {
23121  if (apply_patch.is_object())
23122  {
23123  if (!is_object())
23124  {
23125  *this = object();
23126  }
23127  for (auto it = apply_patch.begin(); it != apply_patch.end(); ++it)
23128  {
23129  if (it.value().is_null())
23130  {
23131  erase(it.key());
23132  }
23133  else
23134  {
23135  operator[](it.key()).merge_patch(it.value());
23136  }
23137  }
23138  }
23139  else
23140  {
23141  *this = apply_patch;
23142  }
23143  }
23144 
23146 };
23147

23151 std::string to_string(const NLOHMANN_BASIC_JSON_TPL& j)
23152 {
23153  return j.dump();
23154 }
